89 struct position_t
90 {
92  std::size_t chars_read_total = 0;
94  std::size_t chars_read_current_line = 0;
96  std::size_t lines_read = 0;
97 
99  constexpr operator size_t() const
100  {
101  return chars_read_total;
102  }
103 };
104 
105 } // namespace detail
106 } // namespace nlohmann

114 // exceptions //

145 class exception : public std::exception
146 {
147  public:
149  const char* what() const noexcept override
150  {
151  return m.what();
152  }
153 
155  const int id;
156 
157  protected:
158  exception(int id_, const char* what_arg) : id(id_), m(what_arg) {}
159 
160  static std::string name(const std::string& ename, int id_)
161  {
162  return "[json.exception." + ename + "." + std::to_string(id_) + "] ";
163  }
164 
165  private:
167  std::runtime_error m;
168 };
169 
214 class parse_error : public exception
215 {
216  public:
226  static parse_error create(int id_, const position_t& pos, const std::string& what_arg)
227  {
228  std::string w = exception::name("parse_error", id_) + "parse error" +
229  position_string(pos) + ": " + what_arg;
230  return parse_error(id_, pos.chars_read_total, w.c_str());
231  }
232 
233  static parse_error create(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const std::string& what_arg)
234  {
235  std::string w = exception::name("parse_error", id_) + "parse error" +
236  (byte_ != 0 ? (" at byte " + std::to_string(byte_)) : "") +
237  ": " + what_arg;
238  return parse_error(id_, byte_, w.c_str());
239  }
240 
250  const std::size_t byte;
251 
252  private:
253  parse_error(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const char* what_arg)
254  : exception(id_, what_arg), byte(byte_) {}
255 
256  static std::string position_string(const position_t& pos)
257  {
258  return " at line " + std::to_string(pos.lines_read + 1) +
259  ", column " + std::to_string(pos.chars_read_current_line);
260  }
261 };
262

309  private:

459 // exclude unsupported compilers

461  #if defined(__clang__)
462  #if (__clang_major__ * 10000 + __clang_minor__ * 100 + __clang_patchlevel__) < 30400
463  #error "unsupported Clang version - see https://github.com/nlohmann/json#supported-compilers"
464  #endif
465  #elif defined(__GNUC__) && !(defined(__ICC) || defined(__INTEL_COMPILER))
466  #if (__GNUC__ * 10000 + __GNUC_MINOR__ * 100 + __GNUC_PATCHLEVEL__) < 40800
467  #error "unsupported GCC version - see https://github.com/nlohmann/json#supported-compilers"

472 // C++ language standard detection
473 #if (defined(__cplusplus) && __cplusplus >= 201703L) || (defined(_HAS_CXX17) && _HAS_CXX17 == 1) // fix for issue #464
474  #define JSON_HAS_CPP_17
475  #define JSON_HAS_CPP_14
476 #elif (defined(__cplusplus) && __cplusplus >= 201402L) || (defined(_HAS_CXX14) && _HAS_CXX14 == 1)
477  #define JSON_HAS_CPP_14

492 // allow for portable deprecation warnings
493 #if defined(__clang__) || defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__GNUG__)
494  #define JSON_DEPRECATED __attribute__((deprecated))
495 #elif defined(_MSC_VER)
496  #define JSON_DEPRECATED __declspec(deprecated)
497 #else
498  #define JSON_DEPRECATED
499 #endif

501 // allow for portable nodiscard warnings
502 #if defined(__has_cpp_attribute)
503  #if __has_cpp_attribute(nodiscard)
504  #if defined(__clang__) && !defined(JSON_HAS_CPP_17) // issue #1535
505  #define JSON_NODISCARD
506  #else
507  #define JSON_NODISCARD [[nodiscard]]
508  #endif
509  #elif __has_cpp_attribute(gnu::warn_unused_result)
510  #define JSON_NODISCARD [[gnu::warn_unused_result]]
511  #else
512  #define JSON_NODISCARD
513  #endif
514 #else
515  #define JSON_NODISCARD
516 #endif

518 // allow to disable exceptions
519 #if (defined(__cpp_exceptions) || defined(__EXCEPTIONS) || defined(_CPPUNWIND)) && !defined(JSON_NOEXCEPTION)
520  #define JSON_THROW(exception) throw exception
521  #define JSON_TRY try
522  #define JSON_CATCH(exception) catch(exception)
523  #define JSON_INTERNAL_CATCH(exception) catch(exception)
524 #else
525  #include <cstdlib>
526  #define JSON_THROW(exception) std::abort()
527  #define JSON_TRY if(true)
528  #define JSON_CATCH(exception) if(false)
529  #define JSON_INTERNAL_CATCH(exception) if(false)
530 #endif

534  #undef JSON_THROW
535  #define JSON_THROW JSON_THROW_USER
536 #endif
537 #if defined(JSON_TRY_USER)
538  #undef JSON_TRY
539  #define JSON_TRY JSON_TRY_USER
540 #endif

546 #endif

552 // manual branch prediction
553 #if defined(__clang__) || defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__GNUG__)
554  #define JSON_LIKELY(x) __builtin_expect(x, 1)
555  #define JSON_UNLIKELY(x) __builtin_expect(x, 0)
556 #else
557  #define JSON_LIKELY(x) x
558  #define JSON_UNLIKELY(x) x

566 #define NLOHMANN_JSON_SERIALIZE_ENUM(ENUM_TYPE, ...) \
567  template<typename BasicJsonType> \
568  inline void to_json(BasicJsonType& j, const ENUM_TYPE& e) \
569  { \
570  static_assert(std::is_enum<ENUM_TYPE>::value, #ENUM_TYPE " must be an enum!"); \
571  static const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType> m[] = __VA_ARGS__; \
572  auto it = std::find_if(std::begin(m), std::end(m), \
573  [e](const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType>& ej_pair) -> bool \
574  { \
575  return ej_pair.first == e; \
576  }); \
577  j = ((it != std::end(m)) ? it : std::begin(m))->second; \
578  } \
579  template<typename BasicJsonType> \
580  inline void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ENUM_TYPE& e) \
581  { \
582  static_assert(std::is_enum<ENUM_TYPE>::value, #ENUM_TYPE " must be an enum!"); \
583  static const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType> m[] = __VA_ARGS__; \
584  auto it = std::find_if(std::begin(m), std::end(m), \
585  [j](const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType>& ej_pair) -> bool \
586  { \
587  return ej_pair.second == j; \
588  }); \
589  e = ((it != std::end(m)) ? it : std::begin(m))->first; \
590  }

598  class StringType, class BooleanType, class NumberIntegerType, \
599  class NumberUnsignedType, class NumberFloatType, \
600  template<typename> class AllocatorType, \
601  template<typename, typename = void> class JSONSerializer>

603 #define NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL \
604  basic_json<ObjectType, ArrayType, StringType, BooleanType, \
605  NumberIntegerType, NumberUnsignedType, NumberFloatType, \
606  AllocatorType, JSONSerializer>

626 // implementation of C++14 index_sequence and affiliates
627 // source: https://stackoverflow.com/a/32223343
628 template<std::size_t... Ints>
629 struct index_sequence
630 {
631  using type = index_sequence;
632  using value_type = std::size_t;
633  static constexpr std::size_t size() noexcept
634  {
635  return sizeof...(Ints);
636  }
637 };
638 
639 template<class Sequence1, class Sequence2>
640 struct merge_and_renumber;
641 
642 template<std::size_t... I1, std::size_t... I2>
643 struct merge_and_renumber<index_sequence<I1...>, index_sequence<I2...>>
644  : index_sequence < I1..., (sizeof...(I1) + I2)... > {};
645 
646 template<std::size_t N>
647 struct make_index_sequence
648  : merge_and_renumber < typename make_index_sequence < N / 2 >::type,
649  typename make_index_sequence < N - N / 2 >::type > {};
650 
651 template<> struct make_index_sequence<0> : index_sequence<> {};
652 template<> struct make_index_sequence<1> : index_sequence<0> {};
653 
654 template<typename... Ts>
655 using index_sequence_for = make_index_sequence<sizeof...(Ts)>;
656 
657 // dispatch utility (taken from ranges-v3)
658 template<unsigned N> struct priority_tag : priority_tag < N - 1 > {};
659 template<> struct priority_tag<0> {};

663 struct static_const

665  static constexpr T value{};
666 };
667 
668 template<typename T>
669 constexpr T static_const<T>::value;
670 } // namespace detail

708 template <typename It, typename = void>
709 struct iterator_types {};
710 
711 template <typename It>
712 struct iterator_types <
713  It,
714  void_t<typename It::difference_type, typename It::value_type, typename It::pointer,
715  typename It::reference, typename It::iterator_category >>
716 {
717  using difference_type = typename It::difference_type;
718  using value_type = typename It::value_type;
719  using pointer = typename It::pointer;
720  using reference = typename It::reference;
721  using iterator_category = typename It::iterator_category;
722 };
723 
724 // This is required as some compilers implement std::iterator_traits in a way that
725 // doesn't work with SFINAE. See https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/1341.
726 template <typename T, typename = void>
727 struct iterator_traits
728 {
729 };
730 
731 template <typename T>
732 struct iterator_traits < T, enable_if_t < !std::is_pointer<T>::value >>
733  : iterator_types<T>
734 {
735 };
736 
737 template <typename T>
738 struct iterator_traits<T*, enable_if_t<std::is_object<T>::value>>
739 {
740  using iterator_category = std::random_access_iterator_tag;
741  using value_type = T;
742  using difference_type = ptrdiff_t;
743  using pointer = T*;
744  using reference = T&;
745 };
746 } // namespace detail

761 // http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/experimental/is_detected
762 namespace nlohmann
763 {
764 namespace detail
765 {
766 struct nonesuch
767 {
768  nonesuch() = delete;
769  ~nonesuch() = delete;
770  nonesuch(nonesuch const&) = delete;
771  nonesuch(nonesuch const&&) = delete;
772  void operator=(nonesuch const&) = delete;
773  void operator=(nonesuch&&) = delete;
774 };
775 
776 template <class Default,
777  class AlwaysVoid,
778  template <class...> class Op,
779  class... Args>
780 struct detector
781 {
782  using value_t = std::false_type;
783  using type = Default;
784 };
785 
786 template <class Default, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
787 struct detector<Default, void_t<Op<Args...>>, Op, Args...>
788 {
789  using value_t = std::true_type;
790  using type = Op<Args...>;
791 };
792 
793 template <template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
794 using is_detected = typename detector<nonesuch, void, Op, Args...>::value_t;
795 
796 template <template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
797 using detected_t = typename detector<nonesuch, void, Op, Args...>::type;
798 
799 template <class Default, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
800 using detected_or = detector<Default, void, Op, Args...>;
801 
802 template <class Default, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
803 using detected_or_t = typename detected_or<Default, Op, Args...>::type;
804 
805 template <class Expected, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
806 using is_detected_exact = std::is_same<Expected, detected_t<Op, Args...>>;
807 
808 template <class To, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
809 using is_detected_convertible =
810  std::is_convertible<detected_t<Op, Args...>, To>;
811 } // namespace detail
812 } // namespace nlohmann

894 // helpers //

897 // Note to maintainers:
898 //
899 // Every trait in this file expects a non CV-qualified type.
900 // The only exceptions are in the 'aliases for detected' section
901 // (i.e. those of the form: decltype(T::member_function(std::declval<T>())))
902 //
903 // In this case, T has to be properly CV-qualified to constraint the function arguments
904 // (e.g. to_json(BasicJsonType&, const T&))
905 
906 template<typename> struct is_basic_json : std::false_type {};

908 NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION

945 template <typename T, typename U>
946 using get_template_function = decltype(std::declval<T>().template get<U>());

948 // trait checking if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&, udt&) exists
949 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename = void>
950 struct has_from_json : std::false_type {};
951 
952 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
953 struct has_from_json<BasicJsonType, T,
954  enable_if_t<not is_basic_json<T>::value>>
955 {
956  using serializer = typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>;
957 
958  static constexpr bool value =
959  is_detected_exact<void, from_json_function, serializer,
960  const BasicJsonType&, T&>::value;
961 };

966 struct has_non_default_from_json : std::false_type {};

972

974  is_detected_exact<T, from_json_function, serializer,
975  const BasicJsonType&>::value;

981 struct has_to_json : std::false_type {};

989  is_detected_exact<void, to_json_function, serializer, BasicJsonType&,
990  T>::value;

1057  is_detected<key_type_t, ConstructibleObjectType>::value >>

1062  (std::is_default_constructible<ConstructibleObjectType>::value and

1068  typename object_t::mapped_type,
1069  typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type >::value)) or
1070  (has_from_json<BasicJsonType,
1071  typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value or

1073  BasicJsonType,
1074  typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type >::value);

1122 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
1123 struct is_compatible_array_type_impl <
1124  BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType,
1125  enable_if_t<is_detected<value_type_t, CompatibleArrayType>::value and
1126  is_detected<iterator_t, CompatibleArrayType>::value and
1127 // This is needed because json_reverse_iterator has a ::iterator type...
1128 // Therefore it is detected as a CompatibleArrayType.
1129 // The real fix would be to have an Iterable concept.
1130  not is_iterator_traits<
1131  iterator_traits<CompatibleArrayType>>::value >>
1132 {

1134  std::is_constructible<BasicJsonType,
1135  typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>::value;

1142 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType, typename = void>
1143 struct is_constructible_array_type_impl : std::false_type {};
1144 
1145 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
1146 struct is_constructible_array_type_impl <
1147  BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType,
1148  enable_if_t<std::is_same<ConstructibleArrayType,
1149  typename BasicJsonType::value_type>::value >>
1150  : std::true_type {};
1151 
1152 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
1153 struct is_constructible_array_type_impl <
1154  BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType,
1155  enable_if_t<not std::is_same<ConstructibleArrayType,
1156  typename BasicJsonType::value_type>::value and
1157  std::is_default_constructible<ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
1158 (std::is_move_assignable<ConstructibleArrayType>::value or
1159  std::is_copy_assignable<ConstructibleArrayType>::value) and
1160 is_detected<value_type_t, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
1161 is_detected<iterator_t, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
1162 is_complete_type<
1163 detected_t<value_type_t, ConstructibleArrayType>>::value >>
1164 {
1165  static constexpr bool value =
1166  // This is needed because json_reverse_iterator has a ::iterator type,
1167  // furthermore, std::back_insert_iterator (and other iterators) have a
1168  // base class `iterator`... Therefore it is detected as a
1169  // ConstructibleArrayType. The real fix would be to have an Iterable
1170  // concept.
1171  not is_iterator_traits<iterator_traits<ConstructibleArrayType>>::value and
1172 
1173  (std::is_same<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type,
1174  typename BasicJsonType::array_t::value_type>::value or
1175  has_from_json<BasicJsonType,
1176  typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>::value or
1177  has_non_default_from_json <
1178  BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type >::value);
1179 };

1182 struct is_constructible_array_type
1183  : is_constructible_array_type_impl<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType> {};

1192  enable_if_t<std::is_integral<RealIntegerType>::value and
1193  std::is_integral<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
1194  not std::is_same<bool, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value >>
1195 {
1196  // is there an assert somewhere on overflows?
1197  using RealLimits = std::numeric_limits<RealIntegerType>;
1198  using CompatibleLimits = std::numeric_limits<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>;
1199 
1200  static constexpr auto value =
1201  std::is_constructible<RealIntegerType,
1202  CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
1203  CompatibleLimits::is_integer and
1204  RealLimits::is_signed == CompatibleLimits::is_signed;
1205 };

1239 namespace nlohmann
1240 {
1241 namespace detail
1242 {
1244 // JSON type enumeration //
1246 
1271 enum class value_t : std::uint8_t
1272 {
1273  null,
1274  object,
1275  array,
1276  string,
1277  boolean,
1278  number_integer,
1279  number_unsigned,
1280  number_float,
1281  discarded
1282 };
1283 
1294 inline bool operator<(const value_t lhs, const value_t rhs) noexcept
1295 {
1296  static constexpr std::array<std::uint8_t, 8> order = {{
1297  0 /* null */, 3 /* object */, 4 /* array */, 5 /* string */,
1298  1 /* boolean */, 2 /* integer */, 2 /* unsigned */, 2 /* float */
1299  }
1300  };
1301 
1302  const auto l_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(lhs);
1303  const auto r_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(rhs);
1304  return l_index < order.size() and r_index < order.size() and order[l_index] < order[r_index];
1305 }
1306 } // namespace detail
1307 } // namespace nlohmann

1312 namespace detail

1314 template<typename BasicJsonType>
1315 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename std::nullptr_t& n)
1316 {
1317  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_null()))
1318  {
1319  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be null, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1320  }
1321  n = nullptr;
1322 }
1323 
1324 // overloads for basic_json template parameters
1325 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
1326  enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
1327  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
1328  int> = 0>
1329 void get_arithmetic_value(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
1330 {
1331  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j))
1332  {
1333  case value_t::number_unsigned:
1334  {
1335  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
1336  break;
1337  }
1338  case value_t::number_integer:
1339  {
1340  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
1341  break;
1342  }
1343  case value_t::number_float:
1344  {
1345  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
1346  break;
1347  }
1348 
1349  default:
1350  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1351  }
1352 }
1353

1355 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t& b)

1358  {
1359  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be boolean, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1360  }
1361  b = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>();
1362 }

1372 }

1418 // forward_list doesn't have an insert method
1419 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename Allocator,
1420  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
1421 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::forward_list<T, Allocator>& l)
1422 {
1423  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1424  {
1425  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1426  }
1427  l.clear();
1428  std::transform(j.rbegin(), j.rend(),
1429  std::front_inserter(l), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1430  {
1431  return i.template get<T>();
1432  });
1433 }
1434 
1435 // valarray doesn't have an insert method
1436 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T,
1437  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
1438 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::valarray<T>& l)
1439 {
1440  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1441  {
1442  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1443  }
1444  l.resize(j.size());
1445  std::copy(j.m_value.array->begin(), j.m_value.array->end(), std::begin(l));
1446 }

1448 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, std::size_t N>
1449 auto from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, T (&arr)[N])
1450 -> decltype(j.template get<T>(), void())
1451 {
1452  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < N; ++i)
1453  {
1454  arr[i] = j.at(i).template get<T>();
1455  }
1456 }

1460 {

1464 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, std::size_t N>
1465 auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, std::array<T, N>& arr,
1466  priority_tag<2> /*unused*/)
1467 -> decltype(j.template get<T>(), void())
1468 {
1469  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < N; ++i)
1470  {
1471  arr[i] = j.at(i).template get<T>();
1472  }

1475 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
1476 auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/)
1477 -> decltype(
1478  arr.reserve(std::declval<typename ConstructibleArrayType::size_type>()),
1479  j.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>(),
1480  void())
1481 {
1482  using std::end;
1483 
1484  ConstructibleArrayType ret;
1485  ret.reserve(j.size());
1486  std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(),
1487  std::inserter(ret, end(ret)), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1488  {
1489  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1490  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1491  return i.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>();
1492  });
1493  arr = std::move(ret);
1494 }
1495 
1496 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
1497 void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleArrayType& arr,
1498  priority_tag<0> /*unused*/)
1499 {
1500  using std::end;
1501 
1502  ConstructibleArrayType ret;
1503  std::transform(
1504  j.begin(), j.end(), std::inserter(ret, end(ret)),
1505  [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1506  {
1507  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1508  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1509  return i.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>();
1510  });
1511  arr = std::move(ret);
1512 }
1513 
1514 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType,
1515  enable_if_t <
1516  is_constructible_array_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
1517  not is_constructible_object_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
1518  not is_constructible_string_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
1519  not is_basic_json<ConstructibleArrayType>::value,
1520  int > = 0 >
1521 
1522 auto from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleArrayType& arr)
1523 -> decltype(from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<3> {}),
1524 j.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>(),
1525 void())
1526 {
1527  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1528  {
1529  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " +
1530  std::string(j.type_name())));
1531  }
1532 
1533  from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<3> {});
1534 }
1535 
1536 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleObjectType,
1537  enable_if_t<is_constructible_object_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleObjectType>::value, int> = 0>
1538 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleObjectType& obj)
1539 {
1540  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_object()))
1541  {
1542  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be object, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1543  }
1544 
1545  ConstructibleObjectType ret;
1546  auto inner_object = j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::object_t*>();
1547  using value_type = typename ConstructibleObjectType::value_type;
1548  std::transform(
1549  inner_object->begin(), inner_object->end(),
1550  std::inserter(ret, ret.begin()),
1551  [](typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type const & p)
1552  {
1553  return value_type(p.first, p.second.template get<typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type>());
1554  });
1555  obj = std::move(ret);
1556 }
1557 
1558 // overload for arithmetic types, not chosen for basic_json template arguments
1559 // (BooleanType, etc..); note: Is it really necessary to provide explicit
1560 // overloads for boolean_t etc. in case of a custom BooleanType which is not
1561 // an arithmetic type?
1562 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
1563  enable_if_t <
1564  std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
1565  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t>::value and
1566  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t>::value and
1567  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t>::value and
1568  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
1569  int> = 0>
1570 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
1571 {
1572  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j))
1573  {
1574  case value_t::number_unsigned:
1575  {
1576  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
1577  break;
1578  }
1579  case value_t::number_integer:
1580  {
1581  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
1582  break;
1583  }
1584  case value_t::number_float:
1585  {
1586  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
1587  break;
1588  }
1589  case value_t::boolean:
1590  {
1591  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>());
1592  break;
1593  }
1594 
1595  default:
1596  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1597  }
1598 }
1599 
1600 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename A1, typename A2>
1601 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::pair<A1, A2>& p)
1602 {
1603  p = {j.at(0).template get<A1>(), j.at(1).template get<A2>()};
1604 }
1605 
1606 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename Tuple, std::size_t... Idx>
1607 void from_json_tuple_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, Tuple& t, index_sequence<Idx...> /*unused*/)
1608 {
1609  t = std::make_tuple(j.at(Idx).template get<typename std::tuple_element<Idx, Tuple>::type>()...);
1610 }
1611 
1612 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename... Args>
1613 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::tuple<Args...>& t)
1614 {
1615  from_json_tuple_impl(j, t, index_sequence_for<Args...> {});
1616 }
1617 
1618 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename Key, typename Value, typename Compare, typename Allocator,
1619  typename = enable_if_t<not std::is_constructible<
1620  typename BasicJsonType::string_t, Key>::value>>
1621 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::map<Key, Value, Compare, Allocator>& m)
1622 {
1623  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1624  {
1625  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1626  }
1627  m.clear();
1628  for (const auto& p : j)
1629  {
1630  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not p.is_array()))
1631  {
1632  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(p.type_name())));
1633  }
1634  m.emplace(p.at(0).template get<Key>(), p.at(1).template get<Value>());
1635  }
1636 }
1637 
1638 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename Key, typename Value, typename Hash, typename KeyEqual, typename Allocator,
1639  typename = enable_if_t<not std::is_constructible<
1640  typename BasicJsonType::string_t, Key>::value>>
1641 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::unordered_map<Key, Value, Hash, KeyEqual, Allocator>& m)
1642 {
1643  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1644  {
1645  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1646  }
1647  m.clear();
1648  for (const auto& p : j)
1649  {
1650  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not p.is_array()))
1651  {
1652  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(p.type_name())));
1653  }
1654  m.emplace(p.at(0).template get<Key>(), p.at(1).template get<Value>());
1655  }
1656 }
1657 
1658 struct from_json_fn
1659 {
1660  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1661  auto operator()(const BasicJsonType& j, T& val) const
1662  noexcept(noexcept(from_json(j, val)))
1663  -> decltype(from_json(j, val), void())
1664  {
1665  return from_json(j, val);
1666  }
1667 };
1668 } // namespace detail

1705 namespace nlohmann
1706 {
1707 namespace detail
1708 {
1709 template <typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy_value
1710 {
1711  public:
1712  using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
1713  using value_type = iteration_proxy_value;
1714  using pointer = value_type * ;
1715  using reference = value_type & ;
1716  using iterator_category = std::input_iterator_tag;
1717 
1718  private:
1720  IteratorType anchor;
1722  std::size_t array_index = 0;
1724  mutable std::size_t array_index_last = 0;
1726  mutable std::string array_index_str = "0";
1728  const std::string empty_str = "";
1729 
1730  public:
1731  explicit iteration_proxy_value(IteratorType it) noexcept : anchor(it) {}
1732 
1734  iteration_proxy_value& operator*()
1735  {
1736  return *this;
1737  }
1738 
1740  iteration_proxy_value& operator++()
1741  {
1742  ++anchor;
1743  ++array_index;
1744 
1745  return *this;
1746  }
1747 
1749  bool operator==(const iteration_proxy_value& o) const
1750  {
1751  return anchor == o.anchor;
1752  }
1753 
1755  bool operator!=(const iteration_proxy_value& o) const
1756  {
1757  return anchor != o.anchor;
1758  }
1759 
1761  const std::string& key() const
1762  {
1763  assert(anchor.m_object != nullptr);
1764 
1765  switch (anchor.m_object->type())
1766  {
1767  // use integer array index as key
1768  case value_t::array:
1769  {
1770  if (array_index != array_index_last)
1771  {
1772  array_index_str = std::to_string(array_index);
1773  array_index_last = array_index;
1774  }
1775  return array_index_str;
1776  }
1777 
1778  // use key from the object
1779  case value_t::object:
1780  return anchor.key();
1781 
1782  // use an empty key for all primitive types
1783  default:
1784  return empty_str;
1785  }
1786  }
1787 
1789  typename IteratorType::reference value() const
1790  {
1791  return anchor.value();
1792  }
1793 };
1794 
1796 template<typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy
1797 {
1798  private:
1800  typename IteratorType::reference container;
1801 
1802  public:
1804  explicit iteration_proxy(typename IteratorType::reference cont) noexcept
1805  : container(cont) {}
1806 
1808  iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType> begin() noexcept
1809  {
1810  return iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>(container.begin());
1811  }
1812 
1814  iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType> end() noexcept
1815  {
1816  return iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>(container.end());
1817  }
1818 };
1819 // Structured Bindings Support
1820 // For further reference see https://blog.tartanllama.xyz/structured-bindings/
1821 // And see https://github.com/nlohmann/json/pull/1391
1822 template <std::size_t N, typename IteratorType, enable_if_t<N == 0, int> = 0>
1823 auto get(const nlohmann::detail::iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>& i) -> decltype(i.key())
1824 {
1825  return i.key();
1826 }
1827 // Structured Bindings Support
1828 // For further reference see https://blog.tartanllama.xyz/structured-bindings/
1829 // And see https://github.com/nlohmann/json/pull/1391
1830 template <std::size_t N, typename IteratorType, enable_if_t<N == 1, int> = 0>
1831 auto get(const nlohmann::detail::iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>& i) -> decltype(i.value())
1832 {
1833  return i.value();
1834 }
1835 } // namespace detail
1836 } // namespace nlohmann

1980  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType,
1981  enable_if_t<not std::is_same<CompatibleArrayType, typename BasicJsonType::array_t>::value,
1982  int> = 0>
1983  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const CompatibleArrayType& arr)
1984  {
1985  using std::begin;
1986  using std::end;
1987  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1988  j.m_value.array = j.template create<typename BasicJsonType::array_t>(begin(arr), end(arr));
1989  j.assert_invariant();

1991 
1992  template<typename BasicJsonType>
1993  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const std::vector<bool>& arr)
1994  {
1995  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1996  j.m_value = value_t::array;
1997  j.m_value.array->reserve(arr.size());
1998  for (const bool x : arr)
1999  {
2000  j.m_value.array->push_back(x);
2001  }
2002  j.assert_invariant();
2003  }
2004 
2005  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T,
2006  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<T, BasicJsonType>::value, int> = 0>
2007  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const std::valarray<T>& arr)
2008  {
2009  j.m_type = value_t::array;
2010  j.m_value = value_t::array;
2011  j.m_value.array->resize(arr.size());
2012  std::copy(std::begin(arr), std::end(arr), j.m_value.array->begin());
2013  j.assert_invariant();
2014  }
2015 };

2183 struct to_json_fn
2184 {
2185  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
2186  auto operator()(BasicJsonType& j, T&& val) const noexcept(noexcept(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val))))
2187  -> decltype(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val)), void())
2188  {
2189  return to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val));
2190  }
2191 };

2312 struct input_adapter_protocol
2313 {
2315  virtual std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() = 0;
2316  virtual ~input_adapter_protocol() = default;
2317 };

2326 class file_input_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
2327 {
2328  public:
2329  explicit file_input_adapter(std::FILE* f) noexcept
2330  : m_file(f)
2331  {}
2332 
2333  // make class move-only
2334  file_input_adapter(const file_input_adapter&) = delete;
2335  file_input_adapter(file_input_adapter&&) = default;
2336  file_input_adapter& operator=(const file_input_adapter&) = delete;
2337  file_input_adapter& operator=(file_input_adapter&&) = default;
2338  ~file_input_adapter() override = default;

2360 class input_stream_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
2361 {
2362  public:
2363  ~input_stream_adapter() override
2364  {
2365  // clear stream flags; we use underlying streambuf I/O, do not
2366  // maintain ifstream flags, except eof
2367  is.clear(is.rdstate() & std::ios::eofbit);
2368  }
2369 
2370  explicit input_stream_adapter(std::istream& i)
2371  : is(i), sb(*i.rdbuf())
2372  {}
2373 
2374  // delete because of pointer members
2375  input_stream_adapter(const input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
2376  input_stream_adapter& operator=(input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
2377  input_stream_adapter(input_stream_adapter&&) = delete;
2378  input_stream_adapter& operator=(input_stream_adapter&&) = delete;
2379 
2380  // std::istream/std::streambuf use std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type, to
2381  // ensure that std::char_traits<char>::eof() and the character 0xFF do not
2382  // end up as the same value, eg. 0xFFFFFFFF.
2383  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() override
2384  {
2385  auto res = sb.sbumpc();
2386  // set eof manually, as we don't use the istream interface.
2387  if (res == EOF)
2388  {
2389  is.clear(is.rdstate() | std::ios::eofbit);
2390  }
2391  return res;
2392  }
2393 
2394  private:
2396  std::istream& is;
2397  std::streambuf& sb;
2398 };

2401 class input_buffer_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
2402 {
2403  public:
2404  input_buffer_adapter(const char* b, const std::size_t l) noexcept
2405  : cursor(b), limit(b + l)
2406  {}
2407 
2408  // delete because of pointer members
2409  input_buffer_adapter(const input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
2410  input_buffer_adapter& operator=(input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
2411  input_buffer_adapter(input_buffer_adapter&&) = delete;
2412  input_buffer_adapter& operator=(input_buffer_adapter&&) = delete;
2413  ~input_buffer_adapter() override = default;
2414 
2415  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override
2416  {
2417  if (JSON_LIKELY(cursor < limit))
2418  {
2419  return std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type(*(cursor++));
2420  }
2421 
2422  return std::char_traits<char>::eof();
2423  }
2424 
2425  private:
2427  const char* cursor;
2429  const char* const limit;
2430 };

2432 template<typename WideStringType, size_t T>
2433 struct wide_string_input_helper
2434 {
2435  // UTF-32
2436  static void fill_buffer(const WideStringType& str,
2437  size_t& current_wchar,
2438  std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4>& utf8_bytes,
2439  size_t& utf8_bytes_index,
2440  size_t& utf8_bytes_filled)
2441  {
2442  utf8_bytes_index = 0;
2443 
2444  if (current_wchar == str.size())
2445  {
2446  utf8_bytes[0] = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
2447  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2448  }
2449  else
2450  {
2451  // get the current character
2452  const auto wc = static_cast<unsigned int>(str[current_wchar++]);
2453 
2454  // UTF-32 to UTF-8 encoding
2455  if (wc < 0x80)
2456  {
2457  utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
2458  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2459  }
2460  else if (wc <= 0x7FF)
2461  {
2462  utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xC0u | ((wc >> 6u) & 0x1Fu));
2463  utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
2464  utf8_bytes_filled = 2;
2465  }
2466  else if (wc <= 0xFFFF)
2467  {
2468  utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xE0u | ((wc >> 12u) & 0x0Fu));
2469  utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((wc >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
2470  utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
2471  utf8_bytes_filled = 3;
2472  }
2473  else if (wc <= 0x10FFFF)
2474  {
2475  utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xF0u | ((wc >> 18u) & 0x07u));
2476  utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((wc >> 12u) & 0x3Fu));
2477  utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((wc >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
2478  utf8_bytes[3] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
2479  utf8_bytes_filled = 4;
2480  }
2481  else
2482  {
2483  // unknown character
2484  utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
2485  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2486  }
2487  }
2488  }
2489 };
2490 
2491 template<typename WideStringType>
2492 struct wide_string_input_helper<WideStringType, 2>
2493 {
2494  // UTF-16
2495  static void fill_buffer(const WideStringType& str,
2496  size_t& current_wchar,
2497  std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4>& utf8_bytes,
2498  size_t& utf8_bytes_index,
2499  size_t& utf8_bytes_filled)
2500  {
2501  utf8_bytes_index = 0;
2502 
2503  if (current_wchar == str.size())
2504  {
2505  utf8_bytes[0] = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
2506  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2507  }
2508  else
2509  {
2510  // get the current character
2511  const auto wc = static_cast<unsigned int>(str[current_wchar++]);
2512 
2513  // UTF-16 to UTF-8 encoding
2514  if (wc < 0x80)
2515  {
2516  utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
2517  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2518  }
2519  else if (wc <= 0x7FF)
2520  {
2521  utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xC0u | ((wc >> 6u)));
2522  utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
2523  utf8_bytes_filled = 2;
2524  }
2525  else if (0xD800 > wc or wc >= 0xE000)
2526  {
2527  utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xE0u | ((wc >> 12u)));
2528  utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((wc >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
2529  utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
2530  utf8_bytes_filled = 3;
2531  }
2532  else
2533  {
2534  if (current_wchar < str.size())
2535  {
2536  const auto wc2 = static_cast<unsigned int>(str[current_wchar++]);
2537  const auto charcode = 0x10000u + (((wc & 0x3FFu) << 10u) | (wc2 & 0x3FFu));
2538  utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xF0u | (charcode >> 18u));
2539  utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((charcode >> 12u) & 0x3Fu));
2540  utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((charcode >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
2541  utf8_bytes[3] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (charcode & 0x3Fu));
2542  utf8_bytes_filled = 4;
2543  }
2544  else
2545  {
2546  // unknown character
2547  ++current_wchar;
2548  utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
2549  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2550  }
2551  }
2552  }
2553  }
2554 };
2555 
2556 template<typename WideStringType>
2557 class wide_string_input_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
2558 {
2559  public:
2560  explicit wide_string_input_adapter(const WideStringType& w) noexcept
2561  : str(w)
2562  {}
2563 
2564  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override
2565  {
2566  // check if buffer needs to be filled
2567  if (utf8_bytes_index == utf8_bytes_filled)
2568  {
2569  fill_buffer<sizeof(typename WideStringType::value_type)>();
2570 
2571  assert(utf8_bytes_filled > 0);
2572  assert(utf8_bytes_index == 0);
2573  }
2574 
2575  // use buffer
2576  assert(utf8_bytes_filled > 0);
2577  assert(utf8_bytes_index < utf8_bytes_filled);
2578  return utf8_bytes[utf8_bytes_index++];
2579  }
2580 
2581  private:
2582  template<size_t T>
2583  void fill_buffer()
2584  {
2585  wide_string_input_helper<WideStringType, T>::fill_buffer(str, current_wchar, utf8_bytes, utf8_bytes_index, utf8_bytes_filled);
2586  }
2587 
2589  const WideStringType& str;
2590 
2592  std::size_t current_wchar = 0;
2593 
2595  std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4> utf8_bytes = {{0, 0, 0, 0}};
2596 
2598  std::size_t utf8_bytes_index = 0;
2600  std::size_t utf8_bytes_filled = 0;
2601 };

2603 class input_adapter
2604 {
2605  public:
2606  // native support
2607  input_adapter(std::FILE* file)
2608  : ia(std::make_shared<file_input_adapter>(file)) {}
2610  input_adapter(std::istream& i)
2611  : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {}
2612 
2614  input_adapter(std::istream&& i)
2615  : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {}
2616 
2617  input_adapter(const std::wstring& ws)
2618  : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::wstring>>(ws)) {}
2619 
2620  input_adapter(const std::u16string& ws)
2621  : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::u16string>>(ws)) {}

2627  template<typename CharT,
2628  typename std::enable_if<
2629  std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
2630  std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
2631  sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
2632  int>::type = 0>
2633  input_adapter(CharT b, std::size_t l)
2634  : ia(std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b), l)) {}
2635 
2636  // derived support
2637 
2639  template<typename CharT,
2640  typename std::enable_if<
2641  std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
2642  std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
2643  sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
2644  int>::type = 0>
2645  input_adapter(CharT b)
2646  : input_adapter(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b),
2647  std::strlen(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b))) {}
2648 
2650  template<class IteratorType,
2651  typename std::enable_if<
2652  std::is_same<typename iterator_traits<IteratorType>::iterator_category, std::random_access_iterator_tag>::value,
2653  int>::type = 0>
2654  input_adapter(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
2655  {
2656 #ifndef NDEBUG
2657  // assertion to check that the iterator range is indeed contiguous,
2658  // see http://stackoverflow.com/a/35008842/266378 for more discussion
2659  const auto is_contiguous = std::accumulate(
2660  first, last, std::pair<bool, int>(true, 0),
2661  [&first](std::pair<bool, int> res, decltype(*first) val)
2662  {
2663  res.first &= (val == *(std::next(std::addressof(*first), res.second++)));
2664  return res;
2665  }).first;
2666  assert(is_contiguous);
2667 #endif
2668 
2669  // assertion to check that each element is 1 byte long
2670  static_assert(
2671  sizeof(typename iterator_traits<IteratorType>::value_type) == 1,
2672  "each element in the iterator range must have the size of 1 byte");
2673 
2674  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(std::distance(first, last));
2675  if (JSON_LIKELY(len > 0))
2676  {
2677  // there is at least one element: use the address of first
2678  ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(&(*first)), len);
2679  }
2680  else
2681  {
2682  // the address of first cannot be used: use nullptr
2683  ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(nullptr, len);
2684  }
2685  }
2686 
2688  template<class T, std::size_t N>
2689  input_adapter(T (&array)[N])
2690  : input_adapter(std::begin(array), std::end(array)) {}
2691 
2693  template<class ContiguousContainer, typename
2694  std::enable_if<not std::is_pointer<ContiguousContainer>::value and
2695  std::is_base_of<std::random_access_iterator_tag, typename iterator_traits<decltype(std::begin(std::declval<ContiguousContainer const>()))>::iterator_category>::value,
2696  int>::type = 0>
2697  input_adapter(const ContiguousContainer& c)
2698  : input_adapter(std::begin(c), std::end(c)) {}
2699 
2700  operator input_adapter_t()
2701  {
2702  return ia;
2703  }
2704 
2705  private:
2707  input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
2708 };

2858 template<typename BasicJsonType>
2859 class json_sax_dom_parser
2860 {
2861  public:
2862  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
2863  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
2864  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
2865  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
2866 
2872  explicit json_sax_dom_parser(BasicJsonType& r, const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
2873  : root(r), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
2874  {}
2875 
2876  // make class move-only
2877  json_sax_dom_parser(const json_sax_dom_parser&) = delete;
2878  json_sax_dom_parser(json_sax_dom_parser&&) = default;
2879  json_sax_dom_parser& operator=(const json_sax_dom_parser&) = delete;
2880  json_sax_dom_parser& operator=(json_sax_dom_parser&&) = default;
2881  ~json_sax_dom_parser() = default;
2882 
2883  bool null()
2884  {
2885  handle_value(nullptr);
2886  return true;
2887  }
2888 
2889  bool boolean(bool val)
2890  {
2891  handle_value(val);
2892  return true;
2893  }
2894 
2895  bool number_integer(number_integer_t val)
2896  {
2897  handle_value(val);
2898  return true;
2899  }
2900 
2901  bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t val)
2902  {
2903  handle_value(val);
2904  return true;
2905  }
2906 
2907  bool number_float(number_float_t val, const string_t& /*unused*/)
2908  {
2909  handle_value(val);
2910  return true;
2911  }
2912 
2913  bool string(string_t& val)
2914  {
2915  handle_value(val);
2916  return true;
2917  }
2918 
2919  bool start_object(std::size_t len)
2920  {
2921  ref_stack.push_back(handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::object));
2922 
2923  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
2924  {
2925  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408,
2926  "excessive object size: " + std::to_string(len)));
2927  }
2928 
2929  return true;
2930  }
2931 
2932  bool key(string_t& val)
2933  {
2934  // add null at given key and store the reference for later
2935  object_element = &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.object->operator[](val));
2936  return true;
2937  }
2938 
2939  bool end_object()
2940  {
2941  ref_stack.pop_back();
2942  return true;
2943  }
2944 
2945  bool start_array(std::size_t len)
2946  {
2947  ref_stack.push_back(handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::array));
2948 
2949  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
2950  {
2951  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408,
2952  "excessive array size: " + std::to_string(len)));
2953  }
2954 
2955  return true;
2956  }
2957 
2958  bool end_array()
2959  {
2960  ref_stack.pop_back();
2961  return true;
2962  }
2963 
2964  bool parse_error(std::size_t /*unused*/, const std::string& /*unused*/,
2965  const detail::exception& ex)
2966  {
2967  errored = true;
2968  if (allow_exceptions)
2969  {
2970  // determine the proper exception type from the id
2971  switch ((ex.id / 100) % 100)
2972  {
2973  case 1:
2974  JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::parse_error*>(&ex));
2975  case 4:
2976  JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::out_of_range*>(&ex));
2977  // LCOV_EXCL_START
2978  case 2:
2979  JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::invalid_iterator*>(&ex));
2980  case 3:
2981  JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::type_error*>(&ex));
2982  case 5:
2983  JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::other_error*>(&ex));
2984  default:
2985  assert(false);
2986  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
2987  }
2988  }
2989  return false;
2990  }
2991 
2992  constexpr bool is_errored() const
2993  {
2994  return errored;
2995  }
2996 
2997  private:
3004  template<typename Value>
3005  BasicJsonType* handle_value(Value&& v)
3006  {
3007  if (ref_stack.empty())
3008  {
3009  root = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
3010  return &root;
3011  }
3012 
3013  assert(ref_stack.back()->is_array() or ref_stack.back()->is_object());
3014 
3015  if (ref_stack.back()->is_array())
3016  {
3017  ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->emplace_back(std::forward<Value>(v));
3018  return &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->back());
3019  }
3020 
3021  assert(ref_stack.back()->is_object());
3022  assert(object_element);
3023  *object_element = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
3024  return object_element;
3025  }
3026 
3028  BasicJsonType& root;
3030  std::vector<BasicJsonType*> ref_stack {};
3032  BasicJsonType* object_element = nullptr;
3034  bool errored = false;
3036  const bool allow_exceptions = true;
3037 };
3038 
3039 template<typename BasicJsonType>
3040 class json_sax_dom_callback_parser
3041 {
3042  public:
3043  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3044  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3045  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3046  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3047  using parser_callback_t = typename BasicJsonType::parser_callback_t;
3048  using parse_event_t = typename BasicJsonType::parse_event_t;
3049 
3050  json_sax_dom_callback_parser(BasicJsonType& r,
3051  const parser_callback_t cb,
3052  const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
3053  : root(r), callback(cb), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
3054  {
3055  keep_stack.push_back(true);
3056  }
3057 
3058  // make class move-only
3059  json_sax_dom_callback_parser(const json_sax_dom_callback_parser&) = delete;
3060  json_sax_dom_callback_parser(json_sax_dom_callback_parser&&) = default;
3061  json_sax_dom_callback_parser& operator=(const json_sax_dom_callback_parser&) = delete;
3062  json_sax_dom_callback_parser& operator=(json_sax_dom_callback_parser&&) = default;
3063  ~json_sax_dom_callback_parser() = default;
3064 
3065  bool null()
3066  {
3067  handle_value(nullptr);
3068  return true;
3069  }
3070 
3071  bool boolean(bool val)
3072  {
3073  handle_value(val);
3074  return true;
3075  }
3076 
3077  bool number_integer(number_integer_t val)
3078  {
3079  handle_value(val);
3080  return true;
3081  }
3082 
3083  bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t val)
3084  {
3085  handle_value(val);
3086  return true;
3087  }
3088 
3089  bool number_float(number_float_t val, const string_t& /*unused*/)
3090  {
3091  handle_value(val);
3092  return true;
3093  }
3094 
3095  bool string(string_t& val)
3096  {
3097  handle_value(val);
3098  return true;
3099  }
3100 
3101  bool start_object(std::size_t len)
3102  {
3103  // check callback for object start
3104  const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::object_start, discarded);
3105  keep_stack.push_back(keep);
3106 
3107  auto val = handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::object, true);
3108  ref_stack.push_back(val.second);
3109 
3110  // check object limit
3111  if (ref_stack.back() and JSON_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
3112  {
3113  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408, "excessive object size: " + std::to_string(len)));
3114  }
3115 
3116  return true;
3117  }
3118 
3119  bool key(string_t& val)
3120  {
3121  BasicJsonType k = BasicJsonType(val);
3122 
3123  // check callback for key
3124  const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::key, k);
3125  key_keep_stack.push_back(keep);
3126 
3127  // add discarded value at given key and store the reference for later
3128  if (keep and ref_stack.back())
3129  {
3130  object_element = &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.object->operator[](val) = discarded);
3131  }
3132 
3133  return true;
3134  }
3135 
3136  bool end_object()
3137  {
3138  if (ref_stack.back() and not callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()) - 1, parse_event_t::object_end, *ref_stack.back()))
3139  {
3140  // discard object
3141  *ref_stack.back() = discarded;
3142  }
3143 
3144  assert(not ref_stack.empty());
3145  assert(not keep_stack.empty());
3146  ref_stack.pop_back();
3147  keep_stack.pop_back();
3148 
3149  if (not ref_stack.empty() and ref_stack.back() and ref_stack.back()->is_object())
3150  {
3151  // remove discarded value
3152  for (auto it = ref_stack.back()->begin(); it != ref_stack.back()->end(); ++it)
3153  {
3154  if (it->is_discarded())
3155  {
3156  ref_stack.back()->erase(it);
3157  break;
3158  }
3159  }
3160  }
3161 
3162  return true;
3163  }
3164 
3165  bool start_array(std::size_t len)
3166  {
3167  const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::array_start, discarded);
3168  keep_stack.push_back(keep);
3169 
3170  auto val = handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::array, true);
3171  ref_stack.push_back(val.second);
3172 
3173  // check array limit
3174  if (ref_stack.back() and JSON_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
3175  {
3176  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408, "excessive array size: " + std::to_string(len)));
3177  }
3178 
3179  return true;
3180  }
3181 
3182  bool end_array()
3183  {
3184  bool keep = true;
3185 
3186  if (ref_stack.back())
3187  {
3188  keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()) - 1, parse_event_t::array_end, *ref_stack.back());
3189  if (not keep)
3190  {
3191  // discard array
3192  *ref_stack.back() = discarded;
3193  }
3194  }
3195 
3196  assert(not ref_stack.empty());
3197  assert(not keep_stack.empty());
3198  ref_stack.pop_back();
3199  keep_stack.pop_back();
3200 
3201  // remove discarded value
3202  if (not keep and not ref_stack.empty() and ref_stack.back()->is_array())
3203  {
3204  ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->pop_back();
3205  }
3206 
3207  return true;
3208  }
3209 
3210  bool parse_error(std::size_t /*unused*/, const std::string& /*unused*/,
3211  const detail::exception& ex)
3212  {
3213  errored = true;
3214  if (allow_exceptions)
3215  {
3216  // determine the proper exception type from the id
3217  switch ((ex.id / 100) % 100)
3218  {
3219  case 1:
3220  JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::parse_error*>(&ex));
3221  case 4:
3222  JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::out_of_range*>(&ex));
3223  // LCOV_EXCL_START
3224  case 2:
3225  JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::invalid_iterator*>(&ex));
3226  case 3:
3227  JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::type_error*>(&ex));
3228  case 5:
3229  JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::other_error*>(&ex));
3230  default:
3231  assert(false);
3232  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
3233  }
3234  }
3235  return false;
3236  }
3237 
3238  constexpr bool is_errored() const
3239  {
3240  return errored;
3241  }
3242 
3243  private:
3259  template<typename Value>
3260  std::pair<bool, BasicJsonType*> handle_value(Value&& v, const bool skip_callback = false)
3261  {
3262  assert(not keep_stack.empty());
3263 
3264  // do not handle this value if we know it would be added to a discarded
3265  // container
3266  if (not keep_stack.back())
3267  {
3268  return {false, nullptr};
3269  }
3270 
3271  // create value
3272  auto value = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
3273 
3274  // check callback
3275  const bool keep = skip_callback or callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::value, value);
3276 
3277  // do not handle this value if we just learnt it shall be discarded
3278  if (not keep)
3279  {
3280  return {false, nullptr};
3281  }
3282 
3283  if (ref_stack.empty())
3284  {
3285  root = std::move(value);
3286  return {true, &root};
3287  }
3288 
3289  // skip this value if we already decided to skip the parent
3290  // (https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/971#issuecomment-413678360)
3291  if (not ref_stack.back())
3292  {
3293  return {false, nullptr};
3294  }
3295 
3296  // we now only expect arrays and objects
3297  assert(ref_stack.back()->is_array() or ref_stack.back()->is_object());
3298 
3299  // array
3300  if (ref_stack.back()->is_array())
3301  {
3302  ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->push_back(std::move(value));
3303  return {true, &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->back())};
3304  }
3305 
3306  // object
3307  assert(ref_stack.back()->is_object());
3308  // check if we should store an element for the current key
3309  assert(not key_keep_stack.empty());
3310  const bool store_element = key_keep_stack.back();
3311  key_keep_stack.pop_back();
3312 
3313  if (not store_element)
3314  {
3315  return {false, nullptr};
3316  }
3317 
3318  assert(object_element);
3319  *object_element = std::move(value);
3320  return {true, object_element};
3321  }
3322 
3324  BasicJsonType& root;
3326  std::vector<BasicJsonType*> ref_stack {};
3328  std::vector<bool> keep_stack {};
3330  std::vector<bool> key_keep_stack {};
3332  BasicJsonType* object_element = nullptr;
3334  bool errored = false;
3336  const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
3338  const bool allow_exceptions = true;
3340  BasicJsonType discarded = BasicJsonType::value_t::discarded;
3341 };

3434 template <typename T>
3435 using null_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().null());
3436 
3437 template <typename T>
3438 using boolean_function_t =
3439  decltype(std::declval<T&>().boolean(std::declval<bool>()));
3440 
3441 template <typename T, typename Integer>
3442 using number_integer_function_t =
3443  decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_integer(std::declval<Integer>()));
3444 
3445 template <typename T, typename Unsigned>
3446 using number_unsigned_function_t =
3447  decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_unsigned(std::declval<Unsigned>()));
3448 
3449 template <typename T, typename Float, typename String>
3450 using number_float_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_float(
3451  std::declval<Float>(), std::declval<const String&>()));
3452 
3453 template <typename T, typename String>
3454 using string_function_t =
3455  decltype(std::declval<T&>().string(std::declval<String&>()));
3456 
3457 template <typename T>
3458 using start_object_function_t =
3459  decltype(std::declval<T&>().start_object(std::declval<std::size_t>()));
3460 
3461 template <typename T, typename String>
3462 using key_function_t =
3463  decltype(std::declval<T&>().key(std::declval<String&>()));
3464 
3465 template <typename T>
3466 using end_object_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().end_object());
3467 
3468 template <typename T>
3469 using start_array_function_t =
3470  decltype(std::declval<T&>().start_array(std::declval<std::size_t>()));
3471 
3472 template <typename T>
3473 using end_array_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().end_array());
3474 
3475 template <typename T, typename Exception>
3476 using parse_error_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().parse_error(
3477  std::declval<std::size_t>(), std::declval<const std::string&>(),
3478  std::declval<const Exception&>()));

3480 template <typename SAX, typename BasicJsonType>
3481 struct is_sax
3482 {
3483  private:
3484  static_assert(is_basic_json<BasicJsonType>::value,
3485  "BasicJsonType must be of type basic_json<...>");
3486 
3487  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3488  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3489  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3490  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3491  using exception_t = typename BasicJsonType::exception;
3492 
3493  public:
3494  static constexpr bool value =
3495  is_detected_exact<bool, null_function_t, SAX>::value &&
3496  is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value &&
3497  is_detected_exact<bool, number_integer_function_t, SAX,
3498  number_integer_t>::value &&
3499  is_detected_exact<bool, number_unsigned_function_t, SAX,
3500  number_unsigned_t>::value &&
3501  is_detected_exact<bool, number_float_function_t, SAX, number_float_t,
3502  string_t>::value &&
3503  is_detected_exact<bool, string_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value &&
3504  is_detected_exact<bool, start_object_function_t, SAX>::value &&
3505  is_detected_exact<bool, key_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value &&
3506  is_detected_exact<bool, end_object_function_t, SAX>::value &&
3507  is_detected_exact<bool, start_array_function_t, SAX>::value &&
3508  is_detected_exact<bool, end_array_function_t, SAX>::value &&
3509  is_detected_exact<bool, parse_error_function_t, SAX, exception_t>::value;
3510 };
3511 
3512 template <typename SAX, typename BasicJsonType>
3513 struct is_sax_static_asserts
3514 {
3515  private:
3516  static_assert(is_basic_json<BasicJsonType>::value,
3517  "BasicJsonType must be of type basic_json<...>");
3518 
3519  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3520  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3521  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3522  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3523  using exception_t = typename BasicJsonType::exception;
3524 
3525  public:
3526  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, null_function_t, SAX>::value,
3527  "Missing/invalid function: bool null()");
3528  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value,
3529  "Missing/invalid function: bool boolean(bool)");
3530  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value,
3531  "Missing/invalid function: bool boolean(bool)");
3532  static_assert(
3533  is_detected_exact<bool, number_integer_function_t, SAX,
3534  number_integer_t>::value,
3535  "Missing/invalid function: bool number_integer(number_integer_t)");
3536  static_assert(
3537  is_detected_exact<bool, number_unsigned_function_t, SAX,
3538  number_unsigned_t>::value,
3539  "Missing/invalid function: bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t)");
3540  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, number_float_function_t, SAX,
3541  number_float_t, string_t>::value,
3542  "Missing/invalid function: bool number_float(number_float_t, const string_t&)");
3543  static_assert(
3544  is_detected_exact<bool, string_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value,
3545  "Missing/invalid function: bool string(string_t&)");
3546  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, start_object_function_t, SAX>::value,
3547  "Missing/invalid function: bool start_object(std::size_t)");
3548  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, key_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value,
3549  "Missing/invalid function: bool key(string_t&)");
3550  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, end_object_function_t, SAX>::value,
3551  "Missing/invalid function: bool end_object()");
3552  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, start_array_function_t, SAX>::value,
3553  "Missing/invalid function: bool start_array(std::size_t)");
3554  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, end_array_function_t, SAX>::value,
3555  "Missing/invalid function: bool end_array()");
3556  static_assert(
3557  is_detected_exact<bool, parse_error_function_t, SAX, exception_t>::value,
3558  "Missing/invalid function: bool parse_error(std::size_t, const "
3559  "std::string&, const exception&)");
3560 };

3578 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename SAX = json_sax_dom_parser<BasicJsonType>>
3579 class binary_reader
3580 {
3581  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3582  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3583  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3584  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3585  using json_sax_t = SAX;
3586 
3587  public:
3593  explicit binary_reader(input_adapter_t adapter) : ia(std::move(adapter))
3594  {
3595  (void)detail::is_sax_static_asserts<SAX, BasicJsonType> {};
3596  assert(ia);
3597  }
3598 
3599  // make class move-only
3600  binary_reader(const binary_reader&) = delete;
3601  binary_reader(binary_reader&&) = default;
3602  binary_reader& operator=(const binary_reader&) = delete;
3603  binary_reader& operator=(binary_reader&&) = default;
3604  ~binary_reader() = default;
3605 
3613  bool sax_parse(const input_format_t format,
3614  json_sax_t* sax_,
3615  const bool strict = true)
3616  {
3617  sax = sax_;
3618  bool result = false;
3619 
3620  switch (format)
3621  {
3622  case input_format_t::bson:
3623  result = parse_bson_internal();
3624  break;
3625 
3626  case input_format_t::cbor:
3627  result = parse_cbor_internal();
3628  break;
3629 
3630  case input_format_t::msgpack:
3631  result = parse_msgpack_internal();
3632  break;
3633 
3634  case input_format_t::ubjson:
3635  result = parse_ubjson_internal();
3636  break;
3637 
3638  default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3639  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3640  }
3641 
3642  // strict mode: next byte must be EOF
3643  if (result and strict)
3644  {
3645  if (format == input_format_t::ubjson)
3646  {
3647  get_ignore_noop();
3648  }
3649  else
3650  {
3651  get();
3652  }
3653 
3654  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
3655  {
3656  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, get_token_string(),
3657  parse_error::create(110, chars_read, exception_message(format, "expected end of input; last byte: 0x" + get_token_string(), "value")));
3658  }
3659  }
3660 
3661  return result;
3662  }
3663 
3671  static constexpr bool little_endianess(int num = 1) noexcept
3672  {
3673  return *reinterpret_cast<char*>(&num) == 1;
3674  }
3675 
3676  private:
3678  // BSON //
3680 
3685  bool parse_bson_internal()
3686  {
3687  std::int32_t document_size;
3688  get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, document_size);
3689 
3690  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(std::size_t(-1))))
3691  {
3692  return false;
3693  }
3694 
3695  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_bson_element_list(/*is_array*/false)))
3696  {
3697  return false;
3698  }
3699 
3700  return sax->end_object();
3701  }
3702 
3710  bool get_bson_cstr(string_t& result)
3711  {
3712  auto out = std::back_inserter(result);
3713  while (true)
3714  {
3715  get();
3716  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::bson, "cstring")))
3717  {
3718  return false;
3719  }
3720  if (current == 0x00)
3721  {
3722  return true;
3723  }
3724  *out++ = static_cast<char>(current);
3725  }
3726 
3727  return true;
3728  }
3729 
3741  template<typename NumberType>
3742  bool get_bson_string(const NumberType len, string_t& result)
3743  {
3744  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(len < 1))
3745  {
3746  auto last_token = get_token_string();
3747  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::bson, "string length must be at least 1, is " + std::to_string(len), "string")));
3748  }
3749 
3750  return get_string(input_format_t::bson, len - static_cast<NumberType>(1), result) and get() != std::char_traits<char>::eof();
3751  }
3752 
3763  bool parse_bson_element_internal(const int element_type,
3764  const std::size_t element_type_parse_position)
3765  {
3766  switch (element_type)
3767  {
3768  case 0x01: // double
3769  {
3770  double number;
3771  return get_number<double, true>(input_format_t::bson, number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
3772  }
3773 
3774  case 0x02: // string
3775  {
3776  std::int32_t len;
3777  string_t value;
3778  return get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, len) and get_bson_string(len, value) and sax->string(value);
3779  }
3780 
3781  case 0x03: // object
3782  {
3783  return parse_bson_internal();
3784  }
3785 
3786  case 0x04: // array
3787  {
3788  return parse_bson_array();
3789  }
3790 
3791  case 0x08: // boolean
3792  {
3793  return sax->boolean(get() != 0);
3794  }
3795 
3796  case 0x0A: // null
3797  {
3798  return sax->null();
3799  }
3800 
3801  case 0x10: // int32
3802  {
3803  std::int32_t value;
3804  return get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, value) and sax->number_integer(value);
3805  }
3806 
3807  case 0x12: // int64
3808  {
3809  std::int64_t value;
3810  return get_number<std::int64_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, value) and sax->number_integer(value);
3811  }
3812 
3813  default: // anything else not supported (yet)
3814  {
3815  std::array<char, 3> cr{{}};
3816  (std::snprintf)(cr.data(), cr.size(), "%.2hhX", static_cast<unsigned char>(element_type));
3817  return sax->parse_error(element_type_parse_position, std::string(cr.data()), parse_error::create(114, element_type_parse_position, "Unsupported BSON record type 0x" + std::string(cr.data())));
3818  }
3819  }
3820  }
3821 
3834  bool parse_bson_element_list(const bool is_array)
3835  {
3836  string_t key;
3837  while (int element_type = get())
3838  {
3839  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::bson, "element list")))
3840  {
3841  return false;
3842  }
3843 
3844  const std::size_t element_type_parse_position = chars_read;
3845  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_bson_cstr(key)))
3846  {
3847  return false;
3848  }
3849 
3850  if (not is_array and not sax->key(key))
3851  {
3852  return false;
3853  }
3854 
3855  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_bson_element_internal(element_type, element_type_parse_position)))
3856  {
3857  return false;
3858  }
3859 
3860  // get_bson_cstr only appends
3861  key.clear();
3862  }
3863 
3864  return true;
3865  }
3866 
3871  bool parse_bson_array()
3872  {
3873  std::int32_t document_size;
3874  get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, document_size);
3875 
3876  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(std::size_t(-1))))
3877  {
3878  return false;
3879  }
3880 
3881  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_bson_element_list(/*is_array*/true)))
3882  {
3883  return false;
3884  }
3885 
3886  return sax->end_array();
3887  }

3892 
3900  bool parse_cbor_internal(const bool get_char = true)
3901  {
3902  switch (get_char ? get() : current)
3903  {
3904  // EOF
3905  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
3906  return unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "value");
3907 
3908  // Integer 0x00..0x17 (0..23)
3909  case 0x00:
3910  case 0x01:
3911  case 0x02:
3912  case 0x03:
3913  case 0x04:
3914  case 0x05:
3915  case 0x06:
3916  case 0x07:
3917  case 0x08:
3918  case 0x09:
3919  case 0x0A:
3920  case 0x0B:
3921  case 0x0C:
3922  case 0x0D:
3923  case 0x0E:
3924  case 0x0F:
3925  case 0x10:
3926  case 0x11:
3927  case 0x12:
3928  case 0x13:
3929  case 0x14:
3930  case 0x15:
3931  case 0x16:
3932  case 0x17:
3933  return sax->number_unsigned(static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(current));
3934 
3935  case 0x18: // Unsigned integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
3936  {
3937  std::uint8_t number;
3938  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
3939  }
3940 
3941  case 0x19: // Unsigned integer (two-byte uint16_t follows)
3942  {
3943  std::uint16_t number;
3944  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
3945  }
3946 
3947  case 0x1A: // Unsigned integer (four-byte uint32_t follows)
3948  {
3949  std::uint32_t number;
3950  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
3951  }
3952 
3953  case 0x1B: // Unsigned integer (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
3954  {
3955  std::uint64_t number;
3956  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
3957  }
3958 
3959  // Negative integer -1-0x00..-1-0x17 (-1..-24)
3960  case 0x20:
3961  case 0x21:
3962  case 0x22:
3963  case 0x23:
3964  case 0x24:
3965  case 0x25:
3966  case 0x26:
3967  case 0x27:
3968  case 0x28:
3969  case 0x29:
3970  case 0x2A:
3971  case 0x2B:
3972  case 0x2C:
3973  case 0x2D:
3974  case 0x2E:
3975  case 0x2F:
3976  case 0x30:
3977  case 0x31:
3978  case 0x32:
3979  case 0x33:
3980  case 0x34:
3981  case 0x35:
3982  case 0x36:
3983  case 0x37:
3984  return sax->number_integer(static_cast<std::int8_t>(0x20 - 1 - current));
3985 
3986  case 0x38: // Negative integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
3987  {
3988  std::uint8_t number;
3989  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
3990  }
3991 
3992  case 0x39: // Negative integer -1-n (two-byte uint16_t follows)
3993  {
3994  std::uint16_t number;
3995  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
3996  }
3997 
3998  case 0x3A: // Negative integer -1-n (four-byte uint32_t follows)
3999  {
4000  std::uint32_t number;
4001  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
4002  }
4003 
4004  case 0x3B: // Negative integer -1-n (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
4005  {
4006  std::uint64_t number;
4007  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1)
4008  - static_cast<number_integer_t>(number));
4009  }
4010 
4011  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
4012  case 0x60:
4013  case 0x61:
4014  case 0x62:
4015  case 0x63:
4016  case 0x64:
4017  case 0x65:
4018  case 0x66:
4019  case 0x67:
4020  case 0x68:
4021  case 0x69:
4022  case 0x6A:
4023  case 0x6B:
4024  case 0x6C:
4025  case 0x6D:
4026  case 0x6E:
4027  case 0x6F:
4028  case 0x70:
4029  case 0x71:
4030  case 0x72:
4031  case 0x73:
4032  case 0x74:
4033  case 0x75:
4034  case 0x76:
4035  case 0x77:
4036  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4037  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4038  case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4039  case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4040  case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
4041  {
4042  string_t s;
4043  return get_cbor_string(s) and sax->string(s);
4044  }
4045 
4046  // array (0x00..0x17 data items follow)
4047  case 0x80:
4048  case 0x81:
4049  case 0x82:
4050  case 0x83:
4051  case 0x84:
4052  case 0x85:
4053  case 0x86:
4054  case 0x87:
4055  case 0x88:
4056  case 0x89:
4057  case 0x8A:
4058  case 0x8B:
4059  case 0x8C:
4060  case 0x8D:
4061  case 0x8E:
4062  case 0x8F:
4063  case 0x90:
4064  case 0x91:
4065  case 0x92:
4066  case 0x93:
4067  case 0x94:
4068  case 0x95:
4069  case 0x96:
4070  case 0x97:
4071  return get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu));
4072 
4073  case 0x98: // array (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4074  {

4076  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4077  }
4078 
4079  case 0x99: // array (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4080  {
4081  std::uint16_t len;
4082  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4083  }
4084 
4085  case 0x9A: // array (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4086  {
4087  std::uint32_t len;
4088  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4089  }
4090 
4091  case 0x9B: // array (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4092  {
