4094  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4095  }
4096 
4097  case 0x9F: // array (indefinite length)
4098  return get_cbor_array(std::size_t(-1));
4099 
4100  // map (0x00..0x17 pairs of data items follow)
4101  case 0xA0:
4102  case 0xA1:
4103  case 0xA2:
4104  case 0xA3:
4105  case 0xA4:
4106  case 0xA5:
4107  case 0xA6:
4108  case 0xA7:
4109  case 0xA8:
4110  case 0xA9:
4111  case 0xAA:
4112  case 0xAB:
4113  case 0xAC:
4114  case 0xAD:
4115  case 0xAE:
4116  case 0xAF:
4117  case 0xB0:
4118  case 0xB1:
4119  case 0xB2:
4120  case 0xB3:
4121  case 0xB4:
4122  case 0xB5:
4123  case 0xB6:
4124  case 0xB7:
4125  return get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu));
4126 
4127  case 0xB8: // map (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4128  {
4129  std::uint8_t len;
4130  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4131  }
4132 
4133  case 0xB9: // map (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4134  {
4135  std::uint16_t len;
4136  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4137  }
4138 
4139  case 0xBA: // map (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4140  {
4141  std::uint32_t len;
4142  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4143  }
4144 
4145  case 0xBB: // map (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4146  {
4147  std::uint64_t len;
4148  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4149  }
4150 
4151  case 0xBF: // map (indefinite length)
4152  return get_cbor_object(std::size_t(-1));
4153 
4154  case 0xF4: // false
4155  return sax->boolean(false);
4156 
4157  case 0xF5: // true
4158  return sax->boolean(true);
4159 
4160  case 0xF6: // null
4161  return sax->null();
4162 
4163  case 0xF9: // Half-Precision Float (two-byte IEEE 754)
4164  {
4165  const int byte1_raw = get();
4166  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "number")))
4167  {
4168  return false;
4169  }
4170  const int byte2_raw = get();
4171  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "number")))
4172  {
4173  return false;
4174  }
4175 
4176  const auto byte1 = static_cast<unsigned char>(byte1_raw);
4177  const auto byte2 = static_cast<unsigned char>(byte2_raw);
4178 
4179  // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
4180  // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added
4181  // to IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often
4182  // still only have limited support for them. It is very
4183  // easy to include at least decoding support for them even
4184  // without such support. An example of a small decoder for
4185  // half-precision floating-point numbers in the C language
4186  // is shown in Fig. 3.
4187  const auto half = static_cast<unsigned int>((byte1 << 8u) + byte2);
4188  const double val = [&half]
4189  {
4190  const int exp = (half >> 10u) & 0x1Fu;
4191  const unsigned int mant = half & 0x3FFu;
4192  assert(0 <= exp and exp <= 32);
4193  assert(0 <= mant and mant <= 1024);
4194  switch (exp)
4195  {
4196  case 0:
4197  return std::ldexp(mant, -24);
4198  case 31:
4199  return (mant == 0)
4200  ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()
4201  : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
4202  default:
4203  return std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
4204  }
4205  }();
4206  return sax->number_float((half & 0x8000u) != 0
4207  ? static_cast<number_float_t>(-val)
4208  : static_cast<number_float_t>(val), "");
4209  }
4210 
4211  case 0xFA: // Single-Precision Float (four-byte IEEE 754)
4212  {
4213  float number;
4214  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
4215  }
4216 
4217  case 0xFB: // Double-Precision Float (eight-byte IEEE 754)
4218  {
4219  double number;
4220  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
4221  }
4222 
4223  default: // anything else (0xFF is handled inside the other types)
4224  {
4225  auto last_token = get_token_string();
4226  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value")));
4227  }
4228  }
4229  }
4230 
4242  bool get_cbor_string(string_t& result)
4243  {
4244  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "string")))
4245  {
4246  return false;
4247  }
4248 
4249  switch (current)
4250  {
4251  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
4252  case 0x60:
4253  case 0x61:
4254  case 0x62:
4255  case 0x63:
4256  case 0x64:
4257  case 0x65:
4258  case 0x66:
4259  case 0x67:
4260  case 0x68:
4261  case 0x69:
4262  case 0x6A:
4263  case 0x6B:
4264  case 0x6C:
4265  case 0x6D:
4266  case 0x6E:
4267  case 0x6F:
4268  case 0x70:
4269  case 0x71:
4270  case 0x72:
4271  case 0x73:
4272  case 0x74:
4273  case 0x75:
4274  case 0x76:
4275  case 0x77:
4276  {
4277  return get_string(input_format_t::cbor, static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu, result);
4278  }
4279 
4280  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4281  {
4282  std::uint8_t len;
4283  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
4284  }
4285 
4286  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4287  {
4288  std::uint16_t len;
4289  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
4290  }
4291 
4292  case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4293  {
4294  std::uint32_t len;
4295  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
4296  }
4297 
4298  case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4299  {
4300  std::uint64_t len;
4301  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
4302  }
4303 
4304  case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
4305  {
4306  while (get() != 0xFF)
4307  {
4308  string_t chunk;
4309  if (not get_cbor_string(chunk))
4310  {
4311  return false;
4312  }
4313  result.append(chunk);
4314  }
4315  return true;
4316  }
4317 
4318  default:
4319  {
4320  auto last_token = get_token_string();
4321  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, "expected length specification (0x60-0x7B) or indefinite string type (0x7F); last byte: 0x" + last_token, "string")));
4322  }
4323  }
4324  }
4325 
4331  bool get_cbor_array(const std::size_t len)
4332  {
4333  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(len)))
4334  {
4335  return false;
4336  }
4337 
4338  if (len != std::size_t(-1))
4339  {
4340  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4341  {
4342  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal()))
4343  {
4344  return false;
4345  }
4346  }
4347  }
4348  else
4349  {
4350  while (get() != 0xFF)
4351  {
4352  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal(false)))
4353  {
4354  return false;
4355  }
4356  }
4357  }
4358 
4359  return sax->end_array();
4360  }
4361 
4367  bool get_cbor_object(const std::size_t len)
4368  {
4369  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(len)))
4370  {
4371  return false;
4372  }
4373 
4374  string_t key;
4375  if (len != std::size_t(-1))
4376  {
4377  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4378  {
4379  get();
4380  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_cbor_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
4381  {
4382  return false;
4383  }
4384 
4385  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal()))
4386  {
4387  return false;
4388  }
4389  key.clear();
4390  }
4391  }
4392  else
4393  {
4394  while (get() != 0xFF)
4395  {
4396  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_cbor_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
4397  {
4398  return false;
4399  }
4400 
4401  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal()))
4402  {
4403  return false;
4404  }
4405  key.clear();
4406  }
4407  }
4408 
4409  return sax->end_object();
4410  }

4788  bool get_msgpack_string(string_t& result)
4789  {
4790  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::msgpack, "string")))
4791  {
4792  return false;
4793  }
4794 
4795  switch (current)
4796  {
4797  // fixstr
4798  case 0xA0:
4799  case 0xA1:
4800  case 0xA2:
4801  case 0xA3:
4802  case 0xA4:
4803  case 0xA5:
4804  case 0xA6:
4805  case 0xA7:
4806  case 0xA8:
4807  case 0xA9:
4808  case 0xAA:
4809  case 0xAB:
4810  case 0xAC:
4811  case 0xAD:
4812  case 0xAE:
4813  case 0xAF:
4814  case 0xB0:
4815  case 0xB1:
4816  case 0xB2:
4817  case 0xB3:
4818  case 0xB4:
4819  case 0xB5:
4820  case 0xB6:
4821  case 0xB7:
4822  case 0xB8:
4823  case 0xB9:
4824  case 0xBA:
4825  case 0xBB:
4826  case 0xBC:
4827  case 0xBD:
4828  case 0xBE:
4829  case 0xBF:
4830  {
4831  return get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu, result);
4832  }
4833 
4834  case 0xD9: // str 8
4835  {
4836  std::uint8_t len;
4837  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
4838  }
4839 
4840  case 0xDA: // str 16
4841  {
4842  std::uint16_t len;

4844  }
4845 
4846  case 0xDB: // str 32
4847  {
4848  std::uint32_t len;
4849  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
4850  }
4851 
4852  default:
4853  {
4854  auto last_token = get_token_string();
4855  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::msgpack, "expected length specification (0xA0-0xBF, 0xD9-0xDB); last byte: 0x" + last_token, "string")));
4856  }
4857  }
4858  }
4859 
4864  bool get_msgpack_array(const std::size_t len)
4865  {
4866  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(len)))
4867  {
4868  return false;
4869  }
4870 
4871  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4872  {
4873  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_msgpack_internal()))
4874  {
4875  return false;
4876  }
4877  }
4878 
4879  return sax->end_array();
4880  }
4881 
4886  bool get_msgpack_object(const std::size_t len)
4887  {
4888  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(len)))
4889  {
4890  return false;
4891  }
4892 
4893  string_t key;
4894  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4895  {
4896  get();
4897  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_msgpack_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
4898  {
4899  return false;
4900  }
4901 
4902  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_msgpack_internal()))
4903  {
4904  return false;
4905  }
4906  key.clear();
4907  }
4908 
4909  return sax->end_object();
4910  }

4913  // UBJSON //
4915 
4923  bool parse_ubjson_internal(const bool get_char = true)
4924  {
4925  return get_ubjson_value(get_char ? get_ignore_noop() : current);
4926  }
4927 
4942  bool get_ubjson_string(string_t& result, const bool get_char = true)
4943  {
4944  if (get_char)
4945  {
4946  get(); // TODO(niels): may we ignore N here?
4947  }
4948 
4949  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "value")))
4950  {
4951  return false;
4952  }
4953 
4954  switch (current)
4955  {
4956  case 'U':
4957  {
4958  std::uint8_t len;
4959  return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
4960  }
4961 
4962  case 'i':
4963  {
4964  std::int8_t len;
4965  return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
4966  }
4967 
4968  case 'I':
4969  {
4970  std::int16_t len;
4971  return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
4972  }
4973 
4974  case 'l':
4975  {
4976  std::int32_t len;
4977  return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
4978  }
4979 
4980  case 'L':
4981  {
4982  std::int64_t len;
4983  return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
4984  }
4985 
4986  default:
4987  auto last_token = get_token_string();
4988  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "expected length type specification (U, i, I, l, L); last byte: 0x" + last_token, "string")));
4989  }
4990  }
4991 
4996  bool get_ubjson_size_value(std::size_t& result)
4997  {
4998  switch (get_ignore_noop())
4999  {
5000  case 'U':
5001  {
5002  std::uint8_t number;
5003  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
5004  {
5005  return false;
5006  }
5007  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5008  return true;
5009  }
5010 
5011  case 'i':
5012  {
5013  std::int8_t number;
5014  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
5015  {
5016  return false;
5017  }
5018  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5019  return true;
5020  }
5021 
5022  case 'I':
5023  {
5024  std::int16_t number;
5025  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
5026  {
5027  return false;
5028  }
5029  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5030  return true;
5031  }
5032 
5033  case 'l':
5034  {
5035  std::int32_t number;
5036  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
5037  {
5038  return false;
5039  }
5040  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5041  return true;
5042  }
5043 
5044  case 'L':
5045  {
5046  std::int64_t number;
5047  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
5048  {
5049  return false;
5050  }
5051  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5052  return true;
5053  }
5054 
5055  default:
5056  {
5057  auto last_token = get_token_string();
5058  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "expected length type specification (U, i, I, l, L) after '#'; last byte: 0x" + last_token, "size")));
5059  }
5060  }
5061  }
5062 
5073  bool get_ubjson_size_type(std::pair<std::size_t, int>& result)
5074  {
5075  result.first = string_t::npos; // size
5076  result.second = 0; // type
5077 
5078  get_ignore_noop();
5079 
5080  if (current == '$')
5081  {
5082  result.second = get(); // must not ignore 'N', because 'N' maybe the type
5083  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "type")))
5084  {
5085  return false;
5086  }
5087 
5088  get_ignore_noop();
5089  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current != '#'))
5090  {
5091  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "value")))
5092  {
5093  return false;
5094  }
5095  auto last_token = get_token_string();
5096  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "expected '#' after type information; last byte: 0x" + last_token, "size")));
5097  }
5098 
5099  return get_ubjson_size_value(result.first);
5100  }
5101 
5102  if (current == '#')
5103  {
5104  return get_ubjson_size_value(result.first);
5105  }
5106 
5107  return true;
5108  }
5109 
5114  bool get_ubjson_value(const int prefix)
5115  {
5116  switch (prefix)
5117  {
5118  case std::char_traits<char>::eof(): // EOF
5119  return unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "value");
5120 
5121  case 'T': // true
5122  return sax->boolean(true);
5123  case 'F': // false
5124  return sax->boolean(false);
5125 
5126  case 'Z': // null
5127  return sax->null();
5128 
5129  case 'U':
5130  {
5131  std::uint8_t number;
5132  return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
5133  }
5134 
5135  case 'i':
5136  {
5137  std::int8_t number;
5138  return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
5139  }
5140 
5141  case 'I':
5142  {
5143  std::int16_t number;
5144  return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
5145  }
5146 
5147  case 'l':
5148  {
5149  std::int32_t number;
5150  return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
5151  }
5152 
5153  case 'L':
5154  {
5155  std::int64_t number;
5156  return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
5157  }
5158 
5159  case 'd':
5160  {
5161  float number;
5162  return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
5163  }
5164 
5165  case 'D':
5166  {
5167  double number;
5168  return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
5169  }
5170 
5171  case 'C': // char
5172  {
5173  get();
5174  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "char")))
5175  {
5176  return false;
5177  }
5178  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current > 127))
5179  {
5180  auto last_token = get_token_string();
5181  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "byte after 'C' must be in range 0x00..0x7F; last byte: 0x" + last_token, "char")));
5182  }
5183  string_t s(1, static_cast<char>(current));
5184  return sax->string(s);
5185  }
5186 
5187  case 'S': // string
5188  {
5189  string_t s;
5190  return get_ubjson_string(s) and sax->string(s);
5191  }
5192 
5193  case '[': // array
5194  return get_ubjson_array();
5195 
5196  case '{': // object
5197  return get_ubjson_object();
5198 
5199  default: // anything else
5200  {
5201  auto last_token = get_token_string();
5202  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value")));
5203  }
5204  }
5205  }
5206 
5210  bool get_ubjson_array()
5211  {
5212  std::pair<std::size_t, int> size_and_type;
5213  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type)))
5214  {
5215  return false;
5216  }
5217 
5218  if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
5219  {
5220  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(size_and_type.first)))
5221  {
5222  return false;
5223  }
5224 
5225  if (size_and_type.second != 0)
5226  {
5227  if (size_and_type.second != 'N')
5228  {
5229  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
5230  {
5231  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second)))
5232  {
5233  return false;
5234  }
5235  }
5236  }
5237  }
5238  else
5239  {
5240  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
5241  {
5242  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal()))
5243  {
5244  return false;
5245  }
5246  }
5247  }
5248  }
5249  else
5250  {
5251  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(std::size_t(-1))))
5252  {
5253  return false;
5254  }
5255 
5256  while (current != ']')
5257  {
5258  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal(false)))
5259  {
5260  return false;
5261  }
5262  get_ignore_noop();
5263  }
5264  }
5265 
5266  return sax->end_array();
5267  }
5268 
5272  bool get_ubjson_object()
5273  {
5274  std::pair<std::size_t, int> size_and_type;
5275  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type)))
5276  {
5277  return false;
5278  }
5279 
5280  string_t key;
5281  if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
5282  {
5283  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(size_and_type.first)))
5284  {
5285  return false;
5286  }
5287 
5288  if (size_and_type.second != 0)
5289  {
5290  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
5291  {
5292  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
5293  {
5294  return false;
5295  }
5296  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second)))
5297  {
5298  return false;
5299  }
5300  key.clear();
5301  }
5302  }
5303  else
5304  {
5305  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
5306  {
5307  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
5308  {
5309  return false;
5310  }
5311  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal()))
5312  {
5313  return false;
5314  }
5315  key.clear();
5316  }
5317  }
5318  }
5319  else
5320  {
5321  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(std::size_t(-1))))
5322  {
5323  return false;
5324  }
5325 
5326  while (current != '}')
5327  {
5328  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_string(key, false) or not sax->key(key)))
5329  {
5330  return false;
5331  }
5332  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal()))
5333  {
5334  return false;
5335  }
5336  get_ignore_noop();
5337  key.clear();
5338  }
5339  }
5340 
5341  return sax->end_object();
5342  }
5343 
5345  // Utility functions //
5347 
5357  int get()
5358  {
5359  ++chars_read;
5360  return current = ia->get_character();
5361  }
5362 
5366  int get_ignore_noop()
5367  {
5368  do
5369  {
5370  get();
5371  }
5372  while (current == 'N');
5373 
5374  return current;
5375  }
5376 
5377  /*
5378  @brief read a number from the input
5379 
5380  @tparam NumberType the type of the number
5381  @param[in] format the current format (for diagnostics)
5382  @param[out] result number of type @a NumberType
5383 
5384  @return whether conversion completed
5385 
5386  @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because
5387  bytes in CBOR, MessagePack, and UBJSON are stored in network order
5388  (big endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
5389  */
5390  template<typename NumberType, bool InputIsLittleEndian = false>
5391  bool get_number(const input_format_t format, NumberType& result)
5392  {
5393  // step 1: read input into array with system's byte order
5394  std::array<std::uint8_t, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
5395  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(NumberType); ++i)
5396  {
5397  get();
5398  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(format, "number")))
5399  {
5400  return false;
5401  }
5402 
5403  // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
5404  if (is_little_endian != InputIsLittleEndian)
5405  {
5406  vec[sizeof(NumberType) - i - 1] = static_cast<std::uint8_t>(current);
5407  }
5408  else
5409  {
5410  vec[i] = static_cast<std::uint8_t>(current); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
5411  }
5412  }
5413 
5414  // step 2: convert array into number of type T and return
5415  std::memcpy(&result, vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
5416  return true;
5417  }
5418 
5433  template<typename NumberType>
5434  bool get_string(const input_format_t format,
5435  const NumberType len,
5436  string_t& result)
5437  {
5438  bool success = true;
5439  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(result), len, [this, &success, &format]()
5440  {
5441  get();
5442  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(format, "string")))
5443  {
5444  success = false;
5445  }
5446  return static_cast<char>(current);
5447  });
5448  return success;
5449  }
5450 
5456  bool unexpect_eof(const input_format_t format, const char* context) const
5457  {
5458  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current == std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
5459  {
5460  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, "<end of file>",
5461  parse_error::create(110, chars_read, exception_message(format, "unexpected end of input", context)));
5462  }
5463  return true;
5464  }
5465 
5469  std::string get_token_string() const
5470  {
5471  std::array<char, 3> cr{{}};
5472  (std::snprintf)(cr.data(), cr.size(), "%.2hhX", static_cast<unsigned char>(current));
5473  return std::string{cr.data()};
5474  }
5475 
5482  std::string exception_message(const input_format_t format,
5483  const std::string& detail,
5484  const std::string& context) const
5485  {
5486  std::string error_msg = "syntax error while parsing ";
5487 
5488  switch (format)
5489  {
5490  case input_format_t::cbor:
5491  error_msg += "CBOR";
5492  break;
5493 
5494  case input_format_t::msgpack:
5495  error_msg += "MessagePack";
5496  break;
5497 
5498  case input_format_t::ubjson:
5499  error_msg += "UBJSON";
5500  break;
5501 
5502  case input_format_t::bson:
5503  error_msg += "BSON";
5504  break;
5505 
5506  default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
5507  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
5508  }
5509 
5510  return error_msg + " " + context + ": " + detail;
5511  }
5512 
5513  private:
5515  input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
5516 
5518  int current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
5519 
5521  std::size_t chars_read = 0;
5522 
5524  const bool is_little_endian = little_endianess();
5525 
5527  json_sax_t* sax = nullptr;
5528 };
5529 } // namespace detail
5530 } // namespace nlohmann

5559 // lexer //
5561 
5567 template<typename BasicJsonType>
5568 class lexer
5569 {
5570  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
5571  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
5572  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
5573  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
5574 
5575  public:
5577  enum class token_type
5578  {
5579  uninitialized,
5580  literal_true,
5581  literal_false,
5582  literal_null,
5583  value_string,
5584  value_unsigned,
5585  value_integer,
5586  value_float,
5587  begin_array,
5588  begin_object,
5589  end_array,
5590  end_object,
5591  name_separator,
5592  value_separator,
5593  parse_error,
5594  end_of_input,
5595  literal_or_value
5596  };
5597 
5599  static const char* token_type_name(const token_type t) noexcept
5600  {
5601  switch (t)
5602  {
5603  case token_type::uninitialized:
5604  return "<uninitialized>";
5605  case token_type::literal_true:
5606  return "true literal";
5607  case token_type::literal_false:
5608  return "false literal";
5609  case token_type::literal_null:
5610  return "null literal";
5611  case token_type::value_string:
5612  return "string literal";
5613  case lexer::token_type::value_unsigned:
5614  case lexer::token_type::value_integer:
5615  case lexer::token_type::value_float:
5616  return "number literal";
5617  case token_type::begin_array:
5618  return "'['";
5619  case token_type::begin_object:
5620  return "'{'";
5621  case token_type::end_array:
5622  return "']'";
5623  case token_type::end_object:
5624  return "'}'";
5625  case token_type::name_separator:
5626  return "':'";
5627  case token_type::value_separator:
5628  return "','";
5629  case token_type::parse_error:
5630  return "<parse error>";
5631  case token_type::end_of_input:
5632  return "end of input";
5633  case token_type::literal_or_value:
5634  return "'[', '{', or a literal";
5635  // LCOV_EXCL_START
5636  default: // catch non-enum values
5637  return "unknown token";
5638  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
5639  }
5640  }
5641 
5642  explicit lexer(detail::input_adapter_t&& adapter)
5643  : ia(std::move(adapter)), decimal_point_char(get_decimal_point()) {}
5644 
5645  // delete because of pointer members
5646  lexer(const lexer&) = delete;
5647  lexer(lexer&&) = delete;
5648  lexer& operator=(lexer&) = delete;
5649  lexer& operator=(lexer&&) = delete;
5650  ~lexer() = default;
5651 
5652  private:
5654  // locales
5656 
5658  static char get_decimal_point() noexcept
5659  {
5660  const auto loc = localeconv();
5661  assert(loc != nullptr);
5662  return (loc->decimal_point == nullptr) ? '.' : *(loc->decimal_point);
5663  }
5664 
5666  // scan functions
5668 
5684  int get_codepoint()
5685  {
5686  // this function only makes sense after reading `\u`
5687  assert(current == 'u');
5688  int codepoint = 0;
5689 
5690  const auto factors = { 12u, 8u, 4u, 0u };
5691  for (const auto factor : factors)
5692  {
5693  get();
5694 
5695  if (current >= '0' and current <= '9')
5696  {
5697  codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x30u) << factor);
5698  }
5699  else if (current >= 'A' and current <= 'F')
5700  {
5701  codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x37u) << factor);
5702  }
5703  else if (current >= 'a' and current <= 'f')
5704  {
5705  codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x57u) << factor);
5706  }
5707  else
5708  {
5709  return -1;
5710  }
5711  }
5712 
5713  assert(0x0000 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0xFFFF);
5714  return codepoint;
5715  }
5716 
5732  bool next_byte_in_range(std::initializer_list<int> ranges)
5733  {
5734  assert(ranges.size() == 2 or ranges.size() == 4 or ranges.size() == 6);
5735  add(current);
5736 
5737  for (auto range = ranges.begin(); range != ranges.end(); ++range)
5738  {
5739  get();
5740  if (JSON_LIKELY(*range <= current and current <= *(++range)))
5741  {
5742  add(current);
5743  }
5744  else
5745  {
5746  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
5747  return false;
5748  }
5749  }
5750 
5751  return true;
5752  }
5753 
5769  token_type scan_string()
5770  {
5771  // reset token_buffer (ignore opening quote)
5772  reset();
5773 
5774  // we entered the function by reading an open quote
5775  assert(current == '\"');
5776 
5777  while (true)
5778  {
5779  // get next character
5780  switch (get())
5781  {
5782  // end of file while parsing string
5783  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
5784  {
5785  error_message = "invalid string: missing closing quote";
5786  return token_type::parse_error;
5787  }
5788 
5789  // closing quote
5790  case '\"':
5791  {
5792  return token_type::value_string;
5793  }
5794 
5795  // escapes
5796  case '\\':
5797  {
5798  switch (get())
5799  {
5800  // quotation mark
5801  case '\"':
5802  add('\"');
5803  break;
5804  // reverse solidus
5805  case '\\':
5806  add('\\');
5807  break;
5808  // solidus
5809  case '/':
5810  add('/');
5811  break;
5812  // backspace
5813  case 'b':
5814  add('\b');
5815  break;
5816  // form feed
5817  case 'f':
5818  add('\f');
5819  break;
5820  // line feed
5821  case 'n':
5822  add('\n');
5823  break;
5824  // carriage return
5825  case 'r':
5826  add('\r');
5827  break;
5828  // tab
5829  case 't':
5830  add('\t');
5831  break;
5832 
5833  // unicode escapes
5834  case 'u':
5835  {
5836  const int codepoint1 = get_codepoint();
5837  int codepoint = codepoint1; // start with codepoint1
5838 
5839  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint1 == -1))
5840  {
5841  error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
5842  return token_type::parse_error;
5843  }
5844 
5845  // check if code point is a high surrogate
5846  if (0xD800 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF)
5847  {
5848  // expect next \uxxxx entry
5849  if (JSON_LIKELY(get() == '\\' and get() == 'u'))
5850  {
5851  const int codepoint2 = get_codepoint();
5852 
5853  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint2 == -1))
5854  {
5855  error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
5856  return token_type::parse_error;
5857  }
5858 
5859  // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
5860  if (JSON_LIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint2 and codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF))
5861  {
5862  // overwrite codepoint
5863  codepoint = static_cast<int>(
5864  // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
5865  (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint1) << 10u)
5866  // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
5867  + static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint2)
5868  // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
5869  // in the result so we have to subtract with:
5870  // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
5871  - 0x35FDC00u);
5872  }
5873  else
5874  {
5875  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
5876  return token_type::parse_error;
5877  }
5878  }
5879  else
5880  {
5881  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
5882  return token_type::parse_error;
5883  }
5884  }
5885  else
5886  {
5887  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDFFF))
5888  {
5889  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must follow U+D800..U+DBFF";
5890  return token_type::parse_error;
5891  }
5892  }
5893 
5894  // result of the above calculation yields a proper codepoint
5895  assert(0x00 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0x10FFFF);
5896 
5897  // translate codepoint into bytes
5898  if (codepoint < 0x80)
5899  {
5900  // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
5901  add(codepoint);
5902  }
5903  else if (codepoint <= 0x7FF)
5904  {
5905  // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
5906  add(static_cast<int>(0xC0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u)));
5907  add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
5908  }
5909  else if (codepoint <= 0xFFFF)
5910  {
5911  // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
5912  add(static_cast<int>(0xE0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 12u)));
5913  add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu)));
5914  add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
5915  }
5916  else
5917  {
5918  // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
5919  add(static_cast<int>(0xF0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 18u)));
5920  add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 12u) & 0x3Fu)));
5921  add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu)));
5922  add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
5923  }
5924 
5925  break;
5926  }
5927 
5928  // other characters after escape
5929  default:
5930  error_message = "invalid string: forbidden character after backslash";
5931  return token_type::parse_error;
5932  }
5933 
5934  break;
5935  }
5936 
5937  // invalid control characters
5938  case 0x00:
5939  {
5940  error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0000 (NUL) must be escaped to \\u0000";
5941  return token_type::parse_error;
5942  }
5943 
5944  case 0x01:
5945  {
5946  error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0001 (SOH) must be escaped to \\u0001";
5947  return token_type::parse_error;
5948  }
5949 
5950  case 0x02:
5951  {
5952  error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0002 (STX) must be escaped to \\u0002";
5953  return token_type::parse_error;
5954  }
5955 
5956  case 0x03:
5957  {
5958  error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0003 (ETX) must be escaped to \\u0003";
5959  return token_type::parse_error;
5960  }
5961 
5962  case 0x04:
5963  {
5964  error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0004 (EOT) must be escaped to \\u0004";
5965  return token_type::parse_error;
5966  }
5967 
5968  case 0x05:
5969  {
5970  error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0005 (ENQ) must be escaped to \\u0005";
5971  return token_type::parse_error;
5972  }
5973 
5974  case 0x06:
5975  {
5976  error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0006 (ACK) must be escaped to \\u0006";
5977  return token_type::parse_error;
5978  }
5979 
5980  case 0x07:
5981  {
5982  error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0007 (BEL) must be escaped to \\u0007";
5983  return token_type::parse_error;
5984  }
5985 
5986  case 0x08:
5987  {
5988  error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0008 (BS) must be escaped to \\u0008 or \\b";
5989  return token_type::parse_error;
5990  }
5991 
5992  case 0x09:
5993  {
5994  error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0009 (HT) must be escaped to \\u0009 or \\t";
5995  return token_type::parse_error;
5996  }
5997 
5998  case 0x0A:
5999  {
6000  error_message = "invalid string: control character U+000A (LF) must be escaped to \\u000A or \\n";
6001  return token_type::parse_error;
6002  }

6276  break;

6280  // U+E000..U+FFFF: bytes EE..EF 80..BF 80..BF
6281  case 0xE1:
6282  case 0xE2:
6283  case 0xE3:
6284  case 0xE4:
6285  case 0xE5:
6286  case 0xE6:

6291  case 0xEB:
6292  case 0xEC:

6294  case 0xEF:

6297  {
6298  return token_type::parse_error;
6299  }
6300  break;
6301  }

6303  // U+D000..U+D7FF: bytes ED 80..9F 80..BF
6304  case 0xED:
6305  {

6307  {
6308  return token_type::parse_error;
6309  }
6310  break;
6311  }
6312

6314  case 0xF0:

6317  {
6318  return token_type::parse_error;
6319  }
6320  break;
6321  }
6322 
6323  // U+40000..U+FFFFF F1..F3 80..BF 80..BF 80..BF
6324  case 0xF1:
6325  case 0xF2:
6326  case 0xF3:
6327  {
6328  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not (next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
6329  {
6330  return token_type::parse_error;
6331  }
6332  break;
6333  }
6334 
6335  // U+100000..U+10FFFF F4 80..8F 80..BF 80..BF
6336  case 0xF4:
6337  {
6338  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not (next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x8F, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
6339  {
6340  return token_type::parse_error;
6341  }
6342  break;
6343  }
6344 
6345  // remaining bytes (80..C1 and F5..FF) are ill-formed
6346  default:
6347  {
6348  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
6349  return token_type::parse_error;
6350  }
6351  }
6352  }
6353  }

6410  token_type scan_number() // lgtm [cpp/use-of-goto]
6411  {
6412  // reset token_buffer to store the number's bytes
6413  reset();
6414 
6415  // the type of the parsed number; initially set to unsigned; will be
6416  // changed if minus sign, decimal point or exponent is read
6417  token_type number_type = token_type::value_unsigned;
6418 
6419  // state (init): we just found out we need to scan a number
6420  switch (current)
6421  {
6422  case '-':
6423  {
6424  add(current);
6425  goto scan_number_minus;
6426  }
6427 
6428  case '0':
6429  {
6430  add(current);
6431  goto scan_number_zero;
6432  }
6433 
6434  case '1':
6435  case '2':
6436  case '3':
6437  case '4':
6438  case '5':
6439  case '6':
6440  case '7':
6441  case '8':
6442  case '9':
6443  {
6444  add(current);
6445  goto scan_number_any1;
6446  }
6447 
6448  // all other characters are rejected outside scan_number()
6449  default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
6450  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
6451  }
6452 
6453 scan_number_minus:
6454  // state: we just parsed a leading minus sign
6455  number_type = token_type::value_integer;
6456  switch (get())
6457  {
6458  case '0':
6459  {
6460  add(current);
6461  goto scan_number_zero;
6462  }
6463 
6464  case '1':
6465  case '2':
6466  case '3':
6467  case '4':
6468  case '5':
6469  case '6':
6470  case '7':
6471  case '8':
6472  case '9':
6473  {
6474  add(current);
6475  goto scan_number_any1;
6476  }
6477 
6478  default:
6479  {
6480  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '-'";
6481  return token_type::parse_error;
6482  }
6483  }
6484 
6485 scan_number_zero:
6486  // state: we just parse a zero (maybe with a leading minus sign)
6487  switch (get())
6488  {
6489  case '.':
6490  {
6491  add(decimal_point_char);
6492  goto scan_number_decimal1;
6493  }
6494 
6495  case 'e':
6496  case 'E':
6497  {
6498  add(current);
6499  goto scan_number_exponent;
6500  }
6501 
6502  default:
6503  goto scan_number_done;
6504  }
6505 
6506 scan_number_any1:
6507  // state: we just parsed a number 0-9 (maybe with a leading minus sign)
6508  switch (get())
6509  {
6510  case '0':
6511  case '1':
6512  case '2':
6513  case '3':
6514  case '4':
6515  case '5':
6516  case '6':
6517  case '7':
6518  case '8':
6519  case '9':
6520  {
6521  add(current);
6522  goto scan_number_any1;
6523  }
6524 
6525  case '.':
6526  {
6527  add(decimal_point_char);
6528  goto scan_number_decimal1;
6529  }
6530 
6531  case 'e':
6532  case 'E':
6533  {
6534  add(current);
6535  goto scan_number_exponent;
6536  }
6537 
6538  default:
6539  goto scan_number_done;
6540  }
6541 
6542 scan_number_decimal1:
6543  // state: we just parsed a decimal point
6544  number_type = token_type::value_float;
6545  switch (get())
6546  {
6547  case '0':
6548  case '1':
6549  case '2':
6550  case '3':
6551  case '4':
6552  case '5':
6553  case '6':
6554  case '7':
6555  case '8':
6556  case '9':
6557  {
6558  add(current);
6559  goto scan_number_decimal2;
6560  }
6561 
6562  default:
6563  {
6564  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '.'";
6565  return token_type::parse_error;
6566  }
6567  }
6568 
6569 scan_number_decimal2:
6570  // we just parsed at least one number after a decimal point
6571  switch (get())
6572  {
6573  case '0':
6574  case '1':
6575  case '2':
6576  case '3':
6577  case '4':
6578  case '5':
6579  case '6':
6580  case '7':
6581  case '8':
6582  case '9':
6583  {
6584  add(current);
6585  goto scan_number_decimal2;
6586  }
6587 
6588  case 'e':
6589  case 'E':
6590  {
6591  add(current);
6592  goto scan_number_exponent;
6593  }
6594 
6595  default:
6596  goto scan_number_done;
6597  }
6598 
6599 scan_number_exponent:
6600  // we just parsed an exponent
6601  number_type = token_type::value_float;
6602  switch (get())
6603  {
6604  case '+':
6605  case '-':
6606  {
6607  add(current);
6608  goto scan_number_sign;
6609  }
6610 
6611  case '0':
6612  case '1':
6613  case '2':
6614  case '3':
6615  case '4':
6616  case '5':
6617  case '6':
6618  case '7':
6619  case '8':
6620  case '9':
6621  {
6622  add(current);
6623  goto scan_number_any2;
6624  }
6625 
6626  default:
6627  {
6628  error_message =
6629  "invalid number; expected '+', '-', or digit after exponent";
6630  return token_type::parse_error;
6631  }
6632  }
6633 
6634 scan_number_sign:
6635  // we just parsed an exponent sign
6636  switch (get())
6637  {
6638  case '0':
6639  case '1':
6640  case '2':
6641  case '3':
6642  case '4':
6643  case '5':
6644  case '6':
6645  case '7':
6646  case '8':
6647  case '9':
6648  {
6649  add(current);
6650  goto scan_number_any2;
6651  }
6652 
6653  default:
6654  {
6655  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after exponent sign";
6656  return token_type::parse_error;
6657  }
6658  }
6659 
6660 scan_number_any2:
6661  // we just parsed a number after the exponent or exponent sign
6662  switch (get())
6663  {
6664  case '0':
6665  case '1':
6666  case '2':
6667  case '3':
6668  case '4':
6669  case '5':
6670  case '6':
6671  case '7':
6672  case '8':
6673  case '9':
6674  {
6675  add(current);
6676  goto scan_number_any2;
6677  }
6678 
6679  default:
6680  goto scan_number_done;
6681  }
6682 
6683 scan_number_done:
6684  // unget the character after the number (we only read it to know that
6685  // we are done scanning a number)
6686  unget();
6687 
6688  char* endptr = nullptr;
6689  errno = 0;
6690 
6691  // try to parse integers first and fall back to floats
6692  if (number_type == token_type::value_unsigned)
6693  {
6694  const auto x = std::strtoull(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
6695 
6696  // we checked the number format before
6697  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
6698 
6699  if (errno == 0)
6700  {
6701  value_unsigned = static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(x);
6702  if (value_unsigned == x)
6703  {
6704  return token_type::value_unsigned;
6705  }
6706  }
6707  }
6708  else if (number_type == token_type::value_integer)
6709  {
6710  const auto x = std::strtoll(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
6711 
6712  // we checked the number format before
6713  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
6714 
6715  if (errno == 0)
6716  {
6717  value_integer = static_cast<number_integer_t>(x);
6718  if (value_integer == x)
6719  {
6720  return token_type::value_integer;
6721  }
6722  }
6723  }
6724 
6725  // this code is reached if we parse a floating-point number or if an
6726  // integer conversion above failed
6727  strtof(value_float, token_buffer.data(), &endptr);
6728 
6729  // we checked the number format before
6730  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
6731 
6732  return token_type::value_float;
6733  }
6734 
6740  token_type scan_literal(const char* literal_text, const std::size_t length,
6741  token_type return_type)
6742  {
6743  assert(current == literal_text[0]);
6744  for (std::size_t i = 1; i < length; ++i)
6745  {
6746  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get() != literal_text[i]))
6747  {
6748  error_message = "invalid literal";
6749  return token_type::parse_error;
6750  }
6751  }
6752  return return_type;
6753  }
6754 
6756  // input management
6758 
6760  void reset() noexcept
6761  {
6762  token_buffer.clear();
6763  token_string.clear();
6764  token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
6765  }
6766 
6767  /*
6768  @brief get next character from the input
6769 
6770  This function provides the interface to the used input adapter. It does
6771  not throw in case the input reached EOF, but returns a
6772  `std::char_traits<char>::eof()` in that case. Stores the scanned characters
6773  for use in error messages.
6774 
6775  @return character read from the input
6776  */
6777  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get()
6778  {
6779  ++position.chars_read_total;
6780  ++position.chars_read_current_line;
6781 
6782  if (next_unget)
6783  {
6784  // just reset the next_unget variable and work with current
6785  next_unget = false;
6786  }
6787  else
6788  {
6789  current = ia->get_character();
6790  }
6791 
6792  if (JSON_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
6793  {
6794  token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
6795  }
6796 
6797  if (current == '\n')
6798  {
6799  ++position.lines_read;
6800  position.chars_read_current_line = 0;
6801  }
6802 
6803  return current;
6804  }
6805 
6814  void unget()
6815  {
6816  next_unget = true;
6817 
6818  --position.chars_read_total;
6819 
6820  // in case we "unget" a newline, we have to also decrement the lines_read
6821  if (position.chars_read_current_line == 0)
6822  {
6823  if (position.lines_read > 0)
6824  {
6825  --position.lines_read;
6826  }
6827  }
6828  else
6829  {
6830  --position.chars_read_current_line;
6831  }
6832 
6833  if (JSON_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
6834  {
6835  assert(not token_string.empty());
6836  token_string.pop_back();
6837  }
6838  }
6839 
6841  void add(int c)
6842  {
6843  token_buffer.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(c));
6844  }
6845 
6846  public:
6848  // value getters
6850 
6852  constexpr number_integer_t get_number_integer() const noexcept
6853  {
6854  return value_integer;
6855  }
6856 
6858  constexpr number_unsigned_t get_number_unsigned() const noexcept
6859  {
6860  return value_unsigned;
6861  }
6862 
6864  constexpr number_float_t get_number_float() const noexcept
6865  {
6866  return value_float;
6867  }
6868 
6870  string_t& get_string()
6871  {
6872  return token_buffer;
6873  }
6874 
6876  // diagnostics
6878 
6880  constexpr position_t get_position() const noexcept
6881  {
6882  return position;
6883  }
6884 
6888  std::string get_token_string() const
6889  {
6890  // escape control characters
6891  std::string result;
6892  for (const auto c : token_string)
6893  {
6894  if ('\x00' <= c and c <= '\x1F')
6895  {
6896  // escape control characters
6897  std::array<char, 9> cs{{}};
6898  (std::snprintf)(cs.data(), cs.size(), "<U+%.4X>", static_cast<unsigned char>(c));
6899  result += cs.data();
6900  }
6901  else
6902  {
6903  // add character as is
6904  result.push_back(c);
6905  }
6906  }
6907 
6908  return result;
6909  }
6910 
6912  constexpr const char* get_error_message() const noexcept
6913  {
6914  return error_message;
6915  }
6916 
6918  // actual scanner
6920 
6925  bool skip_bom()
6926  {
6927  if (get() == 0xEF)
6928  {
6929  // check if we completely parse the BOM
6930  return get() == 0xBB and get() == 0xBF;
6931  }
6932 
6933  // the first character is not the beginning of the BOM; unget it to
6934  // process is later
6935  unget();
6936  return true;
6937  }
6938 
6939  token_type scan()
6940  {
6941  // initially, skip the BOM
6942  if (position.chars_read_total == 0 and not skip_bom())
6943  {
6944  error_message = "invalid BOM; must be 0xEF 0xBB 0xBF if given";
6945  return token_type::parse_error;
6946  }
6947 
6948  // read next character and ignore whitespace
6949  do
6950  {
6951  get();
6952  }
6953  while (current == ' ' or current == '\t' or current == '\n' or current == '\r');
6954 
6955  switch (current)
6956  {
6957  // structural characters
6958  case '[':
6959  return token_type::begin_array;
6960  case ']':
6961  return token_type::end_array;
6962  case '{':
6963  return token_type::begin_object;
6964  case '}':
6965  return token_type::end_object;
6966  case ':':
6967  return token_type::name_separator;
6968  case ',':
6969  return token_type::value_separator;
6970 
6971  // literals
6972  case 't':
6973  return scan_literal("true", 4, token_type::literal_true);
6974  case 'f':
6975  return scan_literal("false", 5, token_type::literal_false);
6976  case 'n':
6977  return scan_literal("null", 4, token_type::literal_null);
6978 
6979  // string
6980  case '\"':
6981  return scan_string();
6982 
6983  // number
6984  case '-':
6985  case '0':
6986  case '1':
6987  case '2':
6988  case '3':
6989  case '4':
6990  case '5':
6991  case '6':
6992  case '7':
6993  case '8':
6994  case '9':
6995  return scan_number();
6996 
6997  // end of input (the null byte is needed when parsing from
6998  // string literals)
6999  case '\0':
7000  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
7001  return token_type::end_of_input;
7002 
7003  // error
7004  default:
7005  error_message = "invalid literal";
7006  return token_type::parse_error;
7007  }
7008  }
7009 
7010  private:
7012  detail::input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
7013 
7015  std::char_traits<char>::int_type current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
7016 
7018  bool next_unget = false;
7019 
7021  position_t position {};
7022 
7024  std::vector<char> token_string {};
7025 
7027  string_t token_buffer {};
7028 
7030  const char* error_message = "";
7031 
7032  // number values
7033  number_integer_t value_integer = 0;
7034  number_unsigned_t value_unsigned = 0;
7035  number_float_t value_float = 0;
7036 
7038  const char decimal_point_char = '.';
7039 };
7040 } // namespace detail
7041 } // namespace nlohmann
7042 
7043 // #include <nlohmann/detail/input/parser.hpp>
7044 
7045 
7046 #include <cassert> // assert
7047 #include <cmath> // isfinite
7048 #include <cstdint> // uint8_t
7049 #include <functional> // function
7050 #include <string> // string
7051 #include <utility> // move
7052 #include <vector> // vector
7053 
7054 // #include <nlohmann/detail/exceptions.hpp>
7055 
7056 // #include <nlohmann/detail/input/input_adapters.hpp>
7057 
7058 // #include <nlohmann/detail/input/json_sax.hpp>
7059 
7060 // #include <nlohmann/detail/input/lexer.hpp>
7061 
7062 // #include <nlohmann/detail/macro_scope.hpp>
7063 
7064 // #include <nlohmann/detail/meta/is_sax.hpp>
7065 
7066 // #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>

7068 
7069 namespace nlohmann
7070 {
7071 namespace detail
7072 {
7074 // parser //
7076 
7082 template<typename BasicJsonType>
7083 class parser
7084 {
7085  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
7086  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
7087  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
7088  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
7089  using lexer_t = lexer<BasicJsonType>;
7090  using token_type = typename lexer_t::token_type;
7091 
7092  public:
7093  enum class parse_event_t : uint8_t
7094  {
7096  object_start,
7098  object_end,
7100  array_start,
7102  array_end,
7104  key,
7106  value
7107  };
7108 
7109  using parser_callback_t =
7110  std::function<bool(int depth, parse_event_t event, BasicJsonType& parsed)>;
7111 
7113  explicit parser(detail::input_adapter_t&& adapter,
7114  const parser_callback_t cb = nullptr,
7115  const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
7116  : callback(cb), m_lexer(std::move(adapter)), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
7117  {
7118  // read first token
7119  get_token();
7120  }
7121 
7132  void parse(const bool strict, BasicJsonType& result)
7133  {
7134  if (callback)
7135  {
7136  json_sax_dom_callback_parser<BasicJsonType> sdp(result, callback, allow_exceptions);
7137  sax_parse_internal(&sdp);
7138  result.assert_invariant();
7139 
7140  // in strict mode, input must be completely read
7141  if (strict and (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
7142  {
7143  sdp.parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7144  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7145  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7146  exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value")));
7147  }
7148 
7149  // in case of an error, return discarded value
7150  if (sdp.is_errored())
7151  {
7152  result = value_t::discarded;
7153  return;
7154  }
7155 
7156  // set top-level value to null if it was discarded by the callback
7157  // function
7158  if (result.is_discarded())
7159  {
7160  result = nullptr;
7161  }
7162  }
7163  else
7164  {
7165  json_sax_dom_parser<BasicJsonType> sdp(result, allow_exceptions);
7166  sax_parse_internal(&sdp);
7167  result.assert_invariant();
7168 
7169  // in strict mode, input must be completely read
7170  if (strict and (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
7171  {
7172  sdp.parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7173  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7174  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7175  exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value")));
7176  }
7177 
7178  // in case of an error, return discarded value
7179  if (sdp.is_errored())
7180  {
7181  result = value_t::discarded;
7182  return;
7183  }
7184  }
7185  }
7186 
7193  bool accept(const bool strict = true)
7194  {
7195  json_sax_acceptor<BasicJsonType> sax_acceptor;
7196  return sax_parse(&sax_acceptor, strict);
7197  }
7198 
7199  template <typename SAX>
7200  bool sax_parse(SAX* sax, const bool strict = true)
7201  {
7202  (void)detail::is_sax_static_asserts<SAX, BasicJsonType> {};
7203  const bool result = sax_parse_internal(sax);
7204 
7205  // strict mode: next byte must be EOF
7206  if (result and strict and (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
7207  {
7208  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7209  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7210  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7211  exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value")));
7212  }
7213 
7214  return result;
7215  }
7216 
7217  private:
7218  template <typename SAX>
7219  bool sax_parse_internal(SAX* sax)
7220  {
7221  // stack to remember the hierarchy of structured values we are parsing
7222  // true = array; false = object
7223  std::vector<bool> states;
7224  // value to avoid a goto (see comment where set to true)
7225  bool skip_to_state_evaluation = false;
7226 
7227  while (true)
7228  {
7229  if (not skip_to_state_evaluation)
7230  {
7231  // invariant: get_token() was called before each iteration
7232  switch (last_token)
7233  {
7234  case token_type::begin_object:
7235  {
7236  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(std::size_t(-1))))
7237  {
7238  return false;
7239  }
7240 
7241  // closing } -> we are done
7242  if (get_token() == token_type::end_object)
7243  {
7244  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_object()))
7245  {
7246  return false;
7247  }
7248  break;
7249  }
7250 
7251  // parse key
7252  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(last_token != token_type::value_string))
7253  {
7254  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7255  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7256  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7257  exception_message(token_type::value_string, "object key")));
7258  }
7259  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->key(m_lexer.get_string())))
7260  {
7261  return false;
7262  }
7263 
7264  // parse separator (:)
7265  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::name_separator))
7266  {
7267  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7268  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7269  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7270  exception_message(token_type::name_separator, "object separator")));
7271  }
7272 
7273  // remember we are now inside an object
7274  states.push_back(false);
7275 
7276  // parse values
7277  get_token();
7278  continue;
7279  }
7280 
7281  case token_type::begin_array:
7282  {
7283  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(std::size_t(-1))))
7284  {
7285  return false;
7286  }
7287 
7288  // closing ] -> we are done
7289  if (get_token() == token_type::end_array)
7290  {
7291  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_array()))
7292  {
7293  return false;
7294  }
7295  break;
7296  }
7297 
7298  // remember we are now inside an array
7299  states.push_back(true);
7300 
7301  // parse values (no need to call get_token)
7302  continue;
7303  }
7304 
7305  case token_type::value_float:
7306  {
7307  const auto res = m_lexer.get_number_float();
7308 
7309  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not std::isfinite(res)))
7310  {
7311  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7312  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7313  out_of_range::create(406, "number overflow parsing '" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'"));
7314  }
7315 
7316  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->number_float(res, m_lexer.get_string())))
7317  {
7318  return false;
7319  }
7320 
7321  break;
7322  }
7323 
7324  case token_type::literal_false:
7325  {
7326  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->boolean(false)))
7327  {
7328  return false;
7329  }
7330  break;
7331  }
7332 
7333  case token_type::literal_null:
7334  {
7335  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->null()))
7336  {
7337  return false;
7338  }
7339  break;
7340  }
7341 
7342  case token_type::literal_true:
7343  {
7344  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->boolean(true)))
7345  {
7346  return false;
7347  }
7348  break;
7349  }
7350 
7351  case token_type::value_integer:
7352  {
7353  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->number_integer(m_lexer.get_number_integer())))
7354  {
7355  return false;
7356  }
7357  break;
7358  }
7359 
7360  case token_type::value_string:
7361  {
7362  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->string(m_lexer.get_string())))
7363  {
7364  return false;
7365  }
7366  break;
7367  }
7368 
7369  case token_type::value_unsigned:
7370  {
7371  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->number_unsigned(m_lexer.get_number_unsigned())))
7372  {
7373  return false;
7374  }
7375  break;
7376  }
7377 
7378  case token_type::parse_error:
7379  {
7380  // using "uninitialized" to avoid "expected" message
7381  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7382  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7383  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7384  exception_message(token_type::uninitialized, "value")));
7385  }
7386 
7387  default: // the last token was unexpected
7388  {
7389  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7390  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7391  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7392  exception_message(token_type::literal_or_value, "value")));
7393  }
7394  }
7395  }
7396  else
7397  {
7398  skip_to_state_evaluation = false;
7399  }
7400 
7401  // we reached this line after we successfully parsed a value
7402  if (states.empty())
7403  {
7404  // empty stack: we reached the end of the hierarchy: done
7405  return true;
7406  }
7407 
7408  if (states.back()) // array
7409  {
7410  // comma -> next value
7411  if (get_token() == token_type::value_separator)
7412  {
7413  // parse a new value
7414  get_token();
7415  continue;
7416  }
7417 
7418  // closing ]
7419  if (JSON_LIKELY(last_token == token_type::end_array))
7420  {
7421  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_array()))
7422  {
7423  return false;
7424  }
7425 
7426  // We are done with this array. Before we can parse a
7427  // new value, we need to evaluate the new state first.
7428  // By setting skip_to_state_evaluation to false, we
7429  // are effectively jumping to the beginning of this if.
7430  assert(not states.empty());
7431  states.pop_back();
7432  skip_to_state_evaluation = true;
7433  continue;
7434  }
7435 
7436  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7437  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7438  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7439  exception_message(token_type::end_array, "array")));
7440  }
7441  else // object
7442  {
7443  // comma -> next value
7444  if (get_token() == token_type::value_separator)
7445  {
7446  // parse key
7447  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::value_string))
7448  {
7449  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7450  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7451  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7452  exception_message(token_type::value_string, "object key")));
7453  }
7454 
7455  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->key(m_lexer.get_string())))
7456  {
7457  return false;
7458  }
7459 
7460  // parse separator (:)
7461  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::name_separator))
7462  {
7463  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7464  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7465  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7466  exception_message(token_type::name_separator, "object separator")));
7467  }
7468 
7469  // parse values
7470  get_token();
7471  continue;
7472  }
7473 
7474  // closing }
7475  if (JSON_LIKELY(last_token == token_type::end_object))
7476  {
7477  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_object()))
7478  {
7479  return false;
7480  }
7481 
7482  // We are done with this object. Before we can parse a
7483  // new value, we need to evaluate the new state first.
7484  // By setting skip_to_state_evaluation to false, we
7485  // are effectively jumping to the beginning of this if.
7486  assert(not states.empty());
7487  states.pop_back();
7488  skip_to_state_evaluation = true;
7489  continue;
7490  }
7491 
7492  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7493  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7494  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7495  exception_message(token_type::end_object, "object")));
7496  }
7497  }
7498  }
7499 
7501  token_type get_token()
7502  {
7503  return last_token = m_lexer.scan();
7504  }
7505 
7506  std::string exception_message(const token_type expected, const std::string& context)
7507  {
7508  std::string error_msg = "syntax error ";
7509 
7510  if (not context.empty())
7511  {
7512  error_msg += "while parsing " + context + " ";
7513  }
7514 
7515  error_msg += "- ";
7516 
7517  if (last_token == token_type::parse_error)
7518  {
7519  error_msg += std::string(m_lexer.get_error_message()) + "; last read: '" +
7520  m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'";
7521  }
7522  else
7523  {
7524  error_msg += "unexpected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(last_token));
7525  }
7526 
7527  if (expected != token_type::uninitialized)
7528  {
7529  error_msg += "; expected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(expected));
7530  }
7531 
7532  return error_msg;
7533  }
7534 
7535  private:
7537  const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
7539  token_type last_token = token_type::uninitialized;
7541  lexer_t m_lexer;
7543  const bool allow_exceptions = true;
7544 };
7545 } // namespace detail
7546 } // namespace nlohmann
7547 
7548 // #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/internal_iterator.hpp>
7549 
7550 
7551 // #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/primitive_iterator.hpp>
7552 
7553 
7554 #include <cstddef> // ptrdiff_t
7555 #include <limits> // numeric_limits
7556 
7557 namespace nlohmann
7558 {
7559 namespace detail
7560 {
7561 /*
7562 @brief an iterator for primitive JSON types
7563 
7564 This class models an iterator for primitive JSON types (boolean, number,
7565 string). It's only purpose is to allow the iterator/const_iterator classes
7566 to "iterate" over primitive values. Internally, the iterator is modeled by
7567 a `difference_type` variable. Value begin_value (`0`) models the begin,
7568 end_value (`1`) models past the end.
7569 */
7570 class primitive_iterator_t
7571 {
7572  private:
7573  using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
7574  static constexpr difference_type begin_value = 0;
7575  static constexpr difference_type end_value = begin_value + 1;
7576 
7578  difference_type m_it = (std::numeric_limits<std::ptrdiff_t>::min)();
7579 
7580  public:
7581  constexpr difference_type get_value() const noexcept
7582  {
7583  return m_it;
7584  }
7585 
7587  void set_begin() noexcept
7588  {
7589  m_it = begin_value;
7590  }
7591 
7593  void set_end() noexcept
7594  {
7595  m_it = end_value;
7596  }
7597 
7599  constexpr bool is_begin() const noexcept
7600  {
7601  return m_it == begin_value;
7602  }
7603 
7605  constexpr bool is_end() const noexcept
7606  {
7607  return m_it == end_value;
7608  }
7609 
7610  friend constexpr bool operator==(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
7611  {
7612  return lhs.m_it == rhs.m_it;
7613  }
7614 
7615  friend constexpr bool operator<(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
7616  {
7617  return lhs.m_it < rhs.m_it;
7618  }
7619 
7620  primitive_iterator_t operator+(difference_type n) noexcept
7621  {
7622  auto result = *this;
7623  result += n;
7624  return result;
7625  }
7626 
7627  friend constexpr difference_type operator-(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
7628  {
7629  return lhs.m_it - rhs.m_it;
7630  }
7631 
7632  primitive_iterator_t& operator++() noexcept
7633  {
7634  ++m_it;
7635  return *this;
7636  }
7637 
7638  primitive_iterator_t const operator++(int) noexcept
7639  {
7640  auto result = *this;
7641  ++m_it;
7642  return result;
7643  }
7644 
7645  primitive_iterator_t& operator--() noexcept
7646  {
7647  --m_it;
7648  return *this;
7649  }
7650 
7651  primitive_iterator_t const operator--(int) noexcept
7652  {
7653  auto result = *this;
7654  --m_it;
7655  return result;
7656  }
7657 
7658  primitive_iterator_t& operator+=(difference_type n) noexcept
7659  {
7660  m_it += n;
7661  return *this;
7662  }
7663 
7664  primitive_iterator_t& operator-=(difference_type n) noexcept
7665  {
7666  m_it -= n;
7667  return *this;
7668  }
7669 };
7670 } // namespace detail
7671 } // namespace nlohmann

7725 
7742 template<typename BasicJsonType>
7743 class iter_impl
7744 {
7746  friend iter_impl<typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value, typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type, const BasicJsonType>::type>;
7747  friend BasicJsonType;
7748  friend iteration_proxy<iter_impl>;
7749  friend iteration_proxy_value<iter_impl>;
7750 
7751  using object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
7752  using array_t = typename BasicJsonType::array_t;
7753  // make sure BasicJsonType is basic_json or const basic_json
7754  static_assert(is_basic_json<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>::value,
7755  "iter_impl only accepts (const) basic_json");
7756 
7757  public:
7758 
7764  using iterator_category = std::bidirectional_iterator_tag;
7765 
7767  using value_type = typename BasicJsonType::value_type;
7769  using difference_type = typename BasicJsonType::difference_type;
7771  using pointer = typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value,
7772  typename BasicJsonType::const_pointer,
7773  typename BasicJsonType::pointer>::type;
7775  using reference =
7776  typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value,
7777  typename BasicJsonType::const_reference,
7778  typename BasicJsonType::reference>::type;
7779 
7781  iter_impl() = default;
7782 
7789  explicit iter_impl(pointer object) noexcept : m_object(object)
7790  {
7791  assert(m_object != nullptr);
7792 
7793  switch (m_object->m_type)
7794  {
7795  case value_t::object:
7796  {
7797  m_it.object_iterator = typename object_t::iterator();
7798  break;
7799  }
7800 
7801  case value_t::array:
7802  {
7803  m_it.array_iterator = typename array_t::iterator();
7804  break;
7805  }
7806 
7807  default:
7808  {
7809  m_it.primitive_iterator = primitive_iterator_t();
7810  break;
7811  }
7812  }
7813  }
7814 
7829  iter_impl(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept
7830  : m_object(other.m_object), m_it(other.m_it) {}
7831 
7838  iter_impl& operator=(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept
7839  {
7840  m_object = other.m_object;
7841  m_it = other.m_it;
7842  return *this;
7843  }
7844 
7845  private:
7850  void set_begin() noexcept
7851  {
7852  assert(m_object != nullptr);
7853 
7854  switch (m_object->m_type)
7855  {
7856  case value_t::object:
7857  {
7858  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->begin();
7859  break;
7860  }
7861 
7862  case value_t::array:
7863  {
7864  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->begin();
7865  break;
7866  }
7867 
7868  case value_t::null:
7869  {
7870  // set to end so begin()==end() is true: null is empty
7871  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
7872  break;
7873  }
7874 
7875  default:
7876  {
7877  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_begin();
7878  break;
7879  }
7880  }
7881  }
7882 
7887  void set_end() noexcept
7888  {
7889  assert(m_object != nullptr);
7890 
7891  switch (m_object->m_type)
7892  {
7893  case value_t::object:
7894  {
7895  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->end();
7896  break;
7897  }
7898 
7899  case value_t::array:
7900  {
7901  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->end();
7902  break;
7903  }
7904 
7905  default:
7906  {
7907  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
7908  break;
7909  }
7910  }
7911  }
7912 
7913  public:
7918  reference operator*() const
7919  {
7920  assert(m_object != nullptr);
7921 
7922  switch (m_object->m_type)
7923  {
7924  case value_t::object:
7925  {
7926  assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
7927  return m_it.object_iterator->second;
7928  }
7929 
7930  case value_t::array:
7931  {
7932  assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
7933  return *m_it.array_iterator;
7934  }
7935 
7936  case value_t::null:
7937  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
7938 
7939  default:
7940  {
7941  if (JSON_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
7942  {
7943  return *m_object;
7944  }
7945 
7946  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
7947  }
7948  }
7949  }
7950 
7955  pointer operator->() const
7956  {
7957  assert(m_object != nullptr);
7958 
7959  switch (m_object->m_type)
7960  {
7961  case value_t::object:
7962  {
7963  assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
7964  return &(m_it.object_iterator->second);
7965  }
7966 
7967  case value_t::array:
7968  {
7969  assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
7970  return &*m_it.array_iterator;
7971  }
7972 
7973  default:
7974  {
7975  if (JSON_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
7976  {
7977  return m_object;
7978  }
7979 
7980  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
7981  }
7982  }
7983  }
7984 
7989  iter_impl const operator++(int)
7990  {
7991  auto result = *this;
7992  ++(*this);
7993  return result;
7994  }
7995 
8000  iter_impl& operator++()
8001  {
8002  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8003 
8004  switch (m_object->m_type)
8005  {
8006  case value_t::object:
8007  {
8008  std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, 1);
8009  break;
8010  }
8011 
8012  case value_t::array:
8013  {
8014  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, 1);
8015  break;
8016  }
8017 
8018  default:
8019  {
8020  ++m_it.primitive_iterator;
8021  break;
8022  }
8023  }
8024 
8025  return *this;
8026  }
8027 
8032  iter_impl const operator--(int)
8033  {
8034  auto result = *this;
8035  --(*this);
8036  return result;
8037  }
8038 
8043  iter_impl& operator--()
8044  {
8045  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8046 
8047  switch (m_object->m_type)
8048  {
8049  case value_t::object:
8050  {
8051  std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, -1);
8052  break;
8053  }
8054 
8055  case value_t::array:
8056  {
8057  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, -1);
8058  break;
8059  }
8060 
8061  default:
8062  {
8063  --m_it.primitive_iterator;
8064  break;
8065  }
8066  }
8067 
8068  return *this;
8069  }
8070 
8075  bool operator==(const iter_impl& other) const
8076  {
8077  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
8078  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object))
8079  {
8080  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
8081  }
8082 
8083  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8084 
8085  switch (m_object->m_type)
8086  {
8087  case value_t::object:
8088  return (m_it.object_iterator == other.m_it.object_iterator);
8089 
8090  case value_t::array:
8091  return (m_it.array_iterator == other.m_it.array_iterator);
8092 
8093  default:
8094  return (m_it.primitive_iterator == other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
8095  }
8096  }
8097 
8102  bool operator!=(const iter_impl& other) const
8103  {
8104  return not operator==(other);
8105  }
8106 
8111  bool operator<(const iter_impl& other) const
8112  {
8113  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
8114  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object))
8115  {
8116  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
8117  }
8118 
8119  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8120 
8121  switch (m_object->m_type)
8122  {
8123  case value_t::object:
8124  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(213, "cannot compare order of object iterators"));
8125 
8126  case value_t::array:
8127  return (m_it.array_iterator < other.m_it.array_iterator);
8128 
8129  default:
8130  return (m_it.primitive_iterator < other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
8131  }
8132  }
8133 
8138  bool operator<=(const iter_impl& other) const
8139  {
8140  return not other.operator < (*this);
8141  }
8142 
8147  bool operator>(const iter_impl& other) const
8148  {
8149  return not operator<=(other);
8150  }
8151 
8156  bool operator>=(const iter_impl& other) const
8157  {
8158  return not operator<(other);
8159  }
8160 
8165  iter_impl& operator+=(difference_type i)
8166  {
8167  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8168 
8169  switch (m_object->m_type)
8170  {
8171  case value_t::object:
8172  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(209, "cannot use offsets with object iterators"));
8173 
8174  case value_t::array:
8175  {
8176  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, i);
8177  break;
8178  }
8179 
8180  default:
8181  {
8182  m_it.primitive_iterator += i;
8183  break;
8184  }
8185  }
8186 
8187  return *this;
8188  }
8189 
8194  iter_impl& operator-=(difference_type i)
8195  {
8196  return operator+=(-i);
8197  }
8198 
8203  iter_impl operator+(difference_type i) const
8204  {
8205  auto result = *this;
8206  result += i;
8207  return result;
8208  }
8209 
8214  friend iter_impl operator+(difference_type i, const iter_impl& it)
8215  {
8216  auto result = it;
8217  result += i;
8218  return result;
8219  }
8220 
8225  iter_impl operator-(difference_type i) const
8226  {
8227  auto result = *this;
8228  result -= i;
8229  return result;
8230  }
8231 
8236  difference_type operator-(const iter_impl& other) const
8237  {
8238  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8239 
8240  switch (m_object->m_type)
8241  {
8242  case value_t::object:
8243  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(209, "cannot use offsets with object iterators"));
8244 
8245  case value_t::array:
8246  return m_it.array_iterator - other.m_it.array_iterator;
8247 
8248  default:
8249  return m_it.primitive_iterator - other.m_it.primitive_iterator;
8250  }
8251  }
8252 
8257  reference operator[](difference_type n) const
8258  {
8259  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8260 
8261  switch (m_object->m_type)
8262  {
8263  case value_t::object:
8264  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(208, "cannot use operator[] for object iterators"));
8265 
8266  case value_t::array:
8267  return *std::next(m_it.array_iterator, n);
8268 
8269  case value_t::null:
8270  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
8271 
8272  default:
8273  {
8274  if (JSON_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.get_value() == -n))
8275  {
8276  return *m_object;
8277  }
8278 
8279  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
8280  }
8281  }
8282  }
8283 
8288  const typename object_t::key_type& key() const
8289  {
8290  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8291 
8292  if (JSON_LIKELY(m_object->is_object()))
8293  {
8294  return m_it.object_iterator->first;
8295  }
8296 
8297  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(207, "cannot use key() for non-object iterators"));
8298  }
8299 
8304  reference value() const
8305  {
8306  return operator*();
8307  }
8308 
8309  private:
8311  pointer m_object = nullptr;
8313  internal_iterator<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type> m_it {};
8314 };
8315 } // namespace detail

8353 template<typename Base>
8354 class json_reverse_iterator : public std::reverse_iterator<Base>
8355 {
8356  public:
8357  using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
8359  using base_iterator = std::reverse_iterator<Base>;
8361  using reference = typename Base::reference;
8362 
8364  explicit json_reverse_iterator(const typename base_iterator::iterator_type& it) noexcept
8365  : base_iterator(it) {}
8366 
8368  explicit json_reverse_iterator(const base_iterator& it) noexcept : base_iterator(it) {}
8369 
8371  json_reverse_iterator const operator++(int)
8372  {
8373  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator++(1));
8374  }
8375 
8377  json_reverse_iterator& operator++()
8378  {
8379  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator++());
8380  }
8381 
8383  json_reverse_iterator const operator--(int)
8384  {
8385  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator--(1));
8386  }
8387 
8389  json_reverse_iterator& operator--()
8390  {
8391  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator--());
8392  }
8393 
8395  json_reverse_iterator& operator+=(difference_type i)
8396  {
8397  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator+=(i));
8398  }
8399 
8401  json_reverse_iterator operator+(difference_type i) const
8402  {
8403  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator+(i));
8404  }
8405 
8407  json_reverse_iterator operator-(difference_type i) const
8408  {
8409  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator-(i));
8410  }
8411 
8413  difference_type operator-(const json_reverse_iterator& other) const
8414  {
8415  return base_iterator(*this) - base_iterator(other);
8416  }
8417 
8419  reference operator[](difference_type n) const
8420  {
8421  return *(this->operator+(n));
8422  }
8423 
8425  auto key() const -> decltype(std::declval<Base>().key())
8426  {
8427  auto it = --this->base();
8428  return it.key();
8429  }
8430 
8432  reference value() const
8433  {
8434  auto it = --this->base();
8435  return it.operator * ();
8436  }
8437 };
