8446 #include <algorithm> // all_of
8447 #include <cassert> // assert
8448 #include <numeric> // accumulate
8449 #include <string> // string
8450 #include <utility> // move
8451 #include <vector> // vector
8452 
8453 // #include <nlohmann/detail/exceptions.hpp>
8454 
8455 // #include <nlohmann/detail/macro_scope.hpp>
8456 
8457 // #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>
8458 
8459 
8460 namespace nlohmann
8461 {
8462 template<typename BasicJsonType>
8463 class json_pointer
8464 {
8465  // allow basic_json to access private members
8466  NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION
8467  friend class basic_json;
8468 
8469  public:
8491  explicit json_pointer(const std::string& s = "")
8492  : reference_tokens(split(s))
8493  {}
8494 
8509  std::string to_string() const
8510  {
8511  return std::accumulate(reference_tokens.begin(), reference_tokens.end(),
8512  std::string{},
8513  [](const std::string & a, const std::string & b)
8514  {
8515  return a + "/" + escape(b);
8516  });
8517  }
8518 
8520  operator std::string() const
8521  {
8522  return to_string();
8523  }
8524 
8541  json_pointer& operator/=(const json_pointer& ptr)
8542  {
8543  reference_tokens.insert(reference_tokens.end(),
8544  ptr.reference_tokens.begin(),
8545  ptr.reference_tokens.end());
8546  return *this;
8547  }
8548 
8565  json_pointer& operator/=(std::string token)
8566  {
8567  push_back(std::move(token));
8568  return *this;
8569  }
8570 
8587  json_pointer& operator/=(std::size_t array_index)
8588  {
8589  return *this /= std::to_string(array_index);
8590  }
8591 
8607  friend json_pointer operator/(const json_pointer& lhs,
8608  const json_pointer& rhs)
8609  {
8610  return json_pointer(lhs) /= rhs;
8611  }
8612 
8628  friend json_pointer operator/(const json_pointer& ptr, std::string token)
8629  {
8630  return json_pointer(ptr) /= std::move(token);
8631  }
8632 
8648  friend json_pointer operator/(const json_pointer& ptr, std::size_t array_index)
8649  {
8650  return json_pointer(ptr) /= array_index;
8651  }
8652 
8666  json_pointer parent_pointer() const
8667  {
8668  if (empty())
8669  {
8670  return *this;
8671  }
8672 
8673  json_pointer res = *this;
8674  res.pop_back();
8675  return res;
8676  }
8677 
8691  void pop_back()
8692  {
8693  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(empty()))
8694  {
8695  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
8696  }
8697 
8698  reference_tokens.pop_back();
8699  }
8700 
8715  const std::string& back()
8716  {
8717  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(empty()))
8718  {
8719  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
8720  }
8721 
8722  return reference_tokens.back();
8723  }
8724 
8737  void push_back(const std::string& token)
8738  {
8739  reference_tokens.push_back(token);
8740  }
8741 
8743  void push_back(std::string&& token)
8744  {
8745  reference_tokens.push_back(std::move(token));
8746  }
8747 
8762  bool empty() const noexcept
8763  {
8764  return reference_tokens.empty();
8765  }
8766 
8767  private:
8775  static int array_index(const std::string& s)
8776  {
8777  std::size_t processed_chars = 0;
8778  const int res = std::stoi(s, &processed_chars);
8779 
8780  // check if the string was completely read
8781  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(processed_chars != s.size()))
8782  {
8783  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + s + "'"));
8784  }
8785 
8786  return res;
8787  }
8788 
8789  json_pointer top() const
8790  {
8791  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(empty()))
8792  {
8793  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
8794  }
8795 
8796  json_pointer result = *this;
8797  result.reference_tokens = {reference_tokens[0]};
8798  return result;
8799  }
8800 
8809  BasicJsonType& get_and_create(BasicJsonType& j) const
8810  {
8811  using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
8812  auto result = &j;
8813 
8814  // in case no reference tokens exist, return a reference to the JSON value
8815  // j which will be overwritten by a primitive value
8816  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
8817  {
8818  switch (result->m_type)
8819  {
8820  case detail::value_t::null:
8821  {
8822  if (reference_token == "0")
8823  {
8824  // start a new array if reference token is 0
8825  result = &result->operator[](0);
8826  }
8827  else
8828  {
8829  // start a new object otherwise
8830  result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
8831  }
8832  break;
8833  }
8834 
8835  case detail::value_t::object:
8836  {
8837  // create an entry in the object
8838  result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
8839  break;
8840  }
8841 
8842  case detail::value_t::array:
8843  {
8844  // create an entry in the array
8845  JSON_TRY
8846  {
8847  result = &result->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
8848  }
8849  JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&)
8850  {
8851  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
8852  }
8853  break;
8854  }
8855 
8856  /*
8857  The following code is only reached if there exists a reference
8858  token _and_ the current value is primitive. In this case, we have
8859  an error situation, because primitive values may only occur as
8860  single value; that is, with an empty list of reference tokens.
8861  */
8862  default:
8863  JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(313, "invalid value to unflatten"));
8864  }
8865  }
8866 
8867  return *result;
8868  }
8869 
8889  BasicJsonType& get_unchecked(BasicJsonType* ptr) const
8890  {
8891  using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
8892  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
8893  {
8894  // convert null values to arrays or objects before continuing
8895  if (ptr->m_type == detail::value_t::null)
8896  {
8897  // check if reference token is a number
8898  const bool nums =
8899  std::all_of(reference_token.begin(), reference_token.end(),
8900  [](const char x)
8901  {
8902  return x >= '0' and x <= '9';
8903  });
8904 
8905  // change value to array for numbers or "-" or to object otherwise
8906  *ptr = (nums or reference_token == "-")
8907  ? detail::value_t::array
8908  : detail::value_t::object;
8909  }
8910 
8911  switch (ptr->m_type)
8912  {
8913  case detail::value_t::object:
8914  {
8915  // use unchecked object access
8916  ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
8917  break;
8918  }
8919 
8920  case detail::value_t::array:
8921  {
8922  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
8923  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0'))
8924  {
8925  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(106, 0,
8926  "array index '" + reference_token +
8927  "' must not begin with '0'"));
8928  }
8929 
8930  if (reference_token == "-")
8931  {
8932  // explicitly treat "-" as index beyond the end
8933  ptr = &ptr->operator[](ptr->m_value.array->size());
8934  }
8935  else
8936  {
8937  // convert array index to number; unchecked access
8938  JSON_TRY
8939  {
8940  ptr = &ptr->operator[](
8941  static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
8942  }
8943  JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&)
8944  {
8945  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
8946  }
8947  }
8948  break;
8949  }
8950 
8951  default:
8952  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
8953  }
8954  }
8955 
8956  return *ptr;
8957  }
8958 
8965  BasicJsonType& get_checked(BasicJsonType* ptr) const
8966  {
8967  using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
8968  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
8969  {
8970  switch (ptr->m_type)
8971  {
8972  case detail::value_t::object:
8973  {
8974  // note: at performs range check
8975  ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
8976  break;
8977  }
8978 
8979  case detail::value_t::array:
8980  {
8981  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
8982  {
8983  // "-" always fails the range check
8984  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402,
8985  "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
8986  ") is out of range"));
8987  }
8988 
8989  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
8990  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0'))
8991  {
8992  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(106, 0,
8993  "array index '" + reference_token +
8994  "' must not begin with '0'"));
8995  }
8996 
8997  // note: at performs range check
8998  JSON_TRY
8999  {
9000  ptr = &ptr->at(static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
9001  }
9002  JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&)
9003  {
9004  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
9005  }
9006  break;
9007  }
9008 
9009  default:
9010  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
9011  }
9012  }
9013 
9014  return *ptr;
9015  }
9016 
9030  const BasicJsonType& get_unchecked(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const
9031  {
9032  using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
9033  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
9034  {
9035  switch (ptr->m_type)
9036  {
9037  case detail::value_t::object:
9038  {
9039  // use unchecked object access
9040  ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
9041  break;
9042  }
9043 
9044  case detail::value_t::array:
9045  {
9046  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
9047  {
9048  // "-" cannot be used for const access
9049  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402,
9050  "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
9051  ") is out of range"));
9052  }
9053 
9054  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
9055  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0'))
9056  {
9057  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(106, 0,
9058  "array index '" + reference_token +
9059  "' must not begin with '0'"));
9060  }
9061 
9062  // use unchecked array access
9063  JSON_TRY
9064  {
9065  ptr = &ptr->operator[](
9066  static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
9067  }
9068  JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&)
9069  {
9070  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
9071  }
9072  break;
9073  }
9074 
9075  default:
9076  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
9077  }
9078  }
9079 
9080  return *ptr;
9081  }
9082

9092  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
9093  {

9097  {
9098  // note: at performs range check
9099  ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
9100  break;
9101  }
9102 
9103  case detail::value_t::array:
9104  {
9105  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
9106  {
9107  // "-" always fails the range check
9108  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402,
9109  "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
9110  ") is out of range"));
9111  }
9112 
9113  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
9114  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0'))

9125  }

9140 
9150  static std::vector<std::string> split(const std::string& reference_string)
9151  {
9152  std::vector<std::string> result;
9153 
9154  // special case: empty reference string -> no reference tokens
9155  if (reference_string.empty())
9156  {
9157  return result;
9158  }
9159 
9160  // check if nonempty reference string begins with slash
9161  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_string[0] != '/'))
9162  {
9163  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(107, 1,
9164  "JSON pointer must be empty or begin with '/' - was: '" +
9165  reference_string + "'"));
9166  }
9167 
9168  // extract the reference tokens:
9169  // - slash: position of the last read slash (or end of string)
9170  // - start: position after the previous slash
9171  for (
9172  // search for the first slash after the first character
9173  std::size_t slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', 1),
9174  // set the beginning of the first reference token
9175  start = 1;
9176  // we can stop if start == 0 (if slash == std::string::npos)
9177  start != 0;
9178  // set the beginning of the next reference token
9179  // (will eventually be 0 if slash == std::string::npos)
9180  start = (slash == std::string::npos) ? 0 : slash + 1,
9181  // find next slash
9182  slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', start))
9183  {
9184  // use the text between the beginning of the reference token
9185  // (start) and the last slash (slash).
9186  auto reference_token = reference_string.substr(start, slash - start);
9187 
9188  // check reference tokens are properly escaped
9189  for (std::size_t pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~');
9190  pos != std::string::npos;
9191  pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~', pos + 1))
9192  {
9193  assert(reference_token[pos] == '~');
9194 
9195  // ~ must be followed by 0 or 1
9196  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(pos == reference_token.size() - 1 or
9197  (reference_token[pos + 1] != '0' and
9198  reference_token[pos + 1] != '1')))
9199  {
9200  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(108, 0, "escape character '~' must be followed with '0' or '1'"));
9201  }
9202  }
9203 
9204  // finally, store the reference token
9205  unescape(reference_token);
9206  result.push_back(reference_token);
9207  }
9208 
9209  return result;
9210  }
9211 
9225  static void replace_substring(std::string& s, const std::string& f,
9226  const std::string& t)
9227  {
9228  assert(not f.empty());
9229  for (auto pos = s.find(f); // find first occurrence of f
9230  pos != std::string::npos; // make sure f was found
9231  s.replace(pos, f.size(), t), // replace with t, and
9232  pos = s.find(f, pos + t.size())) // find next occurrence of f
9233  {}
9234  }
9235 
9237  static std::string escape(std::string s)
9238  {
9239  replace_substring(s, "~", "~0");
9240  replace_substring(s, "/", "~1");
9241  return s;
9242  }
9243 
9245  static void unescape(std::string& s)
9246  {
9247  replace_substring(s, "~1", "/");
9248  replace_substring(s, "~0", "~");
9249  }
9250 
9258  static void flatten(const std::string& reference_string,
9259  const BasicJsonType& value,
9260  BasicJsonType& result)
9261  {
9262  switch (value.m_type)
9263  {
9264  case detail::value_t::array:
9265  {
9266  if (value.m_value.array->empty())
9267  {
9268  // flatten empty array as null
9269  result[reference_string] = nullptr;
9270  }
9271  else
9272  {
9273  // iterate array and use index as reference string
9274  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < value.m_value.array->size(); ++i)
9275  {
9276  flatten(reference_string + "/" + std::to_string(i),
9277  value.m_value.array->operator[](i), result);
9278  }
9279  }
9280  break;
9281  }
9282 
9283  case detail::value_t::object:
9284  {
9285  if (value.m_value.object->empty())
9286  {
9287  // flatten empty object as null
9288  result[reference_string] = nullptr;
9289  }
9290  else
9291  {
9292  // iterate object and use keys as reference string
9293  for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object)
9294  {
9295  flatten(reference_string + "/" + escape(element.first), element.second, result);
9296  }
9297  }
9298  break;
9299  }
9300 
9301  default:
9302  {
9303  // add primitive value with its reference string
9304  result[reference_string] = value;
9305  break;
9306  }
9307  }
9308  }
9309 
9320  static BasicJsonType
9321  unflatten(const BasicJsonType& value)
9322  {
9323  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not value.is_object()))
9324  {
9325  JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(314, "only objects can be unflattened"));
9326  }
9327 
9328  BasicJsonType result;
9329 
9330  // iterate the JSON object values
9331  for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object)
9332  {
9333  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not element.second.is_primitive()))
9334  {
9335  JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(315, "values in object must be primitive"));
9336  }
9337 
9338  // assign value to reference pointed to by JSON pointer; Note that if
9339  // the JSON pointer is "" (i.e., points to the whole value), function
9340  // get_and_create returns a reference to result itself. An assignment
9341  // will then create a primitive value.
9342  json_pointer(element.first).get_and_create(result) = element.second;
9343  }
9344 
9345  return result;
9346  }
9347 
9359  friend bool operator==(json_pointer const& lhs,
9360  json_pointer const& rhs) noexcept
9361  {
9362  return lhs.reference_tokens == rhs.reference_tokens;
9363  }
9364 
9376  friend bool operator!=(json_pointer const& lhs,
9377  json_pointer const& rhs) noexcept
9378  {
9379  return not (lhs == rhs);
9380  }
9381 
9383  std::vector<std::string> reference_tokens;
9384 };
9385 } // namespace nlohmann

9398 namespace detail

9400 template<typename BasicJsonType>
9401 class json_ref
9402 {
9403  public:
9404  using value_type = BasicJsonType;
9405 
9406  json_ref(value_type&& value)
9407  : owned_value(std::move(value)), value_ref(&owned_value), is_rvalue(true)
9408  {}
9409 
9410  json_ref(const value_type& value)
9411  : value_ref(const_cast<value_type*>(&value)), is_rvalue(false)
9412  {}
9413 
9414  json_ref(std::initializer_list<json_ref> init)
9415  : owned_value(init), value_ref(&owned_value), is_rvalue(true)
9416  {}
9417 
9418  template <
9419  class... Args,
9420  enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<value_type, Args...>::value, int> = 0 >
9421  json_ref(Args && ... args)
9422  : owned_value(std::forward<Args>(args)...), value_ref(&owned_value),
9423  is_rvalue(true) {}
9424 
9425  // class should be movable only
9426  json_ref(json_ref&&) = default;
9427  json_ref(const json_ref&) = delete;
9428  json_ref& operator=(const json_ref&) = delete;
9429  json_ref& operator=(json_ref&&) = delete;
9430  ~json_ref() = default;
9431 
9432  value_type moved_or_copied() const
9433  {
9434  if (is_rvalue)
9435  {
9436  return std::move(*value_ref);
9437  }
9438  return *value_ref;
9439  }
9440 
9441  value_type const& operator*() const
9442  {
9443  return *static_cast<value_type const*>(value_ref);
9444  }
9445 
9446  value_type const* operator->() const
9447  {
9448  return static_cast<value_type const*>(value_ref);
9449  }
9450 
9451  private:
9452  mutable value_type owned_value = nullptr;
9453  value_type* value_ref = nullptr;
9454  const bool is_rvalue;
9455 };
9456 } // namespace detail

9494 template<typename CharType> struct output_adapter_protocol
9495 {
9496  virtual void write_character(CharType c) = 0;
9497  virtual void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) = 0;
9498  virtual ~output_adapter_protocol() = default;
9499 };
9500 
9502 template<typename CharType>
9503 using output_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<output_adapter_protocol<CharType>>;
9504 
9506 template<typename CharType>
9507 class output_vector_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
9508 {
9509  public:
9510  explicit output_vector_adapter(std::vector<CharType>& vec) noexcept
9511  : v(vec)
9512  {}
9513 
9514  void write_character(CharType c) override
9515  {
9516  v.push_back(c);
9517  }
9518 
9519  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
9520  {
9521  std::copy(s, s + length, std::back_inserter(v));
9522  }
9523 
9524  private:
9525  std::vector<CharType>& v;
9526 };
9527 
9529 template<typename CharType>
9530 class output_stream_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
9531 {
9532  public:
9533  explicit output_stream_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s) noexcept
9534  : stream(s)
9535  {}
9536 
9537  void write_character(CharType c) override
9538  {
9539  stream.put(c);
9540  }
9541 
9542  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
9543  {
9544  stream.write(s, static_cast<std::streamsize>(length));
9545  }
9546 
9547  private:
9548  std::basic_ostream<CharType>& stream;
9549 };
9550 
9552 template<typename CharType, typename StringType = std::basic_string<CharType>>
9553 class output_string_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
9554 {
9555  public:
9556  explicit output_string_adapter(StringType& s) noexcept
9557  : str(s)
9558  {}
9559 
9560  void write_character(CharType c) override
9561  {
9562  str.push_back(c);
9563  }
9564 
9565  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
9566  {
9567  str.append(s, length);
9568  }
9569 
9570  private:
9571  StringType& str;
9572 };
9573 
9574 template<typename CharType, typename StringType = std::basic_string<CharType>>
9575 class output_adapter
9576 {
9577  public:
9578  output_adapter(std::vector<CharType>& vec)
9579  : oa(std::make_shared<output_vector_adapter<CharType>>(vec)) {}
9580 
9581  output_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s)
9582  : oa(std::make_shared<output_stream_adapter<CharType>>(s)) {}
9583 
9584  output_adapter(StringType& s)
9585  : oa(std::make_shared<output_string_adapter<CharType, StringType>>(s)) {}
9586 
9587  operator output_adapter_t<CharType>()
9588  {
9589  return oa;
9590  }
9591 
9592  private:
9593  output_adapter_t<CharType> oa = nullptr;

9604 // binary writer //
9606 
9610 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CharType>
9611 class binary_writer
9612 {
9613  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
9614 
9615  public:
9621  explicit binary_writer(output_adapter_t<CharType> adapter) : oa(adapter)
9622  {
9623  assert(oa);
9624  }
9625 
9630  void write_bson(const BasicJsonType& j)
9631  {
9632  switch (j.type())
9633  {
9634  case value_t::object:
9635  {
9636  write_bson_object(*j.m_value.object);
9637  break;
9638  }
9639 
9640  default:
9641  {
9642  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(317, "to serialize to BSON, top-level type must be object, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
9643  }
9644  }
9645  }
9646 
9650  void write_cbor(const BasicJsonType& j)
9651  {
9652  switch (j.type())
9653  {
9654  case value_t::null:
9655  {
9656  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xF6));
9657  break;
9658  }
9659 
9660  case value_t::boolean:
9661  {
9662  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
9663  ? to_char_type(0xF5)
9664  : to_char_type(0xF4));
9665  break;
9666  }
9667 
9668  case value_t::number_integer:
9669  {
9670  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
9671  {
9672  // CBOR does not differentiate between positive signed
9673  // integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used the
9674  // code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
9675  if (j.m_value.number_integer <= 0x17)
9676  {
9677  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9678  }
9679  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9680  {
9681  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x18));
9682  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9683  }
9684  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9685  {
9686  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x19));
9687  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9688  }
9689  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9690  {
9691  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1A));
9692  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9693  }
9694  else
9695  {
9696  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1B));
9697  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9698  }
9699  }
9700  else
9701  {
9702  // The conversions below encode the sign in the first
9703  // byte, and the value is converted to a positive number.
9704  const auto positive_number = -1 - j.m_value.number_integer;
9705  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -24)
9706  {
9707  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x20 + positive_number));
9708  }
9709  else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9710  {
9711  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x38));
9712  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(positive_number));
9713  }
9714  else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9715  {
9716  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x39));
9717  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(positive_number));
9718  }
9719  else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9720  {
9721  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x3A));
9722  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(positive_number));
9723  }
9724  else
9725  {
9726  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x3B));
9727  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(positive_number));
9728  }
9729  }
9730  break;
9731  }
9732 
9733  case value_t::number_unsigned:
9734  {
9735  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0x17)
9736  {
9737  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
9738  }
9739  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9740  {
9741  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x18));
9742  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
9743  }
9744  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9745  {
9746  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x19));
9747  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
9748  }
9749  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9750  {
9751  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1A));
9752  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
9753  }
9754  else
9755  {
9756  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1B));
9757  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
9758  }
9759  break;
9760  }
9761 
9762  case value_t::number_float:
9763  {
9764  oa->write_character(get_cbor_float_prefix(j.m_value.number_float));
9765  write_number(j.m_value.number_float);
9766  break;
9767  }
9768 
9769  case value_t::string:
9770  {
9771  // step 1: write control byte and the string length
9772  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
9773  if (N <= 0x17)
9774  {
9775  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x60 + N));
9776  }
9777  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9778  {
9779  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x78));
9780  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
9781  }
9782  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9783  {
9784  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x79));
9785  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
9786  }
9787  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9788  {
9789  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x7A));
9790  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
9791  }
9792  // LCOV_EXCL_START
9793  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
9794  {
9795  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x7B));
9796  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
9797  }
9798  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
9799 
9800  // step 2: write the string
9801  oa->write_characters(
9802  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
9803  j.m_value.string->size());
9804  break;
9805  }
9806 
9807  case value_t::array:
9808  {
9809  // step 1: write control byte and the array size
9810  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
9811  if (N <= 0x17)
9812  {
9813  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x80 + N));
9814  }
9815  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9816  {
9817  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x98));
9818  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
9819  }
9820  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9821  {
9822  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x99));
9823  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
9824  }
9825  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9826  {
9827  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x9A));
9828  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
9829  }
9830  // LCOV_EXCL_START
9831  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
9832  {
9833  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x9B));
9834  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
9835  }
9836  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
9837 
9838  // step 2: write each element
9839  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
9840  {
9841  write_cbor(el);
9842  }
9843  break;
9844  }
9845 
9846  case value_t::object:
9847  {
9848  // step 1: write control byte and the object size
9849  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
9850  if (N <= 0x17)
9851  {
9852  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xA0 + N));
9853  }
9854  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9855  {
9856  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xB8));
9857  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
9858  }
9859  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9860  {
9861  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xB9));
9862  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
9863  }
9864  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9865  {
9866  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xBA));
9867  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
9868  }
9869  // LCOV_EXCL_START
9870  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
9871  {
9872  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xBB));
9873  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
9874  }
9875  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
9876 
9877  // step 2: write each element
9878  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
9879  {
9880  write_cbor(el.first);
9881  write_cbor(el.second);
9882  }
9883  break;
9884  }
9885 
9886  default:
9887  break;
9888  }
9889  }
9890 
9894  void write_msgpack(const BasicJsonType& j)
9895  {
9896  switch (j.type())
9897  {
9898  case value_t::null: // nil
9899  {
9900  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xC0));
9901  break;
9902  }
9903 
9904  case value_t::boolean: // true and false
9905  {
9906  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
9907  ? to_char_type(0xC3)
9908  : to_char_type(0xC2));
9909  break;
9910  }
9911 
9912  case value_t::number_integer:
9913  {
9914  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
9915  {
9916  // MessagePack does not differentiate between positive
9917  // signed integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used
9918  // the code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
9919  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
9920  {
9921  // positive fixnum
9922  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9923  }
9924  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9925  {
9926  // uint 8
9927  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCC));
9928  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9929  }
9930  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9931  {
9932  // uint 16
9933  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCD));
9934  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9935  }
9936  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9937  {
9938  // uint 32
9939  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCE));
9940  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9941  }
9942  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
9943  {
9944  // uint 64
9945  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCF));
9946  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9947  }
9948  }
9949  else
9950  {
9951  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -32)
9952  {
9953  // negative fixnum
9954  write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9955  }
9956  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::min)() and
9957  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)())
9958  {
9959  // int 8
9960  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD0));
9961  write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9962  }
9963  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::min)() and
9964  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)())
9965  {
9966  // int 16
9967  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD1));
9968  write_number(static_cast<std::int16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9969  }
9970  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() and
9971  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
9972  {
9973  // int 32
9974  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD2));
9975  write_number(static_cast<std::int32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9976  }
9977  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::min)() and
9978  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)())
9979  {
9980  // int 64
9981  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD3));
9982  write_number(static_cast<std::int64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9983  }
9984  }
9985  break;
9986  }
9987 
9988  case value_t::number_unsigned:
9989  {
9990  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
9991  {
9992  // positive fixnum
9993  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9994  }
9995  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9996  {
9997  // uint 8
9998  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCC));
9999  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10000  }
10001  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
10002  {
10003  // uint 16
10004  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCD));
10005  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10006  }
10007  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
10008  {
10009  // uint 32
10010  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCE));
10011  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10012  }
10013  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
10014  {
10015  // uint 64
10016  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCF));
10017  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10018  }
10019  break;
10020  }
10021 
10022  case value_t::number_float:
10023  {
10024  oa->write_character(get_msgpack_float_prefix(j.m_value.number_float));
10025  write_number(j.m_value.number_float);
10026  break;
10027  }
10028 
10029  case value_t::string:
10030  {
10031  // step 1: write control byte and the string length
10032  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
10033  if (N <= 31)
10034  {
10035  // fixstr
10036  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xA0 | N));
10037  }
10038  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
10039  {
10040  // str 8
10041  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD9));
10042  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
10043  }
10044  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
10045  {
10046  // str 16
10047  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDA));
10048  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
10049  }
10050  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
10051  {
10052  // str 32
10053  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDB));
10054  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
10055  }
10056 
10057  // step 2: write the string
10058  oa->write_characters(
10059  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
10060  j.m_value.string->size());
10061  break;
10062  }
10063 
10064  case value_t::array:
10065  {
10066  // step 1: write control byte and the array size
10067  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
10068  if (N <= 15)
10069  {
10070  // fixarray
10071  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x90 | N));
10072  }
10073  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
10074  {
10075  // array 16
10076  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDC));
10077  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
10078  }
10079  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
10080  {
10081  // array 32
10082  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDD));
10083  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
10084  }
10085 
10086  // step 2: write each element
10087  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
10088  {
10089  write_msgpack(el);
10090  }
10091  break;
10092  }
10093 
10094  case value_t::object:
10095  {
10096  // step 1: write control byte and the object size
10097  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
10098  if (N <= 15)
10099  {
10100  // fixmap
10101  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x80 | (N & 0xF)));
10102  }
10103  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
10104  {
10105  // map 16
10106  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDE));
10107  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
10108  }
10109  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
10110  {
10111  // map 32
10112  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDF));
10113  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
10114  }
10115 
10116  // step 2: write each element
10117  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
10118  {
10119  write_msgpack(el.first);
10120  write_msgpack(el.second);
10121  }
10122  break;
10123  }
10124 
10125  default:
10126  break;
10127  }
10128  }
10129 
10136  void write_ubjson(const BasicJsonType& j, const bool use_count,
10137  const bool use_type, const bool add_prefix = true)
10138  {
10139  switch (j.type())
10140  {
10141  case value_t::null:
10142  {
10143  if (add_prefix)
10144  {
10145  oa->write_character(to_char_type('Z'));
10146  }
10147  break;
10148  }
10149 
10150  case value_t::boolean:
10151  {
10152  if (add_prefix)
10153  {
10154  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
10155  ? to_char_type('T')
10156  : to_char_type('F'));
10157  }
10158  break;
10159  }
10160 
10161  case value_t::number_integer:
10162  {
10163  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_integer, add_prefix);
10164  break;
10165  }
10166 
10167  case value_t::number_unsigned:
10168  {
10169  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_unsigned, add_prefix);
10170  break;
10171  }
10172 
10173  case value_t::number_float:
10174  {
10175  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_float, add_prefix);
10176  break;
10177  }
10178 
10179  case value_t::string:
10180  {
10181  if (add_prefix)
10182  {
10183  oa->write_character(to_char_type('S'));
10184  }
10185  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.string->size(), true);
10186  oa->write_characters(
10187  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
10188  j.m_value.string->size());
10189  break;
10190  }
10191 
10192  case value_t::array:
10193  {
10194  if (add_prefix)
10195  {
10196  oa->write_character(to_char_type('['));
10197  }
10198 
10199  bool prefix_required = true;
10200  if (use_type and not j.m_value.array->empty())
10201  {
10202  assert(use_count);
10203  const CharType first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front());
10204  const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin() + 1, j.end(),
10205  [this, first_prefix](const BasicJsonType & v)
10206  {
10207  return ubjson_prefix(v) == first_prefix;
10208  });
10209 
10210  if (same_prefix)
10211  {
10212  prefix_required = false;
10213  oa->write_character(to_char_type('$'));
10214  oa->write_character(first_prefix);
10215  }
10216  }
10217 
10218  if (use_count)
10219  {
10220  oa->write_character(to_char_type('#'));
10221  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.array->size(), true);
10222  }
10223 
10224  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
10225  {
10226  write_ubjson(el, use_count, use_type, prefix_required);
10227  }
10228 
10229  if (not use_count)
10230  {
10231  oa->write_character(to_char_type(']'));
10232  }
10233 
10234  break;
10235  }
10236 
10237  case value_t::object:
10238  {
10239  if (add_prefix)
10240  {
10241  oa->write_character(to_char_type('{'));
10242  }
10243 
10244  bool prefix_required = true;
10245  if (use_type and not j.m_value.object->empty())
10246  {
10247  assert(use_count);
10248  const CharType first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front());
10249  const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin(), j.end(),
10250  [this, first_prefix](const BasicJsonType & v)
10251  {
10252  return ubjson_prefix(v) == first_prefix;
10253  });
10254 
10255  if (same_prefix)
10256  {
10257  prefix_required = false;
10258  oa->write_character(to_char_type('$'));
10259  oa->write_character(first_prefix);
10260  }
10261  }
10262 
10263  if (use_count)
10264  {
10265  oa->write_character(to_char_type('#'));
10266  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.object->size(), true);
10267  }
10268 
10269  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
10270  {
10271  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(el.first.size(), true);
10272  oa->write_characters(
10273  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(el.first.c_str()),
10274  el.first.size());
10275  write_ubjson(el.second, use_count, use_type, prefix_required);
10276  }
10277 
10278  if (not use_count)
10279  {
10280  oa->write_character(to_char_type('}'));
10281  }
10282 
10283  break;
10284  }
10285 
10286  default:
10287  break;
10288  }
10289  }
10290 
10291  private:
10293  // BSON //
10295 
10300  static std::size_t calc_bson_entry_header_size(const string_t& name)
10301  {
10302  const auto it = name.find(static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0));
10303  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(it != BasicJsonType::string_t::npos))
10304  {
10305  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(409,
10306  "BSON key cannot contain code point U+0000 (at byte " + std::to_string(it) + ")"));
10307  }
10308 
10309  return /*id*/ 1ul + name.size() + /*zero-terminator*/1u;
10310  }
10311 
10315  void write_bson_entry_header(const string_t& name,
10316  const std::uint8_t element_type)
10317  {
10318  oa->write_character(to_char_type(element_type)); // boolean
10319  oa->write_characters(
10320  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(name.c_str()),
10321  name.size() + 1u);
10322  }
10323 
10327  void write_bson_boolean(const string_t& name,
10328  const bool value)
10329  {
10330  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x08);
10331  oa->write_character(value ? to_char_type(0x01) : to_char_type(0x00));
10332  }
10333 
10337  void write_bson_double(const string_t& name,
10338  const double value)
10339  {
10340  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x01);
10341  write_number<double, true>(value);
10342  }

10347  static std::size_t calc_bson_string_size(const string_t& value)
10348  {
10349  return sizeof(std::int32_t) + value.size() + 1ul;
10350  }

10355  void write_bson_string(const string_t& name,
10356  const string_t& value)
10357  {
10358  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x02);
10359 
10360  write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value.size() + 1ul));
10361  oa->write_characters(
10362  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(value.c_str()),
10363  value.size() + 1);
10364  }

10369  void write_bson_null(const string_t& name)
10370  {
10371  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x0A);
10372  }

10377  static std::size_t calc_bson_integer_size(const std::int64_t value)
10378  {
10379  return (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= value and value <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()
10380  ? sizeof(std::int32_t)
10381  : sizeof(std::int64_t);
10382  }
10383 
10387  void write_bson_integer(const string_t& name,
10388  const std::int64_t value)
10389  {
10390  if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= value and value <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
10391  {
10392  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x10); // int32
10393  write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value));
10394  }
10395  else
10396  {
10397  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x12); // int64
10398  write_number<std::int64_t, true>(static_cast<std::int64_t>(value));
10399  }
10400  }
10401 
10405  static constexpr std::size_t calc_bson_unsigned_size(const std::uint64_t value) noexcept
10406  {
10407  return (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()))
10408  ? sizeof(std::int32_t)
10409  : sizeof(std::int64_t);
10410  }
10411 
10415  void write_bson_unsigned(const string_t& name,
10416  const std::uint64_t value)
10417  {
10418  if (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()))
10419  {
10420  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x10 /* int32 */);
10421  write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value));
10422  }
10423  else if (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)()))
10424  {
10425  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x12 /* int64 */);
10426  write_number<std::int64_t, true>(static_cast<std::int64_t>(value));
10427  }
10428  else
10429  {
10430  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, "integer number " + std::to_string(value) + " cannot be represented by BSON as it does not fit int64"));
10431  }
10432  }

10437  void write_bson_object_entry(const string_t& name,
10438  const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value)
10439  {
10440  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x03); // object
10441  write_bson_object(value);
10442  }
10443 
10447  static std::size_t calc_bson_array_size(const typename BasicJsonType::array_t& value)
10448  {
10449  std::size_t embedded_document_size = 0ul;
10450  std::size_t array_index = 0ul;
10451 
10452  for (const auto& el : value)
10453  {
10454  embedded_document_size += calc_bson_element_size(std::to_string(array_index++), el);
10455  }
10456 
10457  return sizeof(std::int32_t) + embedded_document_size + 1ul;
10458  }
10459 
10463  void write_bson_array(const string_t& name,
10464  const typename BasicJsonType::array_t& value)
10465  {
10466  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x04); // array
10467  write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(calc_bson_array_size(value)));
10468 
10469  std::size_t array_index = 0ul;
10470 
10471  for (const auto& el : value)
10472  {
10473  write_bson_element(std::to_string(array_index++), el);
10474  }
10475 
10476  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
10477  }
10478 
10483  static std::size_t calc_bson_element_size(const string_t& name,
10484  const BasicJsonType& j)
10485  {
10486  const auto header_size = calc_bson_entry_header_size(name);
10487  switch (j.type())
10488  {
10489  case value_t::object:
10490  return header_size + calc_bson_object_size(*j.m_value.object);
10491 
10492  case value_t::array:
10493  return header_size + calc_bson_array_size(*j.m_value.array);
10494 
10495  case value_t::boolean:
10496  return header_size + 1ul;
10497 
10498  case value_t::number_float:
10499  return header_size + 8ul;
10500 
10501  case value_t::number_integer:
10502  return header_size + calc_bson_integer_size(j.m_value.number_integer);
10503 
10504  case value_t::number_unsigned:
10505  return header_size + calc_bson_unsigned_size(j.m_value.number_unsigned);
10506 
10507  case value_t::string:
10508  return header_size + calc_bson_string_size(*j.m_value.string);
10509 
10510  case value_t::null:
10511  return header_size + 0ul;
10512 
10513  // LCOV_EXCL_START
10514  default:
10515  assert(false);
10516  return 0ul;
10517  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10518  }
10519  }
10520 
10528  void write_bson_element(const string_t& name,
10529  const BasicJsonType& j)
10530  {
10531  switch (j.type())
10532  {
10533  case value_t::object:
10534  return write_bson_object_entry(name, *j.m_value.object);
10535 
10536  case value_t::array:
10537  return write_bson_array(name, *j.m_value.array);
10538 
10539  case value_t::boolean:
10540  return write_bson_boolean(name, j.m_value.boolean);
10541 
10542  case value_t::number_float:
10543  return write_bson_double(name, j.m_value.number_float);
10544 
10545  case value_t::number_integer:
10546  return write_bson_integer(name, j.m_value.number_integer);
10547 
10548  case value_t::number_unsigned:
10549  return write_bson_unsigned(name, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
10550 
10551  case value_t::string:
10552  return write_bson_string(name, *j.m_value.string);
10553 
10554  case value_t::null:
10555  return write_bson_null(name);
10556 
10557  // LCOV_EXCL_START
10558  default:
10559  assert(false);
10560  return;
10561  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10562  }
10563  }
10564 
10571  static std::size_t calc_bson_object_size(const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value)
10572  {
10573  std::size_t document_size = std::accumulate(value.begin(), value.end(), 0ul,
10574  [](size_t result, const typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type & el)
10575  {
10576  return result += calc_bson_element_size(el.first, el.second);
10577  });
10578 
10579  return sizeof(std::int32_t) + document_size + 1ul;
10580  }
10581 
10586  void write_bson_object(const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value)
10587  {
10588  write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(calc_bson_object_size(value)));
10589 
10590  for (const auto& el : value)
10591  {
10592  write_bson_element(el.first, el.second);
10593  }
10594 
10595  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
10596  }

10630  // UBJSON: write number (floating point)
10631  template<typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
10632  std::is_floating_point<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
10633  void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
10634  const bool add_prefix)
10635  {
10636  if (add_prefix)
10637  {
10638  oa->write_character(get_ubjson_float_prefix(n));
10639  }
10640  write_number(n);
10641  }
10642 
10643  // UBJSON: write number (unsigned integer)
10644  template<typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
10645  std::is_unsigned<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
10646  void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
10647  const bool add_prefix)
10648  {
10649  if (n <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)()))
10650  {
10651  if (add_prefix)
10652  {
10653  oa->write_character(to_char_type('i')); // int8
10654  }
10655  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(n));
10656  }
10657  else if (n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
10658  {
10659  if (add_prefix)
10660  {
10661  oa->write_character(to_char_type('U')); // uint8
10662  }
10663  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(n));
10664  }
10665  else if (n <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)()))
10666  {
10667  if (add_prefix)
10668  {
10669  oa->write_character(to_char_type('I')); // int16
10670  }
10671  write_number(static_cast<std::int16_t>(n));
10672  }
10673  else if (n <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()))
10674  {
10675  if (add_prefix)
10676  {
10677  oa->write_character(to_char_type('l')); // int32
10678  }
10679  write_number(static_cast<std::int32_t>(n));
10680  }
10681  else if (n <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)()))
10682  {
10683  if (add_prefix)
10684  {
10685  oa->write_character(to_char_type('L')); // int64
10686  }
10687  write_number(static_cast<std::int64_t>(n));
10688  }
10689  else
10690  {
10691  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, "integer number " + std::to_string(n) + " cannot be represented by UBJSON as it does not fit int64"));
10692  }
10693  }
10694 
10695  // UBJSON: write number (signed integer)
10696  template<typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
10697  std::is_signed<NumberType>::value and
10698  not std::is_floating_point<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
10699  void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
10700  const bool add_prefix)
10701  {
10702  if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)())
10703  {
10704  if (add_prefix)
10705  {
10706  oa->write_character(to_char_type('i')); // int8
10707  }
10708  write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(n));
10709  }
10710  else if (static_cast<std::int64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::min)()) <= n and n <= static_cast<std::int64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()))
10711  {
10712  if (add_prefix)
10713  {
10714  oa->write_character(to_char_type('U')); // uint8
10715  }
10716  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(n));
10717  }
10718  else if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)())
10719  {
10720  if (add_prefix)
10721  {
10722  oa->write_character(to_char_type('I')); // int16
10723  }
10724  write_number(static_cast<std::int16_t>(n));
10725  }
10726  else if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
10727  {
10728  if (add_prefix)
10729  {
10730  oa->write_character(to_char_type('l')); // int32
10731  }
10732  write_number(static_cast<std::int32_t>(n));
10733  }
10734  else if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)())
10735  {
10736  if (add_prefix)
10737  {
10738  oa->write_character(to_char_type('L')); // int64
10739  }
10740  write_number(static_cast<std::int64_t>(n));
10741  }
10742  // LCOV_EXCL_START
10743  else
10744  {
10745  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, "integer number " + std::to_string(n) + " cannot be represented by UBJSON as it does not fit int64"));
10746  }
10747  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10748  }
10749 
10759  CharType ubjson_prefix(const BasicJsonType& j) const noexcept
10760  {
10761  switch (j.type())
10762  {
10763  case value_t::null:
10764  return 'Z';
10765 
10766  case value_t::boolean:
10767  return j.m_value.boolean ? 'T' : 'F';
10768 
10769  case value_t::number_integer:
10770  {
10771  if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)())
10772  {
10773  return 'i';
10774  }
10775  if ((std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
10776  {
10777  return 'U';
10778  }
10779  if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)())
10780  {
10781  return 'I';
10782  }
10783  if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
10784  {
10785  return 'l';
10786  }
10787  // no check and assume int64_t (see note above)
10788  return 'L';
10789  }
10790 
10791  case value_t::number_unsigned:
10792  {
10793  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)())
10794  {
10795  return 'i';
10796  }
10797  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
10798  {
10799  return 'U';
10800  }
10801  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)())
10802  {
10803  return 'I';
10804  }
10805  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
10806  {
10807  return 'l';
10808  }
10809  // no check and assume int64_t (see note above)
10810  return 'L';
10811  }
10812 
10813  case value_t::number_float:
10814  return get_ubjson_float_prefix(j.m_value.number_float);
10815 
10816  case value_t::string:
10817  return 'S';
10818 
10819  case value_t::array:
10820  return '[';
10821 
10822  case value_t::object:
10823  return '{';
10824 
10825  default: // discarded values
10826  return 'N';
10827  }
10828  }
10829 
10830  static constexpr CharType get_ubjson_float_prefix(float /*unused*/)
10831  {
10832  return 'd'; // float 32
10833  }
10834 
10835  static constexpr CharType get_ubjson_float_prefix(double /*unused*/)
10836  {
10837  return 'D'; // float 64
10838  }
10839 
10841  // Utility functions //
10843 
10844  /*
10845  @brief write a number to output input
10846  @param[in] n number of type @a NumberType
10847  @tparam NumberType the type of the number
10848  @tparam OutputIsLittleEndian Set to true if output data is
10849  required to be little endian
10850 
10851  @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because bytes
10852  in CBOR, MessagePack, and UBJSON are stored in network order (big
10853  endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
10854  */
10855  template<typename NumberType, bool OutputIsLittleEndian = false>
10856  void write_number(const NumberType n)
10857  {
10858  // step 1: write number to array of length NumberType
10859  std::array<CharType, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
10860  std::memcpy(vec.data(), &n, sizeof(NumberType));
10861 
10862  // step 2: write array to output (with possible reordering)
10863  if (is_little_endian != OutputIsLittleEndian)
10864  {
10865  // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
10866  std::reverse(vec.begin(), vec.end());
10867  }
10868 
10869  oa->write_characters(vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
10870  }
10871 
10872  public:
10873  // The following to_char_type functions are implement the conversion
10874  // between uint8_t and CharType. In case CharType is not unsigned,
10875  // such a conversion is required to allow values greater than 128.
10876  // See <https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/1286> for a discussion.
10877  template < typename C = CharType,
10878  enable_if_t < std::is_signed<C>::value and std::is_signed<char>::value > * = nullptr >
10879  static constexpr CharType to_char_type(std::uint8_t x) noexcept
10880  {
10881  return *reinterpret_cast<char*>(&x);
10882  }
10883 
10884  template < typename C = CharType,
10885  enable_if_t < std::is_signed<C>::value and std::is_unsigned<char>::value > * = nullptr >
10886  static CharType to_char_type(std::uint8_t x) noexcept
10887  {
10888  static_assert(sizeof(std::uint8_t) == sizeof(CharType), "size of CharType must be equal to std::uint8_t");
10889  static_assert(std::is_pod<CharType>::value, "CharType must be POD");
10890  CharType result;
10891  std::memcpy(&result, &x, sizeof(x));
10892  return result;
10893  }
10894 
10895  template<typename C = CharType,
10896  enable_if_t<std::is_unsigned<C>::value>* = nullptr>
10897  static constexpr CharType to_char_type(std::uint8_t x) noexcept
10898  {
10899  return x;
10900  }
10901 
10902  template < typename InputCharType, typename C = CharType,
10903  enable_if_t <
10904  std::is_signed<C>::value and
10905  std::is_signed<char>::value and
10906  std::is_same<char, typename std::remove_cv<InputCharType>::type>::value
10907  > * = nullptr >
10908  static constexpr CharType to_char_type(InputCharType x) noexcept
10909  {
10910  return x;
10911  }
10912 
10913  private:
10915  const bool is_little_endian = binary_reader<BasicJsonType>::little_endianess();
10916 
10918  output_adapter_t<CharType> oa = nullptr;
10919 };
10920 } // namespace detail
10921 } // namespace nlohmann

10981 template <typename Target, typename Source>
10982 Target reinterpret_bits(const Source source)
10983 {
10984  static_assert(sizeof(Target) == sizeof(Source), "size mismatch");
10985 
10986  Target target;
10987  std::memcpy(&target, &source, sizeof(Source));
10988  return target;
10989 }

10991 struct diyfp // f * 2^e
10992 {

10996  int e = 0;
10997 
10998  constexpr diyfp(std::uint64_t f_, int e_) noexcept : f(f_), e(e_) {}
10999 
11004  static diyfp sub(const diyfp& x, const diyfp& y) noexcept
11005  {
11006  assert(x.e == y.e);
11007  assert(x.f >= y.f);
11008 
11009  return {x.f - y.f, x.e};
11010  }
11011 
11016  static diyfp mul(const diyfp& x, const diyfp& y) noexcept
11017  {
11018  static_assert(kPrecision == 64, "internal error");
11019 
11020  // Computes:
11021  // f = round((x.f * y.f) / 2^q)
11022  // e = x.e + y.e + q
11023 
11024  // Emulate the 64-bit * 64-bit multiplication:
11025  //
11026  // p = u * v
11027  // = (u_lo + 2^32 u_hi) (v_lo + 2^32 v_hi)
11028  // = (u_lo v_lo ) + 2^32 ((u_lo v_hi ) + (u_hi v_lo )) + 2^64 (u_hi v_hi )
11029  // = (p0 ) + 2^32 ((p1 ) + (p2 )) + 2^64 (p3 )
11030  // = (p0_lo + 2^32 p0_hi) + 2^32 ((p1_lo + 2^32 p1_hi) + (p2_lo + 2^32 p2_hi)) + 2^64 (p3 )
11031  // = (p0_lo ) + 2^32 (p0_hi + p1_lo + p2_lo ) + 2^64 (p1_hi + p2_hi + p3)
11032  // = (p0_lo ) + 2^32 (Q ) + 2^64 (H )
11033  // = (p0_lo ) + 2^32 (Q_lo + 2^32 Q_hi ) + 2^64 (H )
11034  //
11035  // (Since Q might be larger than 2^32 - 1)
11036  //
11037  // = (p0_lo + 2^32 Q_lo) + 2^64 (Q_hi + H)
11038  //
11039  // (Q_hi + H does not overflow a 64-bit int)
11040  //
11041  // = p_lo + 2^64 p_hi
11042 
11043  const std::uint64_t u_lo = x.f & 0xFFFFFFFFu;
11044  const std::uint64_t u_hi = x.f >> 32u;
11045  const std::uint64_t v_lo = y.f & 0xFFFFFFFFu;
11046  const std::uint64_t v_hi = y.f >> 32u;
11047 
11048  const std::uint64_t p0 = u_lo * v_lo;
11049  const std::uint64_t p1 = u_lo * v_hi;
11050  const std::uint64_t p2 = u_hi * v_lo;
11051  const std::uint64_t p3 = u_hi * v_hi;
11052 
11053  const std::uint64_t p0_hi = p0 >> 32u;
11054  const std::uint64_t p1_lo = p1 & 0xFFFFFFFFu;
11055  const std::uint64_t p1_hi = p1 >> 32u;
11056  const std::uint64_t p2_lo = p2 & 0xFFFFFFFFu;
11057  const std::uint64_t p2_hi = p2 >> 32u;
11058 
11059  std::uint64_t Q = p0_hi + p1_lo + p2_lo;
11060 
11061  // The full product might now be computed as
11062  //
11063  // p_hi = p3 + p2_hi + p1_hi + (Q >> 32)
11064  // p_lo = p0_lo + (Q << 32)
11065  //
11066  // But in this particular case here, the full p_lo is not required.
11067  // Effectively we only need to add the highest bit in p_lo to p_hi (and
11068  // Q_hi + 1 does not overflow).
11069 
11070  Q += std::uint64_t{1} << (64u - 32u - 1u); // round, ties up
11071 
11072  const std::uint64_t h = p3 + p2_hi + p1_hi + (Q >> 32u);
11073 
11074  return {h, x.e + y.e + 64};
11075  }
11076 
11081  static diyfp normalize(diyfp x) noexcept
11082  {
11083  assert(x.f != 0);
11084 
11085  while ((x.f >> 63u) == 0)
11086  {
11087  x.f <<= 1u;
11088  x.e--;
11089  }
11090 
11091  return x;
11092  }
11093 
11098  static diyfp normalize_to(const diyfp& x, const int target_exponent) noexcept
11099  {
11100  const int delta = x.e - target_exponent;
11101 
11102  assert(delta >= 0);
11103  assert(((x.f << delta) >> delta) == x.f);
11104 
11105  return {x.f << delta, target_exponent};
11106  }
11107 };
11108 
11109 struct boundaries
11110 {
11111  diyfp w;
11112  diyfp minus;
11113  diyfp plus;
11114 };
11115 
11122 template <typename FloatType>
11123 boundaries compute_boundaries(FloatType value)
11124 {
11125  assert(std::isfinite(value));
11126  assert(value > 0);
11127 
11128  // Convert the IEEE representation into a diyfp.
11129  //
11130  // If v is denormal:
11131  // value = 0.F * 2^(1 - bias) = ( F) * 2^(1 - bias - (p-1))
11132  // If v is normalized:
11133  // value = 1.F * 2^(E - bias) = (2^(p-1) + F) * 2^(E - bias - (p-1))
11134 
11135  static_assert(std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::is_iec559,
11136  "internal error: dtoa_short requires an IEEE-754 floating-point implementation");
11137 
11138  constexpr int kPrecision = std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::digits; // = p (includes the hidden bit)
11139  constexpr int kBias = std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_exponent - 1 + (kPrecision - 1);
11140  constexpr int kMinExp = 1 - kBias;
11141  constexpr std::uint64_t kHiddenBit = std::uint64_t{1} << (kPrecision - 1); // = 2^(p-1)
11142 
11143  using bits_type = typename std::conditional<kPrecision == 24, std::uint32_t, std::uint64_t >::type;
11144 
11145  const std::uint64_t bits = reinterpret_bits<bits_type>(value);
11146  const std::uint64_t E = bits >> (kPrecision - 1);
11147  const std::uint64_t F = bits & (kHiddenBit - 1);
11148 
11149  const bool is_denormal = E == 0;
11150  const diyfp v = is_denormal
11151  ? diyfp(F, kMinExp)
11152  : diyfp(F + kHiddenBit, static_cast<int>(E) - kBias);
11153 
11154  // Compute the boundaries m- and m+ of the floating-point value
11155  // v = f * 2^e.
11156  //
11157  // Determine v- and v+, the floating-point predecessor and successor if v,
11158  // respectively.
11159  //
11160  // v- = v - 2^e if f != 2^(p-1) or e == e_min (A)
11161  // = v - 2^(e-1) if f == 2^(p-1) and e > e_min (B)
11162  //
11163  // v+ = v + 2^e
11164  //
11165  // Let m- = (v- + v) / 2 and m+ = (v + v+) / 2. All real numbers _strictly_
11166  // between m- and m+ round to v, regardless of how the input rounding
11167  // algorithm breaks ties.
11168  //
11169  // ---+-------------+-------------+-------------+-------------+--- (A)
11170  // v- m- v m+ v+
11171  //
11172  // -----------------+------+------+-------------+-------------+--- (B)
11173  // v- m- v m+ v+
11174 
11175  const bool lower_boundary_is_closer = F == 0 and E > 1;
11176  const diyfp m_plus = diyfp(2 * v.f + 1, v.e - 1);
11177  const diyfp m_minus = lower_boundary_is_closer
11178  ? diyfp(4 * v.f - 1, v.e - 2) // (B)
11179  : diyfp(2 * v.f - 1, v.e - 1); // (A)
11180 
11181  // Determine the normalized w+ = m+.
11182  const diyfp w_plus = diyfp::normalize(m_plus);
11183 
11184  // Determine w- = m- such that e_(w-) = e_(w+).
11185  const diyfp w_minus = diyfp::normalize_to(m_minus, w_plus.e);
11186 
11187  return {diyfp::normalize(v), w_minus, w_plus};
11188 }
11189 
11190 // Given normalized diyfp w, Grisu needs to find a (normalized) cached
11191 // power-of-ten c, such that the exponent of the product c * w = f * 2^e lies
11192 // within a certain range [alpha, gamma] (Definition 3.2 from [1])
11193 //
11194 // alpha <= e = e_c + e_w + q <= gamma
11195 //
11196 // or
11197 //
11198 // f_c * f_w * 2^alpha <= f_c 2^(e_c) * f_w 2^(e_w) * 2^q
11199 // <= f_c * f_w * 2^gamma
11200 //
11201 // Since c and w are normalized, i.e. 2^(q-1) <= f < 2^q, this implies
11202 //
11203 // 2^(q-1) * 2^(q-1) * 2^alpha <= c * w * 2^q < 2^q * 2^q * 2^gamma
11204 //
11205 // or
11206 //
11207 // 2^(q - 2 + alpha) <= c * w < 2^(q + gamma)
11208 //
11209 // The choice of (alpha,gamma) determines the size of the table and the form of
11210 // the digit generation procedure. Using (alpha,gamma)=(-60,-32) works out well
11211 // in practice:
11212 //
11213 // The idea is to cut the number c * w = f * 2^e into two parts, which can be
11214 // processed independently: An integral part p1, and a fractional part p2:
11215 //
11216 // f * 2^e = ( (f div 2^-e) * 2^-e + (f mod 2^-e) ) * 2^e
11217 // = (f div 2^-e) + (f mod 2^-e) * 2^e
11218 // = p1 + p2 * 2^e
11219 //
11220 // The conversion of p1 into decimal form requires a series of divisions and
11221 // modulos by (a power of) 10. These operations are faster for 32-bit than for
11222 // 64-bit integers, so p1 should ideally fit into a 32-bit integer. This can be
11223 // achieved by choosing
11224 //
11225 // -e >= 32 or e <= -32 := gamma
11226 //
11227 // In order to convert the fractional part
11228 //
11229 // p2 * 2^e = p2 / 2^-e = d[-1] / 10^1 + d[-2] / 10^2 + ...
11230 //
11231 // into decimal form, the fraction is repeatedly multiplied by 10 and the digits
11232 // d[-i] are extracted in order:
11233 //
11234 // (10 * p2) div 2^-e = d[-1]
11235 // (10 * p2) mod 2^-e = d[-2] / 10^1 + ...
11236 //
11237 // The multiplication by 10 must not overflow. It is sufficient to choose
11238 //
11239 // 10 * p2 < 16 * p2 = 2^4 * p2 <= 2^64.
11240 //
11241 // Since p2 = f mod 2^-e < 2^-e,
11242 //
11243 // -e <= 60 or e >= -60 := alpha
11244 
11245 constexpr int kAlpha = -60;
11246 constexpr int kGamma = -32;
11247 
11248 struct cached_power // c = f * 2^e ~= 10^k
11249 {
11250  std::uint64_t f;
11251  int e;
11252  int k;
11253 };
11254 
11262 inline cached_power get_cached_power_for_binary_exponent(int e)
11263 {
11264  // Now
11265  //
11266  // alpha <= e_c + e + q <= gamma (1)
11267  // ==> f_c * 2^alpha <= c * 2^e * 2^q
11268  //
11269  // and since the c's are normalized, 2^(q-1) <= f_c,
11270  //
11271  // ==> 2^(q - 1 + alpha) <= c * 2^(e + q)
11272  // ==> 2^(alpha - e - 1) <= c
11273  //
11274  // If c were an exakt power of ten, i.e. c = 10^k, one may determine k as
11275  //
11276  // k = ceil( log_10( 2^(alpha - e - 1) ) )
11277  // = ceil( (alpha - e - 1) * log_10(2) )
11278  //
11279  // From the paper:
11280  // "In theory the result of the procedure could be wrong since c is rounded,
11281  // and the computation itself is approximated [...]. In practice, however,
11282  // this simple function is sufficient."
11283  //
11284  // For IEEE double precision floating-point numbers converted into
11285  // normalized diyfp's w = f * 2^e, with q = 64,
11286  //
11287  // e >= -1022 (min IEEE exponent)
11288  // -52 (p - 1)
11289  // -52 (p - 1, possibly normalize denormal IEEE numbers)
11290  // -11 (normalize the diyfp)
11291  // = -1137
11292  //
11293  // and
11294  //
11295  // e <= +1023 (max IEEE exponent)
11296  // -52 (p - 1)
11297  // -11 (normalize the diyfp)
11298  // = 960
11299  //
11300  // This binary exponent range [-1137,960] results in a decimal exponent
11301  // range [-307,324]. One does not need to store a cached power for each
11302  // k in this range. For each such k it suffices to find a cached power
11303  // such that the exponent of the product lies in [alpha,gamma].
11304  // This implies that the difference of the decimal exponents of adjacent
11305  // table entries must be less than or equal to
11306  //
11307  // floor( (gamma - alpha) * log_10(2) ) = 8.
11308  //
11309  // (A smaller distance gamma-alpha would require a larger table.)
11310 
11311  // NB:
11312  // Actually this function returns c, such that -60 <= e_c + e + 64 <= -34.
11313 
11314  constexpr int kCachedPowersMinDecExp = -300;
11315  constexpr int kCachedPowersDecStep = 8;

11402  // This computation gives exactly the same results for k as
11403  // k = ceil((kAlpha - e - 1) * 0.30102999566398114)
11404  // for |e| <= 1500, but doesn't require floating-point operations.
11405  // NB: log_10(2) ~= 78913 / 2^18
11406  assert(e >= -1500);
11407  assert(e <= 1500);
11408  const int f = kAlpha - e - 1;
11409  const int k = (f * 78913) / (1 << 18) + static_cast<int>(f > 0);
11410 
11411  const int index = (-kCachedPowersMinDecExp + k + (kCachedPowersDecStep - 1)) / kCachedPowersDecStep;
11412  assert(index >= 0);
11413  assert(static_cast<std::size_t>(index) < kCachedPowers.size());
11414 
11415  const cached_power cached = kCachedPowers[static_cast<std::size_t>(index)];
11416  assert(kAlpha <= cached.e + e + 64);
11417  assert(kGamma >= cached.e + e + 64);
11418 
11419  return cached;
11420 }
