20213 
20215 
20217  // JSON Patch functions //
20219 
20222 
20270  basic_json patch(const basic_json& json_patch) const
20271  {
20272  // make a working copy to apply the patch to
20273  basic_json result = *this;
20274 
20275  // the valid JSON Patch operations
20276  enum class patch_operations {add, remove, replace, move, copy, test, invalid};
20277 
20278  const auto get_op = [](const std::string & op)
20279  {
20280  if (op == "add")
20281  {
20282  return patch_operations::add;
20283  }
20284  if (op == "remove")
20285  {
20286  return patch_operations::remove;
20287  }
20288  if (op == "replace")
20289  {
20290  return patch_operations::replace;
20291  }
20292  if (op == "move")
20293  {
20294  return patch_operations::move;
20295  }
20296  if (op == "copy")
20297  {
20298  return patch_operations::copy;
20299  }
20300  if (op == "test")
20301  {
20302  return patch_operations::test;
20303  }
20304 
20305  return patch_operations::invalid;
20306  };
20307 
20308  // wrapper for "add" operation; add value at ptr
20309  const auto operation_add = [&result](json_pointer & ptr, basic_json val)
20310  {
20311  // adding to the root of the target document means replacing it
20312  if (ptr.empty())
20313  {
20314  result = val;
20315  return;
20316  }
20317 
20318  // make sure the top element of the pointer exists
20319  json_pointer top_pointer = ptr.top();
20320  if (top_pointer != ptr)
20321  {
20322  result.at(top_pointer);
20323  }
20324 
20325  // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
20326  const auto last_path = ptr.back();
20327  ptr.pop_back();
20328  basic_json& parent = result[ptr];
20329 
20330  switch (parent.m_type)
20331  {
20332  case value_t::null:
20333  case value_t::object:
20334  {
20335  // use operator[] to add value
20336  parent[last_path] = val;
20337  break;
20338  }
20339 
20340  case value_t::array:
20341  {
20342  if (last_path == "-")
20343  {
20344  // special case: append to back
20345  parent.push_back(val);
20346  }
20347  else
20348  {
20349  const auto idx = json_pointer::array_index(last_path);
20350  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(static_cast<size_type>(idx) > parent.size()))
20351  {
20352  // avoid undefined behavior
20353  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(401, "array index " + std::to_string(idx) + " is out of range"));
20354  }
20355 
20356  // default case: insert add offset
20357  parent.insert(parent.begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(idx), val);
20358  }
20359  break;
20360  }
20361 
20362  // if there exists a parent it cannot be primitive
20363  default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
20364  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
20365  }
20366  };
20367 
20368  // wrapper for "remove" operation; remove value at ptr
20369  const auto operation_remove = [&result](json_pointer & ptr)
20370  {
20371  // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
20372  const auto last_path = ptr.back();
20373  ptr.pop_back();
20374  basic_json& parent = result.at(ptr);
20375 
20376  // remove child
20377  if (parent.is_object())
20378  {
20379  // perform range check
20380  auto it = parent.find(last_path);
20381  if (JSON_LIKELY(it != parent.end()))
20382  {
20383  parent.erase(it);
20384  }
20385  else
20386  {
20387  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(403, "key '" + last_path + "' not found"));
20388  }
20389  }
20390  else if (parent.is_array())
20391  {
20392  // note erase performs range check
20393  parent.erase(static_cast<size_type>(json_pointer::array_index(last_path)));
20394  }
20395  };
20396 
20397  // type check: top level value must be an array
20398  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not json_patch.is_array()))
20399  {
20400  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(104, 0, "JSON patch must be an array of objects"));
20401  }
20402 
20403  // iterate and apply the operations
20404  for (const auto& val : json_patch)
20405  {
20406  // wrapper to get a value for an operation
20407  const auto get_value = [&val](const std::string & op,
20408  const std::string & member,
20409  bool string_type) -> basic_json &
20410  {
20411  // find value
20412  auto it = val.m_value.object->find(member);
20413 
20414  // context-sensitive error message
20415  const auto error_msg = (op == "op") ? "operation" : "operation '" + op + "'";
20416 
20417  // check if desired value is present
20418  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(it == val.m_value.object->end()))
20419  {
20420  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, error_msg + " must have member '" + member + "'"));
20421  }
20422 
20423  // check if result is of type string
20424  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(string_type and not it->second.is_string()))
20425  {
20426  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, error_msg + " must have string member '" + member + "'"));
20427  }
20428 
20429  // no error: return value
20430  return it->second;
20431  };
20432 
20433  // type check: every element of the array must be an object
20434  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not val.is_object()))
20435  {
20436  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(104, 0, "JSON patch must be an array of objects"));
20437  }
20438 
20439  // collect mandatory members
20440  const std::string op = get_value("op", "op", true);
20441  const std::string path = get_value(op, "path", true);
20442  json_pointer ptr(path);
20443 
20444  switch (get_op(op))
20445  {
20446  case patch_operations::add:
20447  {
20448  operation_add(ptr, get_value("add", "value", false));
20449  break;
20450  }
20451 
20452  case patch_operations::remove:
20453  {
20454  operation_remove(ptr);
20455  break;
20456  }
20457 
20458  case patch_operations::replace:
20459  {
20460  // the "path" location must exist - use at()
20461  result.at(ptr) = get_value("replace", "value", false);
20462  break;
20463  }
20464 
20465  case patch_operations::move:
20466  {
20467  const std::string from_path = get_value("move", "from", true);
20468  json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
20469 
20470  // the "from" location must exist - use at()
20471  basic_json v = result.at(from_ptr);
20472 
20473  // The move operation is functionally identical to a
20474  // "remove" operation on the "from" location, followed
20475  // immediately by an "add" operation at the target
20476  // location with the value that was just removed.
20477  operation_remove(from_ptr);
20478  operation_add(ptr, v);
20479  break;
20480  }
20481 
20482  case patch_operations::copy:
20483  {
20484  const std::string from_path = get_value("copy", "from", true);
20485  const json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
20486 
20487  // the "from" location must exist - use at()
20488  basic_json v = result.at(from_ptr);
20489 
20490  // The copy is functionally identical to an "add"
20491  // operation at the target location using the value
20492  // specified in the "from" member.
20493  operation_add(ptr, v);
20494  break;
20495  }
20496 
20497  case patch_operations::test:
20498  {
20499  bool success = false;
20500  JSON_TRY
20501  {
20502  // check if "value" matches the one at "path"
20503  // the "path" location must exist - use at()
20504  success = (result.at(ptr) == get_value("test", "value", false));
20505  }
20506  JSON_INTERNAL_CATCH (out_of_range&)
20507  {
20508  // ignore out of range errors: success remains false
20509  }
20510 
20511  // throw an exception if test fails
20512  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not success))
20513  {
20514  JSON_THROW(other_error::create(501, "unsuccessful: " + val.dump()));
20515  }
20516 
20517  break;
20518  }
20519 
20520  default:
20521  {
20522  // op must be "add", "remove", "replace", "move", "copy", or
20523  // "test"
20524  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, "operation value '" + op + "' is invalid"));
20525  }
20526  }
20527  }
20528 
20529  return result;
20530  }
20531 
20565  JSON_NODISCARD
20566  static basic_json diff(const basic_json& source, const basic_json& target,
20567  const std::string& path = "")
20568  {
20569  // the patch
20570  basic_json result(value_t::array);
20571 
20572  // if the values are the same, return empty patch
20573  if (source == target)
20574  {
20575  return result;
20576  }
20577 
20578  if (source.type() != target.type())
20579  {
20580  // different types: replace value
20581  result.push_back(
20582  {
20583  {"op", "replace"}, {"path", path}, {"value", target}
20584  });
20585  return result;
20586  }
20587 
20588  switch (source.type())
20589  {
20590  case value_t::array:
20591  {
20592  // first pass: traverse common elements
20593  std::size_t i = 0;
20594  while (i < source.size() and i < target.size())
20595  {
20596  // recursive call to compare array values at index i
20597  auto temp_diff = diff(source[i], target[i], path + "/" + std::to_string(i));
20598  result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
20599  ++i;
20600  }
20601 
20602  // i now reached the end of at least one array
20603  // in a second pass, traverse the remaining elements
20604 
20605  // remove my remaining elements
20606  const auto end_index = static_cast<difference_type>(result.size());
20607  while (i < source.size())
20608  {
20609  // add operations in reverse order to avoid invalid
20610  // indices
20611  result.insert(result.begin() + end_index, object(
20612  {
20613  {"op", "remove"},
20614  {"path", path + "/" + std::to_string(i)}
20615  }));
20616  ++i;
20617  }
20618 
20619  // add other remaining elements
20620  while (i < target.size())
20621  {
20622  result.push_back(
20623  {
20624  {"op", "add"},
20625  {"path", path + "/" + std::to_string(i)},
20626  {"value", target[i]}
20627  });
20628  ++i;
20629  }
20630 
20631  break;
20632  }
20633 
20634  case value_t::object:
20635  {
20636  // first pass: traverse this object's elements
20637  for (auto it = source.cbegin(); it != source.cend(); ++it)
20638  {
20639  // escape the key name to be used in a JSON patch
20640  const auto key = json_pointer::escape(it.key());
20641 
20642  if (target.find(it.key()) != target.end())
20643  {
20644  // recursive call to compare object values at key it
20645  auto temp_diff = diff(it.value(), target[it.key()], path + "/" + key);
20646  result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
20647  }
20648  else
20649  {
20650  // found a key that is not in o -> remove it
20651  result.push_back(object(
20652  {
20653  {"op", "remove"}, {"path", path + "/" + key}
20654  }));
20655  }
20656  }
20657 
20658  // second pass: traverse other object's elements
20659  for (auto it = target.cbegin(); it != target.cend(); ++it)
20660  {
20661  if (source.find(it.key()) == source.end())
20662  {
20663  // found a key that is not in this -> add it
20664  const auto key = json_pointer::escape(it.key());
20665  result.push_back(
20666  {
20667  {"op", "add"}, {"path", path + "/" + key},
20668  {"value", it.value()}
20669  });
20670  }
20671  }
20672 
20673  break;
20674  }
20675 
20676  default:
20677  {
20678  // both primitive type: replace value
20679  result.push_back(
20680  {
20681  {"op", "replace"}, {"path", path}, {"value", target}
20682  });
20683  break;
20684  }
20685  }
20686 
20687  return result;
20688  }
20689 
20691 
20693  // JSON Merge Patch functions //
20695 
20698 
20741  void merge_patch(const basic_json& apply_patch)
20742  {
20743  if (apply_patch.is_object())
20744  {
20745  if (not is_object())
20746  {
20747  *this = object();
20748  }
20749  for (auto it = apply_patch.begin(); it != apply_patch.end(); ++it)
20750  {
20751  if (it.value().is_null())
20752  {
20753  erase(it.key());
20754  }
20755  else
20756  {
20757  operator[](it.key()).merge_patch(it.value());
20758  }
20759  }
20760  }
20761  else
20762  {
20763  *this = apply_patch;
20764  }
20765  }
20766 
20768 };
